Since then we've enjoyed traveling with AirBnB across the US, around Australia, in Hong Kong, and also in Vietnam.

As guests we're always out & about most of the time and won't be intruding too much.

So here's an open invitation to come check us out.

My partner Vinh is a keen traveler who works a lot with artists and designers in his coaching practice. He's the energetic, vibrant one...

I lived in Bolivia for a year as a young man just out of school and have worked in social enterprises and not for profits over the years. I'm the more serious, bookish one (with a wicked sense of humour though). Currently working in financial services too...

One of the things we're keen to do is catch up with some social entrepreneurs, coworkers, not for profits, and microfinanciers.

We're particularly interested social enterprise, coworking, and small business incubators & mentoring projects.

More that happy to answer any questions that you may have.

All the best,

Vinh & Stuart
Australia

I am a Canadian who has made Australia her home for over ten years. I appreciate a good place to stay, having had many travel adventures myself.  My home is in Balgowlah, a pretty harbourside village next to Manly with easy access by bus or ferry to Sydney CBD.

I've moved countries twice in the span of 10 years and I've begun to realise that meeting new people and living in new environments is really what makes me tick. I work in the arts, communication & government health sector. I live in a 2-bedroom apartment and had the opportunity to meet and host a countless number of travellers. I am interested in living a sustainable life, so hopefully I can influence people around me to live sustainably.

I am originally Scottish but I have made Sydney my home for the last 14 years, I  love the city and the country and would not live anywhere else. I am well travelled, I enjoy seeing new things, having new experiences, challenging myself and meeting new people.
I work for myself in the corporate work, which can mean I have long days and I may not be around much Mon to Fri. I have a work hard, play hard attitude and have a varied social life, lots of different groups of friends, always doing something.   I am open minded and value peoples differences, though I hate the term, this is a GLBTQ friendly house. 
I would describe myself as a bit of a "foodie"; I cook, host dinner parties/ soirees, I eatout and I travel for food. I enjoy the finer things in life, nice surroundings, beautiful clothes/ shoes/handbags, fine wine etc. I love shopping for the unusual from markets to tucked away little shops, designer sample sales to high end boutiques. I am creative, collect contemporary art and enjoy the creative arts.  
I am a very warm host and will try to meet the needs of all guests. 
If someone wants their privacy and just to have a bed for a few nights and do their own thing that is fine. 
If someone wants to pick my brain about what to do, where to go etc that is also fine. 
If someone wants to share a glass of wine and tell me about themselves that it also fine. 
I also have a little dog, Charlie he is a 9yr old Pomeranian that I have had since he was a puppy, he can gety a little excitable but generally is friendly and very cute.  
My life's motto are "Be the best version of you" & " I can do that"
We are a professional, married couple with 2 children.
Hi everyone,  I look forward to welcoming you to this beautiful area of Sydney in the near future!

Curious about the world and full of wanderlust. Recently traded an established career in health research for full time study to retrain as a medical doctor. As a traveller, I seek out experiences that offer me a glimpse into what local life is like in the places I visit. I also rent out my loft in Sydney occasionally and love that this allows me to help share our beautiful harbour city with guests from all over the world.

I have had a holiday rental business, Ruby's Holiday Residences, for more than 11 years now. I feel like I am running my own private hotel, but the rooms are just spread out over many sites!
I love to travel (my friends call me a gypsy!) and spend my year between Sydney, London and Nice. I run my business from anywhere. But it's work everyday in this industry! No rest for the wicked!
Travel, food, cinema, more travel and more food are my passions. I love all things French, so any travel in France, French food or cinema are my favourites.

We offer a selection of beautifully furnished holiday homes with modern comforts & spacious living areas. All homes are immaculately kept & located in prime locations near the city & beach with public transportation nearby.

I take great pleasure in hosting airbnb guests from all over the world in my lovely apartment.I am an artist and photographer with a love for meeting new people, I have a great collection of books and have made the apartment to be an experience.

Faber est suae quisquae fortunae

We became Airbnb.com hosts back in December 2010.  I was originally an architect, but worked in IT sales/marketing for the past 30 years.  Semi-retired now, but still manage consulting projects involving the Internet for small-medium businesses. 

I call myself an Internet Architect on my business card these days.  Most of my current projects involve marketing using social media tools.

A born and bred Sydneysider, I lived in UK for 10 years till 1984.  I have done lots of travel in Europe, Turkey, Egypt, Jordan, Sri Lanka, Thailand, China, Vietnam, Japan, New Zealand, USA. 

Studio Yindi incorporates the things I look for when selecting boutique hotels, pensions, hostels and B&Bs for myself - space, privacy, wifi Internet access, reading light at the bedside, comfortable and practical for working while "on the road", a bit unusual, a little surprise, value for money. 

My own preferences are for adventure and off the beaten track, rather than luxury, international 5 star. 

I love meeting travellers from all parts of the world, and helping them enjoy the experience of a first visit to Sydney.

Lots of experience assisting overseas based friends and colleagues to see the best parts of Sydney, using public transport, and avoiding the expensive tourist services.

Messing about on boats is one of my passions. I have a 7.2 m (24') yacht moored nearby on the harbour and know a lot about the nice parts of our extensive waterways, including its part in Australian history.  I love sharing tips on how to see the best of the harbour, using inexpensive public ferries, plus strolls around Cremorne Point from Mosman Bay, or the 3 - 4 hour walk from the Spit to Manly, via Sydney Harbour National Park.

My major work project now as a volunteer Director of the Keeping Place centre for aboriginal art, culture and history.  Our biggest challenge is finding a permanent physical home for 2000+ pieces of art and sculpture, plus 200,000+ photographs!

We are a Swedish-Australian family, which means lots of travelling.

2015
Anna Carin in Sweden for her niece's wedding mid year.
David (20) has deferred 2nd year at UTS to backpack around Europe.
Ellinor (19) at Sydney Uni but semester break in Europe.
Robert (16) school UK soccer tour, and soon in mid-year, a Father-Son bonding adventure trip for 3 weeks to Hawaii.
I wake up every morning and wish the best for everyone.
We are a photographer and writer from Sydney's Northern Beaches where we live with our family. We love the beach, art, reading and gardening.

I live near the best beach in Sydney - no, not Bondi but close, Coogee beach. I'm a family man with 3 daughters. When I get any time off from them, I love playing tennis, saxophone and piano and hanging out with friends. Oh, and I also work - I'm afraid I'm very boring as my life's motto is get the work done, then play. But still somehow we get to  travel each year and sometimes stay in other peoples houses and apartments, so I know and appreciate the other side of this (Website hidden by Airbnb) favorite destinations have been Mozambique, Thailand, China, Bali and Argentina. 

But one of the best places to live in this world has to be Coogee, Sydney and I consider myself extremely lucky for that (and for my 3 daughters, of-course). We live 2 blocks away from the Pumpkin (as we call the house listed here), so I am just a minute away if anyone needs help, from a blown light bulb to where to go shopping etc.

I really enjoy the way people are blown away when they first walk into the Pumpkin. Even though they have seen the photos, they are so excited and incredulous about staying there themselves. I also like that when they leave, they report being very satisfied and happy with their stay.

We are from Ireland, but have lived in Sydney for over 30 years.  We enjoy travelling, theatre, movies, nature, walking, and meeting  people. We are happy to help in any way we can, but you can be assured of total privacy if you just want to relax and do your own thing.

Tour Director and Guide, lead tours all over Australia and NZ....and a good source of advice for activities in Sydney and further afield across Australia and NZ. My family live in Sydney, I have a 2 yr old grandson who brings us much joy and entertainment. My home is in a beautiful beach side location, with views to the ocean and across the valley to the NE. Its sunny and warm in winter, cooling sea breezes in summer, no air-con needed! The duplex is completely separate, accessed via one short flight of steps. Well suited to a couple or friends looking for a 'home away from home' for 2+ weeks.

We're an Australian couple both global travelers, dedicated yogis, with an appreciation for design, architectural details and good eating.

Ever since Airbnb started in 2011, both of us (both separately and together) have listed our home/s in Sydney and (formerly) in Hong Kong.  We've successfully hosted and enjoyed meeting a swag of guests in the Airbnb international community from all cultures—some whom we call friends and continue to stay in contact with. 

As Airbnb hosts, aside from covering the accommodation basics, our style is to be friendly and responsive to the needs of our guests.  Are you a first-time visitor to Sydney who's coming without a full itinerary?  We can give you the local scoop on a lot of great activities that you won't read about online or in your guide books (pottery classes? suggestions for families and kids?)  Or, for guests who already know the city or have it all figured out or "just need a place to crash", that's cool with us too.

As Airbnb guests, we've had fantastic stays with hosts in cities such as San Francisco, Istanbul and Berlin—enjoying the flexible option of the homestay which often beats the generic-faceless hotel-stay (especially when travelling solo), and also for its' much more affordable rate.  We also recognise that Airbnb hosts make excellent guests since they treat homes as if they were our own and take extra care to return everything as it was found.

When not hosting, Brendt, a Traditional Chinese Medicine doctor who also speaks fluent Mandarin, can usually be found whiling an afternoon at the beach with a book, where he's the most happy (having grown up in sunny Queensland). He also bounces to-and-from Goa, India, where he helps manage at a yoga retreat center called Samata during the high-peak tourism season for 4-5 months of the year.  

Saysana, who also speaks French, enjoys to be the eternal flaneur in urban cities, roaming the markets, bazaars, hopping on a bicycle, and seeking out where the next Argentine milonga may be.

Don't forget your bathers. THE BEST start to a day in Sydney.

I work for myself as a commercial photographer and I love it!
I have an office at home so sometimes i'm at home during the day working, so can greet you when you arrive, whilst other times I'm out working on location, if this is the case I will leave a key out for you and communicate this with you via the Air BnB message service.
Harry (my dog) and I go walking every morning. She will greet you very enthusiastically when you arrive at the house and be ready for a scratch on her tummy from you to say hello.
It's great to meeting and hosting new people from all over the world and have a chat over a coffee or a wine and share my local knowledge with you, and hear about your travelling experiences, but I also respect your privacy, and my work keeps me pretty busy too!
I love being an Air BnB host and have made some great friends from the guests who have stayed with me from all over the world.
I am aware a lot of people are looking for longer term accommodation, however, short term stays suits me, and I'm not looking for any guests to stay longer than 1 month.
I look forward to meeting you.

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
Hi, welcome to my page

I am a pretty laid back professional, I work in the city Monday-Friday as a policy advisor for a government department and enjoy the beach and social lifestyle of Bondi and Sydney on my days off. 

I am healthy, energetic, fun/serious, open minded, you'll know up front what you need to know about sharing a place with me and I hope to expect that you will do the same with me so that we share the space in harmony. If you book the entire apartment I will greet you and leave you to enjoy your holiday in peace.

I have travelled extensively and appreciate the little things that can make an arrival/stay in a strange or new city/country a positive experience.

What I enjoy: reading, the arts, arthouse/international films, people, learning, puzzles, walking, riding my bike, sitting in cafes discussing everything and anything, people watching, catching up with my kids (they've left home), music, silence, nature, the ocean and much much more :)

Early 30s. Professional. Traveller, Business Owner, Travelpreneur (yes I get paid to travel and I can show you how) Interested in the variety and backgrounds of people and couch surfing without strings.

Friendly, accommodating and willing to help you with inside knowledge whether you are here for a holiday, conference or just a weekend visit. Either way, I will help accommodate with your needs and personal space.

My personal motto would be, "Never wish life was better, only you were Better"

::::THIS IS WHAT I WILL TELL YOU TO EXPECT POSITIVE AND NEGATIVES::::

Positive: I will help and make things easier for you in your stay, pick up from station when I can, leave food out if your hungry and you don't mind trying my/my family's food, and try and give you tips to save yourself here and there. I will as a host try and take care of you.

Negative: I am not a butler, you will be expected to clean up after yourself, follow house rules, keep the kitchen and public area in some order. You have to wear slippers (YES it is an Asian House), and sometimes other people will be staying so you do have to respect their space. I will also expect you to communicate if you wish to extend your stay or are running late.
___________________________________________________________________




All prices include, fully furnished, basic breakfast and tea and coffee, bread, pickup from station and clear directions to maximize your travellers time in the city ( As I am quite a traveller myself). Also wireless internet, toilet paper, soap and clean towels and access to a washing machine and kitchen which needs to be used carefully.

I also believe food is a great way to connect people and I love to source ingredients from markets and cook for my guests and it would be great if we could sit down over a meal and do the same and be able to do that. I am also able to converse in a variety of topics which include culture, music, politics and travel and would love to use a meal to get to know you as well. So all the prices MAY (depending on schedule) a personal cooking together and experience as we get to know each other if schedule suits.

I ONLY host people who I feel are in the same headspace and GENERALLY (but not always) no large families and people who BARGAIN BASEMENT my prices as they already very competitive.

We enjoy travel, our family and friends, the beach, music and home improving often using recycled materials. We hope you enjoy Best of Both Worlds 4 bedroom in the large top home, the Garden Retreat 3 bedroom or the quaint 2 bedroom cottage on the reserve/creek.  People always feel peace, safety and relaxation when they stay at this property of 'country' near the conveniences of northern beaches 'city'.

Since I've had such great experiences with AirBnB, I thought it was only natural that I list my properties for visitors to Sydney. 

The inner eastern suburbs of Sydney  are swimming in good caffeine and food for that matter - any number of cuisines are available nearby as the area is scattered with amazing restaurants and cafes.  

The inner eastern suburbs is extremely central to what Sydney has to offer and has a great village feel to it.  I love living here and can't imagine living anywhere else and I hope for you to have the same experiences during your stay.

Very tidy and organised person. Loves to travel and experience new cultures and hear on different international views/perspectives on things.

My acceptance rate is not 100% because I am absolutely honest to everyone who enquire and book with me. If my place is not convenient or close to their place of business, trip or activity, then I tell people to find a suitable alternative that will save them time, money and effort because Sydney is so spread out.  My foremost concern is the convenience of my guests over my business interest. 

I also like recommending places of interest and share with my guest all the tricks and tips to survive an expensive city like Sydney. 

I've heard so many times of international tourists being put off by how expensive everything is in Sydney. I would like everyone to come back to Sydney or Australia at some point in the future, so by providing an affordable accommodation people can re-experience what a beautiful country Australia is and not everybody will try to fleece all international tourists.

I have recently finished a manuscript about two years I spent in Hong Kong in the late sixties.  It's with a literary agent and I am keeping my fingers crossed for publication.  Now I am writing another memoir about time in Africa.   When I am not writing, I am creating artwork with fabrics; quilts and wall hangings.

Have travelled extensively and love travelling and travellers.  In the last few years I have visited Afghanistan as a volunteer, worked as a woofer with my daughter on an organic farm in Nepal, backpacked on my own in Morocco and visited many other destinations.
Lucky to be a Bondi Beach resident and looking forward to meet you in the future!

We are a retired couple, long time residents in the family orientated southern suburb of Engadine, being part of the Sutherland Shire. Grown family, we are now able to provide guests with restful and relaxing accommodation. Willing to provide as requested by our guests, information, about our Sutherland Shires,  many interesting places which abide within this natural protected National Heritage of surrounding areas of the Shire National Park. One of our many interests is our own heritage garden with wonderful established mountain trees such as the Australian Cedar tree (Toona Australis) which dominates our well established garden of over 50 years.   
Comfortable private double rooms accommodate couples and singles for short and long stays, in self service facilities.  Minimum stay is strictly 2 nights... 
Privacy is respected, interaction as guest indicates.
 On site under cover parking & ample safe street parking for guests. 
Relaxing , quiet, bush land surroundings, and the Royal National Park, distant city skyline sunset views from north facing sunny veranda.
Located 1 km from Princes Highway, trains link direct travel to city in under 40 mins.
Engadine shopping centre  - 10 minute brisk walk - BUS stop at corner 5 mins to local shops or 2 mins drive. 
Parks, service clubs - eateries -  take outs, early breakfasts, dinner, cafe's plus a mix of local restaurants.
24 hour Mc'Cafe' centrally located across from train, bus, taxi  station.

Easy going professional who sometimes works from home and loves to travel. I have lived in London and New York and enjoy meeting new people. I love this city and happy to provide you with some tips to get the most out of your stay.

I am a single woman, who works part time.  I have lived and travelled extensively - San Francisco, Tokyo, Saigon and outside of London when I was a child.  Love to travel and meet new people, particularly those from other places.  Have travelled in Asia, and a bit in Europe. Love Italy and la dolce vita.  Have seen quite a bit of the US (my dad took me to New York for my 14th birthday!!) and been on safari in Africa but not made it to other continents yet.  
Can't imagine life without friends, good spicy food and the prospect of another travel adventure.  Have backpacked, and travelled in style, kayaked down rivers and even hiked the Kokoda Track sharing a backpack with my boyfriend of the time.  I continue to travel now with perhaps the focus being on catching up with beloved friends all over the world from the days of living and working overseas.
Now prefer softer options along with a good bottle of wine, delicious food of the region wherever, classical music or some great rock.
Age is a state of mind rather than the years lived, and it is good to be able to look backwards and forwards.
I love meeting people through airbnb - different chats over a glass of wine and if the opportunity arises showing them the lesser known beauty of Sydney.
Beachside Breaks services Sydney's beautiful coastal and city areas

I live with my husband Marc in our Bondi garden apartment. We absolutely love living in the eastern suburbs of Sydney and spend our time going to the beach, cooking at home, exercising in Centennial Park, having BBQs, eating out and catching up with friends and family. There is so much to see and do in Sydney and the weather is generally always pretty good so you can enjoy the outdoors. Our apartment has a lovely feel to it and is in a nice central location yet still very quiet and private so you get the best of both worlds. If you're thinking about coming to Sydney, do it. AirBnB is the perfect way to experience this beautiful city. We love travelling and meeting new people and look forward to hosting you in our home.

I love art, nature and politics.
I try and live as GREEN as possible, both at home and out.
I enjoy story telling-both listening and telling.
I enjoy other people and also like my own company.
I live without a microwave because I love cooking simply and sharing slowly with people over great conversations.
Love the cinema and watching DVD's.
I have lived and travelled overseas and at the moment am choosing to explore my own continent more than OS.

I am a Sydney-sider born and bred and totally love this city. It really is one of the most beautiful places in the world. I love meeting people, including people from different cultures and places, which I get to do with my work (most frequently in Timor-Leste) and enjoy this element to Air B and B. 

Although I love to live, work and play in different places, I still and currently call Australia home. Living right on the coast and seeing the sunshine and moonlight on the water everyday is amazing. Totally topped by seeing whales passing by too (at certain times of year) - come and stay at my place and you will want to move to Coogee, Sydney, Australia as well :) I love Summer and swimming in the ocean at all points of the day (and occasional dips during Summer eves too) and also yoga overlooking gorgeous Coogee beach. Also, have just gotten into cycling- as have many Sydney-siders and it is great riding to Surry Hills (where I work and one of the best places for great cafes, shops, theatres and galleries) and do so via Centennial Park, a truly beautiful park. 

I love festivals, particularly world music festivals and film festivals. Sydney has heaps of festivals, so come and enjoy :) food festivals, short (Italian, Human Rights, Gay/ Lesbian/ Transgender, Docos, Bike) film festivals, music festivals, etc etc. It's hard to choose, even when you live here....and when it is equally fun just hanging out at the beach. 

Contact me for dates as I'm not great at keeping my calendar up-to-date and also sometimes I can be flexible with dates, so I like to hear from peeps directly.

My husband and I are both teachers. We have grown up children and 3 grand children. We love to travel. We have been hosting travelers and students for many years and love to share our home. We have developed many wonderful ongoing friendships in the past with our guests.
We live in a lovely newly renovated family home in Newtown, Sydney. We have 3 children aged 4 - 7.
Originally from Queensland. I Enjoy being on the water paddling and look forward to meeting you soon!

We enjoy meeting new people and being outdoors in and around the ocean.
Our motto is  " take a bit longer  to find the positives in everything that happens in life"

Mitch,Riley and I live in the house above the sandstone apartment. Gemma sometimes stay with us on her university holidays.

I spent 2014/15 taking a much needed break and spent the time exploring hidden gems in Europe.  I was based  at a friend's place in Surrey in England.  I enjoy meeting people of all ages and exploring different places and cultures.  I have two sons who thought I was a little crazy traveling on my own but the people I met and the places I have stayed were fantastic so far.
I am looking forward to hosting so I can repay some of the kindnesses shown to me.
I'm new to Airbnb and so far I'm loving the experience as I've met some gorgeous people. I'm an out going friendly person who enjoys travel, great wine & food and meeting new people.

I am a French Canadian woman who came to Australia long time ago just to visit and I never left. I love traveling more than anything and love meeting new people. I fell in love with Sydney and it's people because it is a new country, it is free and the climate is semi-tropical. What's not to like?

Hi! I I am Kristin. I  Love outdoor activities like going to the beach, surfing and cycling.  Hope to see you soon.  The location of our house makes all this possible and easily accessible.  If you enjoy these activities then you'll love this spot!

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I have been working in Advertising for 15 odd years working for many of the top shops around town from M&C Saatchi and Saatchi & Saatchi to DDB and BBDO.

I love living near the beach.  There is nothing better than getting up and going for an early morning swim before work.  I have lived in Bondi for over 10 years and for some reason never learned to surf.  Stupid really as it's so accessible for me.  I have had a few lessons over the years but never followed it through. Anyway I just enjoy everything else the beach has to offer.

If you can't live near the beach full time, my home is a great place to experience it for for a week or so.

I am a self employed Massage Therapist, I love my work, and the flexible lifestyle it allows me. 

I live between between Bondi Junction and Narrandera NSW, my home town.

My favorite thing is my KelpieX, Jimmy!!

Hello - I'm a gallery director from Sydney Australia. I love art and travelling and meeting new people. I have been both a host and a guest with airbnb and have really enjoyed the experience. 



 (Hidden by Airbnb) Likes:
CarriageWorks Arts Centre, ICP - International Center of Photography, Radiolab, 505, MOP Projects, Stills Gallery, Art Month Sydney, Animal Kingdom, Samson & Delilah, Kiki Smith, This American Life, The Moon, QIRKZ, American Suburb X
Treat others the way you'd like to be treated...

Bonjour! I'm a  french leaving in Australia since 11 years, in fact I was falling in love with this beautiful contry 20 years ago and decided to move 11 years ago to set up my own business. Tourism !
 I like to travel for my work or pleasure but love to saty also relaxe in my cosy place where I leave.
 It is simple place but with I think a great vibe and energie. You can feel the sun, when the sun is shining, the rain, or the (Website hidden by Airbnb) night always canddle.
I like to read nearby fireplace, listen music doing mediatation or practising  Yoga Kundalini on the cliff.

Always nice to share and meet people even for short time. sharing nice moment of life around a nice glass of wine, telling you best place to go in australia or Sydney or over the (Website hidden by Airbnb) will be just a simple pleasure to meet with you.

The Merton Hotel is a true local accommodation in the inner west of Sydney. 

We promote a relaxed atmosphere where people can catch up with friends – a true meeting place. Enjoy a cold beer or glass of wine from the front bar with a view of the Harbour Bridge.

We are looking forward to welcome you to Sydney in the near future and are more than happy to share our local knowledge!
I am a fun loving person who loves to travel and meet new people, share my travel experiences with them &  listen to their stories .

My family and I live in Potts Point. We love it and think it is the best neighbourhood in Sydney. It is full of life - cafes, restaurants, bars, markets, shops and parks. If Potts Point does not have it, it is nearby by foot, taxi or public transport. It is rated as the most liveable part of Sydney.

We like to travel. I have been fortunate enough to live in Singapore (Tanglin School), France (Dijon - Universite di Bourgogne), Holland (Delft), Italy (Perugia - Universita per Stranieri), UK (London), PNG (Moresby) and Germany (Hamburg). Our experience in travelling and living abroad has been distilled into our apartments.

Airbnb gives us the opportunity to offer to you the five homes we own (not just manage) in this neighbourhood for your stay in Sydney.

All our homes are well designed, comfortable, clean, secure and fully equipped with everything you will need to enjoy your holiday or business trip. We live a minute away so we are available should you need something.

HELPFUL TIP: If you are new to Airbnb, and have not yet completed your profile, it is highly recommended by both Airbnb and myself, that you do. If this is not completed prior to contacting me, then please take the time to introduce yourself in your first contact message when sending in an inquiry or booking request. We would like to know who is coming to our homes. 

The homes we have on Airbnb can be found below.
Hi everyone, I am looking forward to meet and welcome you to my apartment and city!
Enjoy spectacular views of the Opera House Harbour bridge and CBD from this stunning renovated apartment in a exclusive building in the heart of Sydney`s most diverse cafe and restaurant precinct.
Originally from the Mornington Peninsula, but have called Sydney home for almost 12 years now. Cyclist, biophile, lousy cook.
Welcome to Sydney! looking forward to hearing from you, Sonke.

I am a well seasoned traveller and lover of life with an insatiable curiosity and thirst to discover the world. 
I love interesting people, places of natural beauty, design, architecture and art and would be happy to share my home with like minded people who appreciate nice things and who will treat my home with respect.
----
Je m’appelle Edwina et je suis Franco-Australienne. 
J’adore les voyages, le design et l’architecture. 
J’ai pris soin de créer un environnement invitant, relaxant et un peu stylé pour mes invités et je serais ravie d’accueillir chez moi une personne ou un couple qui aimerait ma maison autant que moi et la traitera avec respect. 
Merci et bonne journée.

HI I"m Betty
I'm 67yrs young .Worked as fashion acesessory consultant,now retired and  1/2 day as a receptionist for my childrens Real Estate business.
I'm a very easy going relaxed person who enjoys the company of other interesting people.
I have been doing homestay for international students for the past 14 years which I have thoroughly enjoyed.
I love to read and belong to a bookclub, enjoy good movies, I play social bridge and in my spare time I love having my grandchildren around me.
I like to travel but I also like to hear about other peoples travel experiences.
And now I like to enjoy and share my home with other people who would enjoy my beautiful city by the sea.

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: American who has been living in Sydney Australia the last 10 years, love the ocean, beach, outdoors and a laid back lifestyle

fields.location: Sydney Olympic Park, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I am married, well educated, warm, sincere, honest and fun loving. I was born in Cambodia (Chinese/Cambodian/Thai origin) and have been in Sydney for 35 years. I worked for the Dept of Education and currently I also run a Training Consultancy. My wife and I love traveling and we have been to many countries. We have two grown up children who have moved out and are successful in what they do.
We love home decoration, cooking and hanging out with nice friends of ours. We love big cities and at the same time we enjoy the tranquility of our suburb which is located at the centre of Sydney metropolitan areas. As I was an executive for a very large NGO and was and have been a government employee, I am very resourceful about Sydney, its people and culture. I love to get connected with people of all ages and nationalities to enjoy each other's company and to learn from each other.

I look forward to welcoming you to Sydney!

With kind regards,

Andrew

I guess my life motto would be to help others and give back to society.  I am a people person and love meeting new people from other parts of the world.  I have volunteered for various charity events and do visit an elderly lady once a week .  Travelling has been my passion since I turned 17 and I worked as a travel consultant for many years in England and also when I arrived in Australia.  I like to stay in apartments and live like the locals travelling on trains and buses to get around.  I have travelled extensively in Asia and stayed in guest houses which has been a wonderful experience.

Hi! I'm Lucy. 

I’m all about coffee, health &  fitness, good food & wine, exploring cities, discovering great restaurants, nightlife and enjoying live music.

I’ve travelled to over 30 countries, so I respect people and places and know how great it can be to experience a slice of home while being away. 

Sydney is a beautiful city and I’m so lucky to live here!
Hi everyone, I am looking forward to welcome you to Sydney, Coogee in the near future !

A Visual artist from Sydney, Australia, living in Berlin for three years.
 Into good food despite being Coeliac and Pescatarian, enjoy live music, art, yoga, of course experiencing new places and generally joyous and mindful living (:

Hi, We have a character filled studio that we love hosting to travellers and guests. We used to have 3 properties on Airbnb so you'll see reviews for other places no longer run as holiday rentals. We cut back because our family expanded so we are now focusing on our children for a few years and might put our homes to holiday rental again one day.

We both work in the design fields, my husband on shows like The Voice and Master Chef and I have worked in design marketing for over twenty years.

We are the owners and managers of our properties. We are not subletting a rental so you won't be evicted should landlords discover you! We do not live in them, so you can be sure of the highest standard and quality as we are dedicated solely to you. We have been doing this for over seven years (long before Airbnb), so we are familiar with the process and have ironed out all the bumps that a newby might not have.

We absolutely love making a space beautiful and want our guests to enjoy our spaces as much as we do.

You are welcome to come and stay and enjoy our little city studio :-)

72 years old.  Married to the lovely Heather with four adult (three unmarried) children.  I'm now retired but was a fairly senior State public servant with experience across a range of departments and agencies.  Have masters degrees in psychology & town planning.  Interests include all sports (especially rugby), squash, gardening, bushwalking, reading, cooking, wine, movies and, of course, travelling.
Heather was an executive secretary and strata manager in her working life. She was also an excellent tennis and squash player.  She loves decorating, gardening, reading and travelling.   
We have enjoyed travelling in Canada and the US in particular, but have also visited Africa, Japan, Nepal, Italy, France, Denmark, England, Scotland, Wales, Ireland, The Netherlands and most parts of Australia. Our next OS trip is to Ireland, England, The Netherlands and Portugal.

Inner city Sydney guy, loves to travel, but has mostly only explored Europe and the US so far! Favourite destinations are Berlin, New York, Chicago, and Barcelona. Looking forward to exploring more, and hosting visitors from all around the globe!

Hi. I'm Anna. 
I'm a Sydney-based doctor who loves to travel.
I also host in Sydney with my boyfriend, and we love having interesting visitors here enjoying our neighborhood. As hosts, we have plenty of recommendations for you, but will otherwise be pretty hands-off. We're at the work most days, and enjoy cooking dinner at home. Looking forward to speaking to you, Anna.
A young minded fun loving lady.  I enjoy meeting our B and B guests plus travelling, movies, eating out and watching sport.  As a Mum and Grandma, I also enjoy activities with my family.

Hi, I’m Kathy
I am a retired high school teacher, and now spend time travelling with my husband, spending time with the family, reading and going to movies. I am privileged that I have been able to have over 70 families or groups of guests from all over the world over the last 4 years who without exception have thoroughly enjoyed their stay in Glebe.

I am a radio documentary/feature maker with the national public broadcaster, ABC Radio National.  It is a wonderful job in which I get to meet all sorts of fascinating people.  I focus on environmental issues, and music in my programs but have covered all sorts of things, from the secret history of lacemakers from France, who came to Sydney to a story of the Amerindians in Guyana. I've also edited a book called In their branches, with short stories about the trees people have loved.
 
My husband Nick is a professional guitarist - both performer and teacher, specialising in Atlantic soul, alt country and has done a lot of tv and session work with singer songwriters.
A few years ago we had a fantastic time touring Europe for a few months with our son and using Airbnb with delight.   
We live in Sydney in the 'inner west' in an old, restored terrace house, and love sailing our 12 foot boat on the harbour, time in the wonderful National Parks that surround the city, and camping on the coast and in the bush. 
We're keen travellers - Europe, America, Asia, and like to use Airbnb and share our own home and beautiful suburb in the same way.

I'm an educational designer working at the University of Sydney, married to Josef, a teacher. We have 2 kids and are yoga enthusiasts.
We love traveling, eating and meeting new people.

My aim is for you to feel at home. Being a linguist, I like to discuss any subject. I also like travelling, trekking, swimming, dancing... I teach or have taught English, French, Italian, Spanish and German, so if you are from those background, we have a language in common. I also like cooking, particularly Asian food, but I also prepare French and Breton dishes.
My house is simple and has always had a good feel about it. The lovely little lorikeets that visit everyday are one of its blessings. One the best features of the garden is the hammock on the top tier, from which there is a beautiful view over the harbour.

With background in travel and hospitality industry, we have travelled extensively for business and pleasure in Australia and internationally. As part of our experience we place high value on high quality accommodation in peaceful and quiet neighborhood. We are delighted to be able to offer that to fellow travellers.

We enjoy exchanging travelling tips, favourite tourist attractions,local favourite eating places, and to avoid tourist traps. 

Being independent travellers, we have driven on many scenic routes in Europe, North America, Asia, Australia and New Zealand. Amongst the 400+ cities in 36 countries on my travel map, we love Berlin, Praha, New York, Washington DC, Carmel by the Sea, Sedona, London, Edinburgh. Paris, Barcelona, Amsterdam, Munich, Salzburg, Athens, Florence, Kyoto, Tokyo, Beijing, Hanoi, Penang, Bandar Sri Begawan, Bali, Jogjakarta, Sydney, Melbourne, Adelaide, Hobart and much more. However, New Zealand is our favourite holiday destination. 

As proud Sydney siders, we love showing Sydney to travellers from all walks of life and make sure that everyone experiences the best of Sydney and Australia. In addition to opening our home to travellers, we offer personalised tailor made travel arrangement for international travellers to make the most of their time in Australia. 

We look forward to meeting you, show you Sydney & Australia, and hear all about your home town and your travel experiences.

Cheers

Travel is a passion for me and I try to escape maybe twice a year. The rest of the time I work as an art director. I have been renting The Pacific for a couple of years now and have met an interesting selection of people from around the world. Sometimes I live at the Pacific so you will find a library of books as I tend to devour them apart from the collection of artworks. I will be happy to meet you if you decide to stay in Balmain.

Active and energetic Swedish born Australian. Well travelled all over the world.
Run my own business as a hands on small business consultant.
Interests:
- Skiing
- Tennis
- Flying
- Glidng
- Sailing

Friendly and fun-loving; I'm a retired businesswoman, mother of six children and five gorgeous grandchildren.  Together with my partner I love to travel the world far and wide although there are still many countries we have yet to experience.  We occasionally host international homestay students, having had visitors from the USA, Turkey, Japan, Korea, Thailand, China, Colombia, Peru, Argentina and Germany and would love to host Airbnb members visiting Sydney.

“One's life has value so long as one attributes value to the life of others, by means of love, friendship, indignation and compassion”  Simone de Beauvoir  ( (Phone number hidden by Airbnb) )

Very easy going, accommodating and helpful and very happy to share  advice about the local area including best places to eat and drink.

Live with my partner Nick and our three year old. I work in Indigenous education. Enjoy swimming, camping, picnicking and reading. My mum and sister live very close by because we love our neighborhood so much. Can't imagine living anywhere else.   

I have stayed in Air B n B residences in lots of locations in Australia and overseas including in New York and London which has been so much nicer than staying in a hotel. 

Our house is so perfectly situated for anyone who loves the city and wants to be able to get out and about and walk everywhere but still want a bit of peace and quiet. We love living where we do and get a lot of enjoyment out of Sydney and like the thought of other people getting to experience that and enjoy our house when we are away. 

We have cots, high chairs etc for people with kids so there is less for you to bring.

We are also happy for people to bring a small dog if they would like as we have a dog door and courtyard and lots of dog friendly parks nearby.

Sydney Australia, Travel n learn, take photos and learn about differing cultures. Produce short fims/ art
self employed.

That's the only photograph I could find. Looks a bit corporate, doesn't it. I'll have to find one of the family or one of me doing something whacky.
We live in the house next door to the building where the apartment is.
Over the years, we've had various people living with us at our rambling property. And now, thanks to Airbnb, we are sharing the place with the world. There are three buildings: the house, the studio/apartment building, the garage where one long term visitor is still living (11 years and counting). There are often interesting people hanging around our place and we'd be keen for you to be part of all that if it suits you.
I work in the city - office job. My wife is far more interesting. She's an artist and does some stuff in the downstairs studio as well as teaching art and design at a university. (I might have to make up some stuff about myself.)

fields.location: Pennant Hills, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I am a travel lover and I enjoy meeting people from other countries and cultures. I teach ESL (English as a Second Language) at a local community college. I also make videos and have published the book Producing Videos. Phil is a retired research scientist and an active inventor.

Hi,
I'm a prop stylist from Sydney. I live with my husband Michael who is a musician and school teacher. We have a wonderul art deco apartment in the sweetest suburb on the inner west side of Sydney by the name of Summer Hill. We are renting our home for two months while house sitting nearby.  
 We like to host friends for dinner parties that don't go too late. We are respectful of our neighbours and their working hours and expect the same from our guests. We love all forms of visual art and we absolutely love music. When we travel, we like to travel light so we can spend most of our time exploring other places. We loved visiting the south of France and I fell in love with Berlin.  If you like being close to the city and not being woken up in the middle of the night then this is the place for you.

I am a registered nurse and travel a fair bit . I am able to short lease my apartment to neat , like minded (Website hidden by Airbnb) life motto is carpe diem. I cannot live without my iPad ,iPod, iphone,my family and my friends. You can tell I am an apple freak!
My style of traveling is mostly based on comfort...the more comfortable, the better.  Looking forward to hosting you, my airbnb afficionados...

As Bondi locals, we love our beachside community. The beautiful coastal walks, swimming laps in the Ice Bergs pool or behind the shore break.  With so many great restaurants on our door step, we make sure we eat out at least once a week.  Each day starts with a world class coffee in our local cafe.   Living one block away from the studios we are close at hand for our Airbnb guests to answer any questions or provide local advice.

I'm originally from the UK and although I've been here almost twenty years I still LOVE going back to London and traveling in Europe. I'm a bit partial to Spain, Italy, Greece and Scotland, but give me a beautiful house and garden anywhere with my family and I'll love it.

We're a family of 3. Myself, Kent and Liam our six year old son. Fortunately he's a fab traveler (Liam that is) and we take advantage of that and take ourselves off on overseas trips and we've recently become avid campers too. When we're not doing that I'm a mum and a designer and painter. Kent's very clever and does stuff I don't understand with Internet protocol and tv.

We love our house and I especially like spring and autumn and having all our doors and windows open, that inside outside living thing (obviously we do that all summer too). I think our house is great for hanging out in and we really enjoy having many guests and visitors. If we're at home, social occasions are relaxed and friendly, preferably with kids running in and out. If you're staying at our house we hope you like the feel of it as much as we do.

Hi we are Vic and Lori and live in the main house on this wonderful  property on Shipwright Bay, we are happy to host your stay. 

We have listed this apartment because we thought it is such a great place that many people would surely love to stay here. 

We are business people and enjoy the work we do and our lifestyle on the water

Vic has a mobile billboard business and has great stories about the jobs he does. 

Lori is an interpreter and mainly works for the hospitals to help with patients that speak Italian.

We are happy people and with our Italian background we are naturally hospitable. Many times we have enjoyed good company with our friends and associates over many years and many meals and glasses of wine on the balcony overlooking the bay.

We have two children in their twenties so if you want to get out on the town and really enjoy Sydney then between us all we can point you in the right direction. If it is good food and restaurants you want then we have plenty for you to enjoy. If you are from overseas then we can provide plenty of tips on what to see and where to go.

We have a cockatoo called Charlie and he adds character to the place.

We all like to relax and have some fun but are also very interested in current affairs and travel so we are across most things. We are looking forward to meeting guests from different walks of life and helping to make their stay a memorable one.

We invite you to come and spend some time here, we know you will enjoy it immensely.

We are an Asian-Caucasian gay couple.

9 sqm bedroom in a large 2-bedroom apartment with balcony and a courtyard garden, you will have your own private bathroom.
Originally respectively from France and Colombia, we met in Sydney in 2001 and decided to stay. Now a family with three young kids, we enjoy the outdoors in Bondi as well as travelling around.

Hi, I am a friendly Creative Director having lived in Surry Hills for the last 10 years plus. Hosted many housemates, guests and travelers with many good memories shared over the years. I love traveling and meeting new people and appreciate sharing life experiences. Sydney is a fantastic place to live and it has been my 7th city that I have lived so I'm easy going of people from all walks of life. Being a professional in the Creative industry I appreciate all sorts of art and design related stuff. So do feel free to use my library.

I am respectful of your privacy. I look forward to welcome you to Sydney in the near future!

Hello.  I'm a graphic designer living in Sydney. Grew up in Melbourne. Lived in Hong Kong, London and San Francisco for a few years, before settling back in Sydney.  Love my flat and Surry Hills, and genuinely love people enjoying my place :-)

Me and my husband Andrew love to travel and we go away a lot. We started by using Airbnb to rent our place out when we were away, and became really passionate about hosting and sharing our home. 
I love to learn about people's stories and journeys whilst sharing my neighbourhood and its wonders.
I aim to give guests the experience I like having when I am travelling, the opportunity to live like a local in a unique, clean, convenient and homely place.
We care a lot about sustainability and the environment. We love travelling, getting to know new cultures and people, we love hiking, surfing, yoga, skiing, snorkelling, the movies, a good book and good food and wines.
I try to make each day count. 
I choose to be happy. 
I believe we must be the change we want to see in the world.
I believe no one is better than anyone and therefore we must take care of one another.
Hi everyone, I am looking forward to meet you either here in Coogee, or at some other beautiful destination in the world!

I'm a 50-something man, originally from Bermuda, but have lived in Sydney for more than 20 years and feel very Australian now.  I've travelled widely, and lived in Canada, England and France.  My job is teaching English as a second language.  I'm also a semi-professional singer and have been a backing singer for Andrea Bocelli, Delta Goodrem and the Rolling Stones and perform regularly in the Sydney Opera House.  In my free time, I enjoy going to the theatre and cinema, swimming, bush-walking, and going to museums or galleries. I love travel and meeting new people, and have friends all over the world, who I try and see as often as I can.  I'm an experienced host, and always willing to help guests with recommendations and advice about transport and things to do in Sydney.

I (Paul) am  Senior Lecturer at the largest counselling and psychotherapy college in Australia, and this work is fascinating both in terms of the wonderful students, and also the amazing staff with whom I work.  I spent 10 years being a social researcher on sexual behaviour, gender and sexuality, having come to academia late after running a small manufacturing business, being a tram driver in Melbourne (a job a STILL have great dreams about!) and a wasted year in a clothing factory after high school. 

Raymond works as an analyst in government and corporate media, a field he has been involved in since graduation. After his honours year, he spent the best part of the next year backpacking around the world. Every continent covered.... except Antarctica. So that's on our mutual Wishlist!

Meeting guests - especially those visiting Australia - is like having a little holiday without leaving Sydney as we get to hear what their home countries are like. We manage to meet over 80% of our guests to welcome them to town! And this is the best part of being hosts with Airbnb. Hi. My name is Kellie. 

My family (myself, my husband and 3 kids) have been welcoming guests at our Studio since August 2010, but we only started using “airbnb” in July 2012. To see the feedback guests give us about their time with us in The Darling Studio, please see below. We have never had any negative feedback and the feedback is not “cherry-picked” (i.e., we only show you the best of our feedback – we show it all). 

The Studio is a separate residence, sitting at the back of the main house, separated by a courtyard.  Our approach to hosting is to give our guests privacy, however, if you need us or need help, we do our utmost to help ... Whether you want recommendations for the best local pastry shops (Black Star in Newtown), advice about lovely walks around Sydney harbour or local beaches (that us locals use – not just the typical ‘tourist’ haunts) or you’d like a home-made map of the quickest-back-street-way to drive to the airport, we are there for you.  

We travelled through Europe staying in serviced apartments and we use that experience to make our Darling Studio the most comfortable we can for our guests. We learnt what not to do, as well as what travelers appreciate (e.g., some little “goodies” like chocolates, fruit, cereal, some milk and butter or fruit on arrival to help you settle in before your first big supermarket shop); helpful (but not intrusive) hosts, honesty in advertising and so on. 

We have had guests stay as long as 11 months, and others return 3-5 times, so we think that suggests we are getting something right with hosting. We find it a real joy to meet people from all over the world, and help their stay in Sydney be comfortable, friendly and memorable. 

Warm regards & I look forward to hosting you at our Darling Studio sometime soon.
Kellie (with feedback from our guests below).

FEEDBACK FROM GUESTS
What a jewel: This studio is beautifully designed, practical, clean, peaceful with a lovely court yard, and in walking distance to the University of Sydney and Redfern station (one station from Central station). The hosts are most welcoming and helpful while guaranteeing privacy and individuality to the guest. The parallel street is charming, too, with student atmosphere, small coffee shops, deli and restaurants. The Darling Studio is definitely my favourite accommodation in Sydney (Stefan, German/Swiss professor, five separate visits across 2011 and 2012). 

The Darling Studio is my cozy and beautifully designed haven whenever I am in Sydney. The hosts are warm and welcoming with an eye for attention and comfort. The location is ideal - a very short walk to Redfern train station and the neighbourhood is filled with charming cafes and friendly neighbours. I highly recommend a stay (Heather, Consultant, four separate visits across 2011). 

I stayed at the Darling Studio for a week and the only way to sum up the place is to say it was a home away from home! The hosts were wonderful and assisted with all my inquiries (eg. location of hairdresser, train services, best eatery, etc). The Darling Studio was not only clean and fresh but contained EVERYTHING you could possibly need and more than is advertised (eg. DVD's, books, maps, take away pamphlets, shampoo, ear buds, basic foods - just everything). I would highly recommend it to anyone needing a place to stay in Sydney. The price you pay for what you get is great value and only a short distance (via train or taxi) away from major attractions in Sydney. Definitely will be staying there again in the future! (Claudia, Midwife, October 2011). 

I was a Japanese visiting researcher in Sydney University and stayed in this studio for eleven months. It was very convenient for commuting to University and for shopping at Broadway and Eveleigh Markets. On weekends I walked down to Cockle Bay, Circular Quay and Hyde Park and went to suburbs from nearby Redfern Railway Station. The hosts are very kind and friendly. If you want to concentrate on your work in the day and to have a quiet night, you can do it here just as I did (Professor Ueshima, 2010-2011).

My place is comfortable and homey and would suit a clean, mature traveller or student who likes to be out and exploring the beautiful coastal walks and cafes around here.
I am looking forward to welcoming you soon!

Bondi Beach is one of the world's most famous beaches, Bondi Beach is as much a lifestyle choice as a place. Bondi Beach draws the visitor, captivates them and forges memories of sun, surf and sand. So book and experience yourself!

I work in the city at a Media/Publishing Company as a Project/Event Manager and Natalie works at Fairfax. We are both very clean and homely, and that really reflects our apartment.

I love Bronte's beach lifestyle and adore my two grandchildren. I enjoy hosting friends and hopefully you'll be one of them.

English orriginally, I love my adopted home of Manly.  Who wouldn't love the beaches, ocean and (mostly) year round sunshine.
Welcome to Bondi! I am a music teacher passionate about travelling. I look forward to having you stay.

OUR WORK 
I'm an environmental journalist and trainer in new media. My wife Lisa is an artist and teaches kids art. 
  
WHY WE LIVE IN SYDNEY'S EAST 
We love the ocean. We love being able to swim or surf every day - which you can do living in Sydney near the beach. We also love the creative and cultural side of Sydney. There's plenty happening around here and in the inner city which is close too.  
  
OUR TRAVEL EXPERIENCE 
Lisa lived in Amsterdam and Europe for many years. I've travelled to Britain, Europe, America, New Zealand, South East Asia and India. We both enjoy meeting people from around the world. And we know that feeling of landing in a new city - it can be both exciting and a bit daunting. 
  
OUR EXPERIENCE HOSTING 
Over the years we've enjoyed showing visitors the best places to go in Sydney. If you stay in our apartment here in Sydney you'll find lots of great secret local info on where to go. Plus you'll find yourself in one of the best places to stay in the city - in terms of both the location and the accommodation itself. 
  
We'll also help you settle in and make the most of one of the most interesting cities in the world - Sydney.
Sydney sider, yoga teacher, runner, creative industries analyst, chartered accountant, mother & wife.
Outgoing mum with 3 kids aged 47. Love my family, going to the beach, being outdoors , sport, hiking, good food and wine and Chocolate
Hi everyone! I am a passionate traveller and always prefer to do as the locals do. So staying in someones apartement or room is always special.

We (Neil and myself) are pretty simple people. We work hard, play hard, and look to get the most out of life as we can. Recently this has meant moving from the cold mountains of the Great White North (i.e. Canada) to the sunny beaches of Sydney's Eastern Suburbs. 

Taking advantage of Sydney's great weather and multicultural vibe, we've been busy with sailing lessons, golf, spanish lessons, camping, salsa dancing classes, and meeting a tonne of cool new people from around the world who have also flocked to this great city. We love to cook (having recently signed up for fresh food delivery each week we've been busy in the kitchen), enjoy catching up with mates down at the local watering holes, and can't get enough of exploring Sydney and its surroundings.

We love Bondi and the life it provides, and we know you will too. So come check it out!

My wife Jo and I have 2 kids; Sophia who is 12 YO and Aidan, who is 9. We are from Sydney, and will be travelling with my wifes mother Lyn, who is 70 this year. This trip is a special birthday treat for her, and will be meeting up with her other daughter Sonia and her daughter, who are coming over from the US. This is part of a 6 week trip, where we will be spending time in England, Italy and Germany.
I like outdoor activities, in particular, surfing and skateboarding. I used to snow board but now I'm getting a little old :) In fact there's a skatable deck at my house. I like movies.

Otherwise I'm pretty happy on the couch watching a movie.

We are a young professional couple living an active life in Bondi, busy with work, loving good food and wine, staying healthy with running, swimming and yoga, and spending any other free time we have in our special home.  We love it here and know you will too.

I've been living in and loving Sydney for over 10 years. Originally from NZ I made the move and never looked back. It's such a great city to visit, live and to work in. I met my wonderful husband here and we now have a true blue Aussie daughter together.

We spend our holidays visiting the Grandparents either in the UK or NZ and we like the idea of offering our Sydney home as a great base for someone's stay for their own holidays. We especially want someone to look after our very affectionate cat Chelsea.

We hope you enjoy our home and all the city of Sydney and Australia has to offer.

I am a direct, outgoing and friendly person. I have an enthusiasm for people and travel. I like to drink lovely wine, eat great food and try new foodie things. I am happy spending time with my friends and can be found at my local cafe drinking good coffee catching up with people. My friends and family visit regularly from New Zealand and  can testify that I am a great shopper and tour guide when and as required. I have a career in media and currently work as a sales manager at Macquarie Media, I love most types of music, old and classic movies and books that I can get lost in. Some of my best life experiences have been in Africa and Europe. For me, I believe that being authentic and having respect for oneself and others are important to help get you through life.
I am a 43 year work  as a skipper on rosmans ferrys on the harbour.

Hi!

My name is Ines and I was born in Germany but have been living in Sydney for the last 11 years. I love the beach, diving, invertebrates, creating things with my hands and most recently rock climbing... I can get excited about almost anything really, if there is passion. Same goes for people, I love hearing stories about how people got to where they are and what makes them tick. Working in film kind of fits into that picture.

Francesco, my partner, is Italian and has been calling Sydney his home for a few years as well. 

Together we'll try to show you our beautiful neighbourhood with local insides of our favourite spots if you're here to explore. That's usually how we both like to discover a new place and feel right at home.

Most of the time we try to share a dinner with our guests if time allows as we've really learned to appreciate to give people some time of our day to get to know them beyond a hello and farewell.

We're both very low key, chilled out, zen some might call it but we do enjoy life to its fullest. 

Come and share the house of happiness with us.

I'm an easy going guy who enjoys travel and meeting new and interesting people. Also love spending time in the ocean, cinema and time out with friends.

I love Sydney. This property is normally my home but I'm downsizing for a couple of years while in a career change, so I'm very happy to offer it to you to be your home while you're in Sydney. I'm also happy to share all that I know about this town with my guests to help their stay be more enjoyable.

We have lived in our beautiful home for nearly 20 years which we  have renovated twice! Bronte is a gorgeous beach in the eastern suburbs which is connected by a stunning coastal walk to either Bondi and Tamarama Beach in one direction or Clovelly and Coogee Beach in the other. We are a casual two minute stroll to the beach which has some great cafes and restaurants as well as a fantastic park land and playground. The sydney CBD is only 15 minutes away and Westfield at Bondi Junction is only 5 minutes away.

We love Sydney and the natural beauty of Australia and for us, there's just nowhere like Manly- gorgeous ocean and harbourside beaches a few minutes walk apart, the best commute in the world (as one of our guests put it) via the iconic Manly ferry, fantastic restaurants and shops, and a tranquil national park with the best views in Sydney just up the road from our home. Everything you could possibly need is right here, yet it's kept its laid back beachy village feel. 

But we still love to travel! We're really fortunate that Mike's work as a Lonely Planet travel photographer has taken us on so many wonderful adventures. Our home even showcases things from some of our favourite places, like Nepal and Argentina or even our own backyard Australia, where our photo here was taken! 

Whenever we're on the road we use Airbnb, and as travellers ourselves we love that by sharing the place we love with our guests from around the world while we're away, our home is a little part of their happy travel memories too. :)
About me: I am a professional working full time during the week. On the weekend I spend weekends outdoors.

I have lots of lovely artworks on my walls and treasured finds from my travels on display. I have a great deal of pride and respect for people's homes and if you ever visit Bondi, i'd love for you to come and stay.

I am a mother of 2 teenage children and work part tome in health as well as running a small adventure business specialising in canoe trips out of Kangaroo Valley and walking, camping trips to Fraser Island.
I have travelled extensively and spent a lot of time in India and Indonesia.
i love getting away for weekends when i can, usually up and down the coast or walking in the mountains. i have recently got into kayaking and have done a few trips around the Whitsundays as well as in New Zealand.
At home i love to cook and entertain, play tennis occasionally, go to the movies and do yoga.

Hello! I'm Claire, a Producer from Sydney who loves mid-century furniture, collecting records, traveling and seeing live music. My husband David and I have listed our Paddington terrace which is filled with items that we've lovingly sourced, restored and collected.

Please feel free to contact us about staying at our house or, if we've requested to stay with you, for more info about us and our visit.

We are a couple who love and enjoy meeting new people and never shy away from building friendship when given a chance. When you stay with us,  we are not just opening our home to you but our hearts as well. WELCOME and EXPERIENCE Home away from home hospitality!

fields.location: Balgowlah Heights, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Administration Manager and CPA (retired)

Passionate about travel, music, books, entertaining
As a guest, I'm a considerate and warm person...like to explore places and meet good, interesting people. 
As a host, my first wish is for guests to feel comfortable, happy to be exploring and relaxed enough to just breathe out..and let the bliss of the place envelop them.

I am originally from the UK my partner Brad is an Australian.  We have travelled extensively throughout the world and Australia and love to meet people from everywhere.
We have a small dog named Ted, he loves a cuddle and is very social.
We are big exercise fans and love the gym, swimming, yoga and bush walking, so we are lucky to live with in walking distance to the beautiful beaches of Bronte, Bondi, Clovelly and Coogee.  Close to public transport ( 1 -2 mins away from bus route for airport, city and trains ) 
Interests are music, arts, football, travelling and cooking.

Hi, I'm a traveller to. My passions are editing moving pictures, skiing, surfing and sailing. Most of my holidays are spent chasing at least one of the above. Home is Sydney because it has it all. Except for the skiing.That's about 6 hours away in Winter.  If you are interested in staying in this beautiful part of Sydney then please send me an enquiry.

We are from the Netherlands and Colombia, fell in love in New York, and then decided to move to Sydney... We love it here. And we are very happy to help you love it as well whenever we are taking a break from our busy jobs and not using the apartment ourselves.

I'm a New Zealander in my mid-50's, who moved to Sydney after the earthquakes in Christchurch resulted in losing my long term job there. I am an English language teacher, and luckily I found a great job here and was able to start fresh and get my great little house. I absolutely love Sydney and can spend hours just walking around looking at the wonderful architecture and browsing through shop after shop in Newtown, which is just 10 minutes' walk from where I live.
Welcome to Paddington! I enjoy travelling, cooking and sport. I also enjoy dining out. I look forward to meeting you soon!

I work freelance in the film/TV industry as a production manager.  I enjoy movies, theatre, books, travelling to new and interesting places, walking, the outdoors generally and meeting new people from a variety of cultures.  I have a wide circle of friends, who likewise, love to travel and am stimulated by variety in life.  I have produced a short film in the last year and enjoy attending films festivals of which there are many in Sydney.

Born and bred in Sydney, Australia, I'm a single creative guy working in the Interior Design and Architecture business who loves to travel, theatre, film, swimming, reading, eating good food and hanging out in my great home town. 

Live in a fun, vibrant corner of Sydney called Newtown, which prides itself on its good food, good vibes and diverse bunch of great people. You'll love it (Website hidden by Airbnb) come visit!

Currently in between jobs in jobs at the moment, so trying to enjoy life til I find the next best thing.

I like the outdoors, and boxing, and bushwalking if I haven't injured a ligament or pulled a muscle.
Just completed the Oxfam 100km Trail Walker.  And looking for the next challenge.

I love to travel and have travelled to the US, Africa, London, Spain, Morocco and some parts of Asia, Hong Kong, China, Thailand and Singapore and Malaysia.

I love delicious food, good coffee, friendly cats and dogs, and taking photos (not that good, but it doesn't stop me).

I consider myself respectful of other people's places.

Hi, we are a family of 5 originally from New Zealand.  We moved to Sydney in 2000 and fell in love with Manly, the lovely weather and laid back lifestyle.  We have 3 children 16, 13 and 6 years.  We enjoy the beach and spend a lot of time either in the pool or at one of the many gorgeous beaches in the area.  We renovated our house 4 years ago and are very happy with the results.   We live in a lovely street close to everything you need to have an awesome holiday in Manly!

Hello All

Wow its been over 5 years since I joined Airbnb and is one of the best decisions I have ever made. I have Met some great people from around the world and friends I keep in touch with today. 

A little about me. I am  a very outgoing guy who enjoys the Sydney lifestyle. You will find me at the beach most mornings or cycling around the park. I am a huge cafe and coffee lover so be assured I can send you to the right places!!

 I love sharing this city and happy to guide you where to hang out to make the most of your visit.   I travel whenever possible and love hiking and backpacking.  Favorite places are Canada and New Zealand but I have traveled thru Europe , South America and North America on many occasions.

Having traveled a lot and stayed in many different types of accommodation I know what's good and what's not!!  So expect a very clean and safe place  to relax and enjoy your creature comforts, but somewhere that's easy to get around and to enjoy your time in Sydney. 

I secretly want to be a  tour guide so this is the closest thing to it!!

So just ask  me anything and I will do my best to help you have the a great time.

Ciao Robert

PS. I know I have been booked out a lot with Airbnb and Private bookings, so thanks for all the enquirers !! 

Please don't hesitate ask about availability.

We are a local team who love to connect our guests to the lush nature  and unique culture of Bali. This eco-luxury property consists of 5 antique and teak Joglo Suites surrounded by the lush rice fields of Ubud. Our organic farm provides supplies for meals, and eggs from the ducks will make your breakfast. Each of our unique Suites offers authentic Balinese detailing with the luxuries of quality furnishings and beddings.

fields.location: St Clair, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Married with 3 adult chn.  We enjoy meeting new people and whilst our home is a shared space we hope to provide a welcoming environment for all who visit with us.  Our guests will have their own room.   Breakfast provided and access to kitchen.

Hi! I'm Gabriel, a freelancer graphic designer and collage artist. I've been lucky enough to live in this beautiful part of the world and keen to share the experience with other like-minded people travelling or looking for short stay accommodation in Sydney.

Hi, we're a couple offering up our lovely home while we are away over Christmas. We pride ourselves on a clean and tidy home, and love living close to the beach. If you'd like to ask us questions about the place please get in touch, we'd love to hear from you.

I work full time in superannuation industry starting some of my days at 6am yoga class at Coogee before heading off to my Sydney office. I love watching sunrise over the ocean. You might get inspired to experience that too. I lam very happy  in my quiet location so close to everything I need. I hope you will like it too.
I live in beautiful Avalon with my family. Its one of the most spectacular areas in Sydney and we would be happy to answer any questions you have about the area.

Hi there - I have worked in the film industry and have an interest in most things cultural. I enjoy swimming, walking and riding my bike. I also like to cook healthy meals and have a nice glass of wine. Rose Bay is a great place to base yourself to explore this wonderful city and beautiful beaches. I am sure you will enjoy your stay and look forward to meeting you!

I live with my partner Seb in our 2 bedroom apartment in Bronte/Tamarama. The area is absolutely gorgeous, we feel so privileged to be able to walk to the beach, enjoy the calm and quiet, yet be so close to Bondi cafes and restaurants. Our family lives in France, so we usually go there once or twice a year, plus we love traveling and discovering new countries and cultures, so we are looking to sublet our home when we are away. The flat is very cosy and has everything you need for a comfortable and very special stay in Sydney.

We live in Sydney (Bondi), we have a cat, I run my own events business, Ben runs his own music business. We love socialising, going to the beach, keeping fit and travelling. Looking forward to sharing our home with a fun, friendly and tidy person!
Lived in Sydney for 30+ years. Married with a young daughter. Well travelled: Europe, Russia, China, East Asia, USA.
Welcome to my beachside apartment, a short walk via the coast path to both Clovelly and Bronte beaches.
From sydney

Easy going, well travelled professional couple offering a friendly townhouse to share near Bronte Beach. 
We spend a lot of time thinking about our next holiday destination - fave spots: Guatemala, Belize, Ecuador & The Galapagos, Peru, Cuba, The Gili Islands, Spain, Vietnam, India & many more.
Diving is always a shared reason to travel & we always aim to combine the two ... along with great food!

Welcome to Chippendale! 

Live and work in a bachelor studio in a New York style warehouse in city edge location.

I am a local surfer and have lived in the area for over 20years. I run a advertising agency and I love travel and meeting new people from around the world.

I am a foodie and would love to show you our local restaurants and attractions. I believe this is one of the best places to live in the world, from all my travels I have never seen a beach so close to the city, you are spoilt for choice. I look forward to meeting you and having you stay at our beach side home.

I love living in the Eastern Suburbs, close to everything including the ocean, where I like to spend as much time as possible (near it, not so much in it!).  I have done lots of travelling and these days prefer to tavel to diverse cultures and more nature-based destinations.

My motto for this year is to Seize the Moment, which is why I am offering my beautiful apartment for others to enjoy while I take some time for new adventures both here and overseas.

27 year old lifesaver at Bondi Beach in Sydney. 

I lived here in Kirribilli for a year and a half and absolutely loved it. It really is the perfect place to experience the quintessential Sydney life.
Couple from the Northern Beaches of Sydney, Australia. Lovers of travel and adventure.
full of life

I am an Irani girl who lives in Sydney. I have been here for 10 years and am a true adventurer! My partner Reid is from America. We love hosting on Airbnb as it is a great way to meet people from all walks of life from all corners of the globe. We love yoga, meditation, veganism, nature and art. We are open minded and welcome all types to our warm home!

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: We are a young family looking to rent out our recently renovated Bondi Beach apartment whilst we are on holidays.
Media professional.
I am a Paediatric Nurse Educator and love to get the best out of life. Travel and fun with friends and family is the way to go.

We have been living in Coogee for the last 25 years and take full advantage of all Coogee has to offer. We greet each day with a wonderful view of the ocean and take a quick walk to the beach for a longer  walk and swim each day. This is followed by a coffee at one of the many cafes Coogee has to offer. Coogee is the place where we want to spend the rest of our live. There is n oreal  comparison.
