I live in Sydney with my partner Melanie and son Elliot (8). We love living in Bondi Junction - it's so easy to get to the beach or the city and there's always something to do. We've done a fair bit of travelling, especially in Europe, and our favourite part of it is always living in someone's home so we can get a sense of what it's like to be local - that's why we're happy to list our place on Air BnB. 

As we will only be renting out our place when we are away, we won't get the chance to meet you if you stay in our home, but hopefully you'll get a sense of who we are from where we live.
Australian Chinese IT professional on business and family trips.
I enjoy living near Bronte beach with my family!  Come and see this beautiful part of the world! I'm happy to suggest great things to see and do.

We work in Sydney part week but live in Kangaroo Valley.  We have a business in Sydney where we work Monday to Thursday.  We have 3 children and 4 grandchildren.  We have hosted Willing Workers on Organic Farms participants on our organic farm so are used to overseas guests.
We have travelled to France, England and Ireland as well as New Zealand and Bali.
My name is Galina. I'm a proud mum of a 5 year old boy and I love to travel.

We are a small family of three. My husband is Welsh and I am Australian. We have lived in Australia for 5 years after 15 years in the UK. 

We love travelling and are passionate about cities and what makes them liveable. 

Our house is always full of people visiting on holidays, for BBQs, playdates, sleepovers or friends using the spare room as they establish themselves in Sydney.

On weekends we get up early and cycle or walk down to the beach and then have breakfast in one of our favourite cafes - The Butcher's Cafe  or the Belgrave Cartel (photos included in our property profile). In the summer we surf or do laps in the sea pool. The walk to Shelly Beach is also a favourite. 

We have  relocated back to Australia from the UK along with many of our friends. We know what it is like to start a life in a new place and how important it is to feel at home and part of a community when you first arrive. Particularly for children. We also like to stay in local places when we travel rather than hotels to get a real feel for the cities we visit.  This is why we are so keen to share our house with people rather than leave it empty when we travel.  

Our neighbourhood is just outside 'touristy Manly' which is how we like it. We have all the advantages of having access to the beach, facilities, ferry, restaurants and events but the peace and quiet of a local's neighbourhood''. 

We have regularly hosted families and couples in our home when we travel which has been great. Perhaps the most fun was proving accommodation for a bride'and her family from the UK with our neighbour hosting the groom's family.  We also have dabbled with home swaps which has been fun.

Hi, I'm Lorna. I'm a young 50 year old living in beautiful Sydney for the last 13 years, originally from UK. I came to Australia 22 years ago as a backpacker and travelled all over Australia. I emigrated in 1998 and I love the outdoors lifestyle Australia has to offer. I love living by the beach and going for long walks to Long reef headland or to Curl Curl beach via the cliff walk. My passion is sailing on the harbour and I go yacht racing every weekend and some evenings during the summer.
I have my own physiotherapy business in a clinic in Manly as well as providing physiotherapy to the elderly in their homes. I enjoy helping people to recover from injuries and maintain a healthy lifestyle.

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I am French and have been living in Bondi for 7 years with my husband. We have enjoyed life here so much that we have had 2 kids and are now all Australian citizens. We love the outdoor, especially swimming, surfing, golfing, playing tennis, hiking in Australian national parks... Bondi beach is for us the best place to live in the world!

I am a writer/performer who loves traveling, singing, reading, writing and hanging out with fellow creatives. I travel often to Asia to literary and performance festivals and collaborate often with Indonesian artists, musicians, and poets.
I also take groups on writing retreats to Bali, Laos, Cambodia, Burma, Morocco, Fiji.
I am interested in Eastern religions and culture, but have also spent time in USA and Canada in the 70's hitching from LA to Vancouver and across to Montreal, so I have a lot of great traveling stories.
These days I don't hitch but I love meeting fellow travellers and exploring new places. One of my favorite destinations in Luang Prabang in Laos, I lead a writers retreat there every November.
My life motto is passed down from my mother to me  - Happiness through creativity.

I work in the Business School at Sydney University and my husband and I have one son whose 14 years old.  I originate from Ireland but have lived in Australia for too long to mention the number of years.  We have travelled extensively and are always keen to see new places.  Truth be told we work to travel!

I'm 33, love food, wine, the arts, theatre and travel. Love meeting new people and get excited telling them local places to check out in Syd!

Love where i live and sharing it with people, passionate about music, life and being by the harbour or beach.

This is my first AirBNB host. So if I forget to tell you something or do something silly, please let me know. I'm just a beginner.

I'm a 29 year old professional, working in environmental engineering in Sydney, right next to Central Station. 
I love food, music and travelling. This is why i'm on here! I'm travelling overseas and want to share my house while I'm away.
My favourite place is still Mexico, but I'm not scared of finding a place I love more. I'm still a backpacker at heart but have landed in a few big hotels once in a while.

I hope you love my place as much as I do. And I'd love to hear your feedback about your stay and if you have any tips for me, that would be awesome. Thank you.
I am an independent arts professional and travel regularly. I am married and we love our home. I just completed my Masters in Creative Arts at Wollongong University.
Hi, I'm Simone and I live with my partner Ralph in Sydney/Australia. We both work in art and design, love surfing and the ocean.

I love meeting people from all over the world and hearing about everyone's interesting life. I'm dedicated to health and wellbeing and currently studying a master in  Psychotherapy. Feel free to reach out to me if you have any more questions about my listing or Sydney!
Currently living in Curl Curl on Sydney's Northern Beaches.  Feel free to send me a message if you have any questions!

I own my own company in the CBD we make music, record for ad agencies  and produce audio for Radio, Web TV  commercials, documentaries and more!

I love the city of Sydney mainly because of the mix of city life and the beaches, I travel a lot and love exploring new countries and new experiences

My apartment I own and is in immaculate condition It's always very clean and well presented.

I am into music, food, travel, honesty and good will amongst other things

I have my own production company specialising in corporate events.  I have outgoing personality, enjoy spending time with friends, cooking and entertaining. I swim, do pilates and walk to keep fit, a necessity after enjoying a glass or two of good wine with friends on the weekend. 
I enjoy gardening although living in inner Sydney limits you to how much of a garden you can really have.
Jeff and I love travelling and know how important it is to feel comfortable and spoilt with the accommodation. Having been lucky to spend many years in 5 star hotels due to my work, I enjoy ensuring others can also enjoy a touch of luxury when they come and stay in our studio.

Hello Travelers to Sydney, Holiday Makers, Business People,  We are Self Catering Property Hosts based in inner East Sydney AUSTRALIA.   We currently host guests to Sydney, and some specialty guest hosting in Nepal and Bali.   

We host true to the Airbnb concept and the Airbnb spirit because we developed Airbnb as our very first booking channel and it is still our largest.

Our objective is to communicate well, explain properties properly, and do our best to complete the occupancy for all our guests.   Sydney tourism is all about guests who come back.  That is Team Sydney.  Local advice, through to guest check out and key return, it is our job to understand every guest is unique.  Every rental apartment is also unique, and not to be compared to hotel type stays.  

Peter’s bio . . 
Paxsafe Director. Age 53.  With 20 years’ experience in accommodation services in the sharing economy.   Also working carbon emission reduction development aid in Nepal and development of international electronic travel services.  

Rupesh’s bio . .
Paxsafe Audit Officer.  Age 27.   Graduated  in B.com ( Accounting) from Australian Catholic University.  5 years’ former experience  as house man and guest housekeeping officer at Pullman Grand Quay on Sydney harbour, and Pullman on Sydney Hyde Park  Now making sure all Paxsafe bookings are completely legal, accurate and risk free.

If you ask us what the share economy is all about, jet us just say, come as a guest.  Go as a friend.  We hope.  To share is to travel.  It is the spirit of travel.  The capacity, and the wonderment. 

Best Regards
Peter Morony & Rupesh Poudel
 PAXSAFE Sydney

We started 18 years ago in fully furnished rentals to the corporate and holiday market with our own properties. 
James Parsons and I set up our own company being one of the first in corporate rentals in Sydney, when internet was dial up and a distant dream as a advertising tool.
Our agency is now based in Pyrmont and we boast between 185 to 215 properties throughout Sydney Metro spanning from Castle Hill, Parramatta, Wentworth Point, The Lower North Shore including North Sydney, Sydney CBD the Inner West /Pyrmont and the Eastern Suburbs Darlinghurst/ Surry Hills.
I hope you enjoy your stay will us, 
Safe travels

Friendly & mature Sydney Accountant, been living in Australia for 20 years I've been living with many people from different nationalities which I really enjoy! For me, family is the most important part of my life & since 2016 I have returned to Indonesia & now I'm based in Canggu, Bali. I'm really into fashion, music, surfing & movies, and in my spare time I usually spend time with my friends; go out to have meals, go to movies, & shopping.
Welcome to my lovely home! I am a friendly host. I hope you will enjoy your stay in Sydney! I'm sure you will!

From Germany, living in this house since 8 years and loving it.

As I had to stay several nights in a filthy youth hostel in KingsCross, when I arrived in Australia, I am happy to rent out.

My boyfriend is born in Ireland and grew up in Tassie. We both love travelling, a very good red wine and meeting new people. We are easy going but we love our house clean. We are both professionals working in North Sydney. Minding our friend's cat at the moment. We can give you tips re sightseeing and surf spots.

I'm from Sydney and love the beach, sunshine and living on the coast of beautiful Bondi.

I travel a lot for business. My company Fonzarelli makes electric mopeds & motorcycles.  

I am passionate about all things sustainable and believe that we must tread lightly on the earth.

We live just a little way from Manly beach and I love living here.  I try to speed walk or run the soft sand at least 3 or 4 times a week because it is so close and I am trying to lose weight. I couldn't live without my family, music a bit of wine and lots of friends.  The best part of visiting here is not knowing what lovely surprises you have right around the corner and not knowing what you will do each day.  That is just life on the beaches here.. beautiful blue sea and lovely golden sand. Come and see for yourself.

fields.location: Surry Hills, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I'm Scott, very active guy from Sydney who loves traveling and exploring different cultures. Look forward to meeting you!

Hi - I'm Louise and I've lived in Sydney for 15+ years - mostly at the lovely penthouse in Darling Point.  

I hope you enjoy your stay at the penthouse as much as I've enjoyed living here. Please let me know if I can assist with any special arrangements to make your visit more enjoyable. 

Warm regards,
Louise

We are a professional couple who enjoy entertaining and travelling.  We have lived in Sydney for over 30 years and are happy to help out with advice on how to get the best out of your stay in this magnificent city.  We are both active with walking, yoga, golfing, boating, tennis and enjoying Sydney's cultural and restaurant life.
We love to share our light and airy spacious home.  We will greet you and show you around and enjoy chatting, but respect your privacy.

fields.location: North Bondi, New South Wales, Australia

fields.about:
I am a very clean, tidy conservative but very international and artistic type.   I used to be a professional musician (pianist/vocalist/songwriter). Now I work full time as an Executive Assistant one of of Sydney's largest private schools and I love living in Sydney. It's a magical wonderland!

I appreciate the fine things in life and live simply but elegantly.  I enjoy the nurturing connection to nature which I experience here.  My home is a great space for creating and recharging.
Northern Beaches local looking forward to welcoming both local and international guests and showing off this wonderful place in Sydney :-)
I am university lecturer from Sydney Australia. I live with my partner in North Bondi. We are socially conscious and concerned about the environment.

I love traveling and exploring the world with all its amazing adventures. I live in and love sunny Sydney and find the inner city to be one of the most exciting and interesting places to live. I run my own business so am out and about most of the time - but more then happy to lend a helping hand when it comes to local information on what to see and do!
I am from Brookvale, I like to keep fit by swimming, running and riding my bicycle.

I'm single, footloose and fancy free. Very rational and  honest... which can sometimes seem a bit gauche though with good intentions.  My interests are very wide-ranging and you can probably expect an opinion from me on many topics, though I don't necessarily accept or believe everything that is written as fact.

As a youngster, I had set my sights on the Trans Siberian express; I haven't given up on this dream yet despite the aches & pains that accompany age.
At the very least, I'd like to go to Paris, Prague and Vienna before I sign off from this mortal coil.  I tend to travel cheap but prefer clean, secure and convenient digs.

Best to look me up on fbk if you want to know more about my fav  music, movies, tv etc.

The internet is fantastic, is it not?!  I am old enough to recall life before computers and all research was done rifling through books in the library... way back when music was real (not synthesized) and voices and lyrics were pure & groovy.

Life's motto:   Time Is Passing Us By ~ Joan Baez. No Time To Lose ~ Boney M. Eat, Live and Be Merry (for tomorrow we die) ~ Luke 12:19 I think there might be a message in there for some of us; maybe grow old DISGRACEFULLY. 
tempered by: There But For Fortune Go You or I (lyrics Phil Ochs, Joan Baez cover) - thoughts and action on behalf of those less fortunate and the animals that humanity needs to treat better.

I'm also on (Hidden by Airbnb) and linkedin. cheers

Welcome to my three bedroom house, shared by my adult son, our friendly dog and myself. It is situated very close to Centennial Park, Oxford St, Bondi Junction and all of the Eastern Suburbs magnificent beaches. I enjoy gardening, swimming.skiing and socialising with my friends.

Hi.  I work in communications for a bank but study interior design, which is my main passion.  I am a long time yogi and can provide advice to those wishing to practice yoga around Sydney - there are some world-class teachers here. 

I love to swim and often am down at Icebergs for a lap, or gathering with friends to do a Bondi bay swim.  Otherwise, I love film and music.

I have travelled far and wide and am ever curious about new places and people.  I hope to offer you a home that lets you explore Sydney but provides a comfortable base for you to regroup and relax

I look forward to meeting like-minded souls soon!

Born in Jamaica. Arrived in Australia (via London) as a child. I practice Krav Maga - an amazing Martial Art. I work in the Personal/Professional Development field. I am a Effective Action Coach, working with large groups. I also run courses in Communication & Pain Free Presentation skills for adults & Confidence/Self esteem programs for young people and teens. I cant live without grass fed, grass finished meat, wild caught fish, pastured eggs & fresh sprouts, ferments, Kombucha, Kefir, my family & friends, beauty, great sounds & raw chocolate. I have traveled to over 30 countries. I speak excellent English, basic French & awesome body language. I am a quiet introvert, studying psychology, who loves reading, learning & pondering the possibilities of life... With our thoughts ...we make our world... (Thank goodness)
Welcome to my studio apartment located just around the corner from The Corso and only couple of minutes from the famous Manly Beach.

Love homes, which is why my wife and I are passionate about ours.
We love it, and hope those that stay love it equally!

I have lived in Sydney for over 40 years. Inspired by past travel experiences, we would  like to offer you a home away from home. Our mission is to provide our guests with the best possible hospitality and customer service. It is really important to us that all our guests feel happy, comfortable, welcome, and at home.

Yoga Teacher and filmmaker living in a big (6 bedroom) terrace between Redfern and Surry Hills, close to Central Station.
I study Japanese and love going to Japan.
I'm mostly vegetarian and am passionate about animal rights.
I love growing my own food, travelling and singing :)

I am born and raised in Sydney, Australia. I love to travel, both within Australia and overseas, and try to get away as often as I can. I enjoy eating out at some of the great restaurants and cafes Sydney has to offer and I have listed a few of my favourites places in my guide book. 

I love living in inner-city Sydney and being close to the all the great restaurants, bars, the city and beaches. My apartments in Potts Point are close to all these and more. It is such a unique part of Sydney and an excellent base for your visit.
I have a fantastic cottage listed in Surry Hills.  Feel free to ask any questions you have about the place or staying in Surry Hills.

I love Sydney and the spot where I live.  My 32 year old son still lives with me as so many young people in big cities do these days. And who would move if you lived mso close from all  the beaches...
I offer 2 places on airbnb - the attic in Bondi and a small room in Vaucluse.
I came to Australia 37 years ago and still go home at least once a year to do a bit of exploring, which I missed out on because I left when I was only 20.
I love to relax with a good movie or book when I get home from a stressful 9-5 job in the city.  But no complaints - I work in the travel industry and "if I can't go there myself, at least I can talk about it" with other travel minded people.
Clean, tidy and cozy is my motto for creating a welcoming atmosphere and a comfortable stay.
 welcome to Bondi!!

Hi! I'm a travel writer so my work takes me all over the world writing for newspapers and magazines. I'm English originally but have lived in Sydney for 12 years.

I work from home so love the convenience of being so close to the city and having so many great cafes, restaurants and bars around me.
Welcome to Sydney! I am a young TV/ radio professional. You'll love this stunning apartment, near one of the most beautiful beaches in Sydney. I look forward to hearing from you.

WHY BOOK WITH US
1. Conveniently located, Bright, Beautiful Space and constantly being updated. We care..
2. Well serviced, Super reliable and responsible hosts, we are always there for you... hence the SuperHost status. We treat our guests how we like to be treated.
3. Value for money.. Our rates are generally based on min. one month stay, which are not much more than the cost of renting these fully furnished apartments on long term basis.  If you find cheaper rates, do compare the location, quality and service.
 
I have lived in Sydney over 27 years, I know the city extremely well, and now get to know the eastern beach areas.

I have been in travel and web development businesses over 17 years.
 
We manage great properties in Sydney city and Clovelly, with great quality, bright, spacious, with good view, very clean and well maintained. 

We welcome guests whom i would love to rate 5 star on all 3 aspects on the airbnb review form after departure - cleanliness, communication, observance of house rule..

We would also offer our best service to make your stay as comfortable as possible. 


Please note,
when you read reviews from guests, bear in mind, these guests stayed in different properties, some rented the whole place, some rented a private room.

I'm a long-time designer and writer, and have my own small biz and now shop:)
I love books, creating stuff with paper (have written a book on the subject), anything 'vintage' or 'old'...things with history, basically. I am a keen cook and gardener though slightly more successful at the former (thankfully the garden looks after itself!) I love music, talking and walking...oh god this is sounding like a lonely hearts ad! It isnt! I have a lovely beau a few kms away with whom I will stay if you are at mine! I have enjoyed quite a few airbnb experiences staying at others' places and love the idea of it all.

Welcome to Sydney! I work as a nanny, looking after babies. I love spending time with friends, having a wine, playing with my two adorable puppies Brooklyn and Iggy and meeting new people who join us for their stays!

Great fun. Professional working lady. Easy to get along with, excellent communication skills with all ages. I love a good sense of humour and like to believe I have one, good manners, common sense and good food are a must in my home. I love to cook, my specialties are a good old fashioned baked leg of lamb with all the baked vegies drowned with copious amounts of gravy AND  garlic prawns with white wine and cream sauce tossed in pasta. garlic bread and a rocket and parmesan salad.... yumm .
Loved watching the Game of Thrones and I have heaps of movies for you watch on Stan or a hard drive while relaxing at home.
My aim is to make your stay in my home  to be like you were at home.
I have been hosting for 3 years now and am very blessed to have met soo many awesome travellers.
I look forward to meeting you one day
Michelle

I am a Sydney sider,  born and bred. I have lived in the USA, Canada, and the UK  and traveled extensively and continue to do so for work and pleasure. As  a result I am pretty easy going on the road and adaptable to new places. 
I love traveling and meeting new people. When I can't be doing my own traveling I love sharing my knowledge on all things Sydney. I live in an amazing place with access to all the best things Sydney has to offer. I have been on AirBNB a while now and have always enjoyed hosting travellers!  Looking forward to meeting you!
We're enjoying life in Manly. We love having coffee, walking along the beach and looking after our guests.

My husband & I are passionate travellers ourselves & love hosting friends in our home. With our daughter now having moved out we have had many friends use our downstairs retreat whilst holidaying or working in Sydney. We have decided to use airbnb to fill it for more of the time but envisage it to be like having like minded friends staying there. We are happy to be as sociable as you like or leave you to your own devices if you prefer. I am a personal trainer & chef so I am usually cooking up goodies in the kitchen or up in the park putting people through their paces. My husband Donald is semi retired & usually found pottering in his shed or attending to the garden & pool. We are keen sailors & often out on the waters of Sydney harbour. We are also keen skiers with a passion for good food & good wine. We look forward to meeting you & sharing our home with you.

Hello and welcome! I am an experienced host, having welcomed a number of students and International travellers in the past. I have hosted travellers and Students from China, Germany, France, Italy and even New Zealand! I look forward to meeting you and sharing our love of Sydney with you soon!
I am a retired school principal and grandmother of 8 who loves gardening, reading and travelling.

My husband and I moved to Sydney in 2011 and like most visitors have been enjoying exploring what this fantastic city has to offer.
We have great tips and recommendation for visitors new to Sydney and the eastern beaches.
We are looking forward to hosting good people from all around the world.

My son Seamus and I share hosting. I mostly live on North Stradbroke Island, where my husband builds sailing canoes, keeps bees and surfs.  I mess around with organic food, making mead, yoga and fermenting.  We built Cypress House, designed by 2013 Wilkinson Award-winning architect Drew Heath, at Point Lookout, North Stradbroke Island. The house has featured in Monument magazine and other leading architecture publications.  I am from Sydney where Seamus lives and hosts our beautiful industrial-style terrace house in Redfern.  
Please come stay with Seamus in Redfern or make a visit to Straddie and Cypress House.
I am an easy going home owner, happy to share my spare room with interesting travellers. I look forward to hearing from you!

Easy going, optimistic, spontaneous, creative and adventurous person. After former corporate life that propelled me to explore what life has to offer outside of what many people see as an attractive 'career path', I have been happily living an unconventional life experiencing it to the full.

I'm quite active, I love ocean swimming, riding my motorbike, go hiking, skating or long walks to enjoy the outdoors. I go dancing from time to time (tango or salsa) and I channel a fair bit of energy through my creative outlet in photography. I love to travel, even though I haven't been to nearly as many places as i wished to, but each and every travel experience brings immense joy, learning and friendship that I value. 

I enjoy meeting people, I especially love spending time with those who are positive, easy going, adventurous, open minded and passionate in following their dreams.

Recently i have swam the English Channel (yes UK->FR) and am now working on my next challenge (and a few of them too :)

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I'm from Sydney but live and work overseas intermittently. I have a sunny, clean Bondi pad that will make you feel right at home.

I am a French Canadian lady living in Sydney permanently. I lived on 3 continents. I am a Speaker and a Coach working for myself. I had a rich life experience it made be open understanding adaptable, I am offering a room and a bright quiet homy living space by the sea in a central location in Sydney, fabulous spot! I love people and sharing. I am a conscious, worldly, optimistic, healthy and caring woman. I love laughing! I am into arts, nature, traveling, singing, chanting, dancing, music, yoga, swimming in the ocean, learning and teaching, personal development, discovering and enjoying life. I love good food, fresh & healthy! I practice to always look at the bright side of life!

I'm a professionally employed guy working in the Theatre industry at Sydney's iconic Opera House.  My career takes up alot of my time, but it's a position I've loved for the past 18 years and continue to enjoy.  My main interest outside of work would be photography, and more specifically, portraiture.  I'm quiet yet talkative, and enjoy a good conversation.  Working mostly nights means that visitors would be able to take advantage of having the apartment to themselves.  On the occasional evening that I am home, I appreciate a bit of relaxation, a good home-cooked meal and a glass of wine.  I'm very easy-going and I've been told by those who know me well, I have a very 'calming' nature.  For those who are interested in astrology, I am Taurean .... born in the Chinese year of the Horse.  I'm clean and tidy and keep the apartment in good, presentable condition in order to make any visitor's stay as pleasant as possible.  My friends describe my apartment as very 'homely'.

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: We live in Bondi Beach together. We have been at this location for over 2 years and have been enjoying every ounce of sunlight since. The beach lifestyle is what had originally attracted us here and since we arrived we have no intention of leaving it!

Fully imported from the UK, we are a Civil Engineer (Yorkshire) and an HR/OD consultant (Edinburgh!) who work in the week & who both love calling the Northern Beaches home & escaping to the tranquility of the Peninsula - weekends are spent practising Pilates, Yoga, walking, catching up with friends.  Respectful of other's needs for quiet & privacy but equally happy to engage in chat over dinner with recommendations for dining out, walking & cycling tracks & what to visit in the City & beyond.  


The Engineer is also an exceptionally  accomplished home cook & is therefore open to providing dinner, with prior arrangement & at an additional cost.    As an example, he can provide an authentic Paella which serves up to 4 guests, at $30.00 per head - you provide your own wines/drinks.  Other than this offering, please note we do not offer breakfast, lunch or dinner unless of course there is a special request in advance.

Twp small very friendly dogs live in this home - we shall ensure they do not get in your space.  They are not  however used to very young children and whilst it is unlikely they would snap, we would prefer not to invite  guests who have very young children.  In addition, our staircase is steep with quite formidable treads to the steps and again not suitable for very young children or for anyone who may have some physical restrictions.

We are comfortable with guests having the run of the house - using the Jacuzzi, the BBQ & the kitchen etc & would ask that considerate cleaning takes place after use.  Other than that, we will leave you alone to enjoy the magical beauty of the Peninsula!  One note to add is that parking on the Peninsula can be expensive & we can provide, subject to a small security deposit, a Pittwater parking permit for your car which would save you up to $20.00 a day in parking charges.

PLEASE NOTE A CAR IS ESSENTIAL FOR THIS PART OF THE LOCALITY.  THERE IS A LOCAL BUS SERVICE BUT IN ALL HONESTY THE TIMETABLE MAY NOT SUIT EVERYONE AND IN ORDER TO MAKE THE MOST OF STAYS HERE, WE HIGHLY  RECOMMEND A CAR.

We live in the beachside suburb of Manly and we love to swim, exercise, go to movies, eat out and spend most of our time outdoors.
Travel is something we love to do but most importantly we love being with our family and our lovely friends

I am a fun loving Manly local.  My husband and I have lived in Manly since 1996.  We enjoy beach and bush walks and sailing in Sydney Harbour.  As we live in Manly I am normally around if you need any assistance.
Easygoing guy from North Sydney, just over the Harbour Bridge!  If you are interested in staying in my listing then feel free to send me a message!

We are a family run Business consisting of Mark, Lynne and Paul Taylor who all share a love of boats of all shapes and sizes! We believe in great customer service, we aim to offer a unique and fun experience both our Beneteau Oceanis and at our Lake House & The Ark on the south coast! We take pride in offering this exciting way to spend a night or two or beautiful Pittwater at Palm Beach, Sydney.You can stay in everything from a tree house to a castle when you travel with Airbnb but how about staying in a place where you’ll get waterfront views - on all sides. Catch the drift? It’s a boat! Check in to Airbnb Yacht Stay @ Palm Beach Pittwater for a weekend that’ll literally rock you. This stylish French yacht is moored at the famous Palm Beach so keep an eye out for Home & Away stars. You can fish right from your front door. Your Airbnb hosts Paul and Lynne have all the gear ready for you. They’ll also set you up with a tasty platter full of delicious seafood (at an additional cost) Hungry for more? Man overboard! But don’t worry because you can jump straight off the boat for a swim. There’s even a waterproof bag for a fish and chip run. For all you landlubbers, you can also take a tinny to shore. You’ll love the novelty of sleeping on water in one of their three comfy cabins. They also have a spacious saloon, bathroom and a large cockpit that’s perfect for dining. If you really want to get moving, have a chat to your Airbnb hosts about their cruises. Paul and Lynne are full of local knowledge so they can show you the highlights of Sydney’s waterways.
More Information
Airbnb Yacht Stay @ Palm Beach Pittwater
https://www.airbnb.com.au/rooms/894300               
www.airbnb.com          
If you want to book the yachtstay at Palm Beach Pittwater or if you’d like to stay at thousands of exciting places right across the country, then Airbnb is the way to go.
Get online at www.airbnb.com!
I enjoy living on the coast.  I live and work in Sydney, love the beach lifestyle while still being able to enjoy all the benefits of living in a city.

I'm a home based travel agent and while I enjoy my job of booking travel arrangements for my customers, I also enjoy getting out and exploring the world for myself!  When I'm home in Bondi, my unit is the perfect location to experience the best of Sydney.

A little about us:
We both work in corporate roles and enjoy good food and watching and participating sports in particular. If you have questions about sporting events, dining destinations, etc, we are more than happy to help if we can. We are both fairly well travelled (globally, as well as having travelled every state in Australia) and are more than happy to either or point you in the right direction to help with your travel plans. 
If you are a foodie, a climber, hiker or adventurer, a museum goer, a fighter, a photographer, a random sightsee’er, or just in town for  business, we look forward to accommodating you.

fields.location: Byron Bay, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Friendly and outgoing professional female in 30's. I love the beach, movies, music and of course traveling :)
Check out the listing and let me know if you have any questions.

Hello,my name is Hendrika and I am a semi -retired veterinarian living in a lovely part of Sydney. I have 2 dogs,my best friends,and I love walking with them around the area.The cabin was my mothers granny flat until recently as she needed to be placed into a nursing facility so decided to use the space for those wishing to stay in area for short breaks.I have removed her old furniture and endeavoured to  make the space user friendly for guests and am happy to help in any way I can to make your stay with us most enjoyable.
Beachy chick who loves to surf! Welcome to Sydney sun and surf at Bondi beach!

I love creating spaces for people to enjoy and relax in.
I love travelling and seeing how other cultures live - but don't do enough of it.

fields.location: Balmain East, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Keen traveller, gardener, foodie and collector of vintage ephemera.

My name is Karl J and I live in Sydney.  My husband Alan and I have been at this great apartment for nearly 8 years.  I came from NYC prior to Sydney and I am very grateful for the places I have lived.

We look forward to hosting like minded travellers and offering a great value with an fantastic apartment in a superb location.

Another great feature of our apartment is our well mannered and social dog named Panda. She is the highlight for many of our guests.

I am easy going, reliable and well-travelled. I had the privilege and pleasure to live in Europe, USA, Asia and Australia. I work in the financial services industry and like outdoor activities in my spare time.

A fun loving person that enjoys socialising, shopping, fashion, music, fitness, surfing and dining out with friends.   I'm a nurse eductator working in the local Manly Hospital, a career I'm passionate about.   I enjoy travel & meeting people from all over the world.  I live every day as if its my last.

I'm a well travelled Mother of two, married to my lovely husband Ralf. I'm originally from Austria, have spent many years living in the UK, and  I now call Avalon Beach home. I love this place, the natural beauty and relaxed lifestyle. We are a family of keen sailors, and this is the perfect place for it!!

We are a retired couple who spend the southern winter in France every year. We are very house proud and keep it in excellent condition. We love our 3 months in the Languedoc as it presents us with a different culture and lifestyle. We have many friends over there and look forward to seeing them every year. 
Back home here, we enjoy tennis, golf and boating.
We enjoy our house very much, as it has lots of space; it is bright - with several skylights - and very comfortable. As well, the back garden is extensive and leads onto a state park with views of Sydney Harbour, the entrance to the harbour and the Pacific Ocean. On a clear day you can almost see New Zealand (!)
We love to have overseas guests who have never visited Sydney before. It is a delight to show them our city and harbour.

I have lived in Manly for 5 years and could not imagine any better place in the world to live. When in Manly, I love going to the beach, snorkeling and Stand Up Paddle boarding. I love to travel, especially to places with great food such as Italy, Morocco and Asia. I currently live in Singapore with my husband and 3 kids.

I am a wife and a mother of Little Tom (born 2012).
I live in a beautiful part of Sydney where I enjoy the outdoors.  I like to run with my husband and son (who sits in a jogging pram) around the beautiful natural landscapes of Little Bay. I often sit on the safe secluded Little Bay beach and build sand castles with Little Tom or have a hot chocolate at one of the local cafes.
I was once a school teacher, however I now work a couple of days a week as a pastoral care and child playgroup organizer for a church in the eastern suburbs of Sydney.
I love my husband and we love sharing life together.
Bought a stunning home in cottage point and want to be able to share this unique experience with others worthy of it.

I have been working in the design industry for over 10 years and enjoy staying active and social. I have always enjoyed taking advantage of the amazing restaurants, culture and cafe scene the immediate area has to offer. Weekends are never long enough!

Hello,

I wish to welcome you to Manly, Sydney, Australia.
I am an Australian, married to another Australian and and I live near the Apartment.
The Apartment is a Holiday Rental facility which I look after and manage  and take great pride in. 
I enjoy being the Hostess and providing a comfortable, homely, clean and welcoming 'home away from home' for you to stay in and relax. 

Travelling is a passion of mine and experiencing other destinations around the World has made me a better person.

Things that I cannot live with out include: Good Food, Live Music, Sunshine and Warmth, The Outdoors, Sporting Events and my Family.

I like being a Host as I like meeting people and hearing about their lives, stories, dreams and hopes.

When we (my Husband and Myself) travel together we like to stay in Cities and we like to walk around to capture the atmosphere of the location and to try and talk to the local people of that Town or City.

My Motto is to be Happy, Friendly, Thankful and be Kind to your Neighbour.
Welcome to a truly beautiful part of Sydney - on the harbour, close to the city and with easy access to the best beaches, what more could you want? Get in touch!
Hi I am Kelly.  I am a mother of 2, wife of one and full time employee.  I love travelling and the outdoors.  Combining the best of both makes the best breaks

I'm a friendly, honest, reliable and genuinely helpful host and strive  to make your stay as comfortable and memorable as possible. I have a lot of local knowledge so if you need some tips or information you just have to ask. I'm always happy to give my guests advise and am very open and willing to assist if you have any questions or concerns. I take great pride in my properties and keep them in pristine condition so when you set foot in the door you will be impressed and feel good about your choice of accommodation.

Hey, I'm Julia. I'm in my thirties I use Airbnb when I travel, usually with my partner Daniel, and as a host for our apartment in Potts Point as well as on behalf of my mother when she travels and her great apartment in Rose Bay is vacant. 
As a guest I understand what it is to be a host and as such, I will treat your place with respect. 
As your host, I can then be in contact with you as much or as little as you like. Both properties have a key box so access can be within your time restrictions. I can be on email/text if needed during your stay.
I love travelling so it's great to have so many travelers stay at our guest house. I look forward to welcoming you! And I hope you really enjoy your stay in Sydney.
Currently living in the beachside suburb of Newport in Sydney.  Feel free to get in touch if you have any questions.

I have been welcoming guests to my B&B from around the world since 2000.  I love meeting people, travel, theatre, music and getting together with family and friends.  I have lived in the Manly/Fairlight area for over 30 years and love it!
Professional Real Estate Agent specializing in Short Term Holiday Accommodation in Sydney's East & Lower Shore

I'm a Sydney girl who loves my beachside neighbourhood but loves to travel. In fact I spend a fair amount of time in the U S of A these days. Life is magic and you've gotta get out there and see, do and love it all.
When not traveling or busting out some incredible yoga move, I work as a writer in the magazine industry and feel passionately about an organic life and fitness of body and mind.

We love Sydney and our neighbourhood in particular, enjoy sharing our home in Putney, entertaining our family and friends,  love reading and travelling,  listening to music, doing crosswords, watching our 2 little granddaughters discovering the world, patronising local restaurants on a regular basis with good friends, participating in art shows, and have lately discovered the older one gets, the quicker time passes!
   

5 things I/we can't live without?  Laughter and chat with a good friend, crossword puzzles (good for the brain), the sound of the waves on our little beach,  a great cappucino,    But the obvious ones of course, are family and good health, and we are blessed to have both.

We both love Europe, (and who doesn't?), Venice and Paris particularly, though we really enjoy pottering about in some of the smaller towns you find in France and Italy, that are a little off the beaten track.  We love "people watching" so are very happy just ambling around these smaller towns, sitting in a small cafe or town square, or poking about in interesting little shops, having a chat with a "local" and  finding out how other folk live.

I am a wife, mother, designer and Airbnb accommodation manager. I live and work in the Redfern/Surry Hills area of Sydney and love it! I have lived in the area for about 15 years with my husband and we wouldn't live anywhere else. We love to travel and are always looking for interesting places to stay. It's always so much nicer to stay in a home rather than a hotel, so we thought we should offer our loft to fellow travelers.

Hi there,
I'm Simon, a musician from Sydney, Australia. I'm married to the wonderful Amanda  (she's a singer) and we have a little boy Joey (he can be a bit cheeky).  

Anyway, we love music and laughter and would love to have you stay in our lovely place.  We love the vibe of our home and hope you will too...

Besides the music obsession, we are both keen travellers, there's only South America left to add to our list.  Our fridge gives you an idea of our love for travel (if not cheesy fridge magnets) from Japan, Thailand, Vietnam, France, Netherlands, Czech Republic, Germany, Italy, Spain, Tanzania, South Africa, Canada, Mexico, US, UK etc,etc..

Anyway, if you have any questions about our place, just send us a message.  
Cheers
Simon

I love living in Lilyfield with my beautiful family. Just 5mins to Sydney city with enough space for the kids, close to the bay, fabulous pubs and restaurants, weekend markets and wonderful shops.
I am now hosting two funky studios on Bondi Beach as well which is so exciting. It is such a vibrant area of Sydney which makes for a great holiday!
I look forward to taking guests through all the amazing things the innerwest, eastern suburbs and greater Sydney has to offer and then leaving them to explore, enjoy and relax.

Our two children have now moved out of home during term so we thought we could rent out their bedrooms. We have a lovely pet rabbit Fred. We are both very active people who like running in the nearby Centennial Park.

Hello and welcome to Sydney! I was born in Sydney but grew up in Sydney, Vienna and Paris and am fluent in French, German, Italian, Spanish and English. I am in the film/ television industry and also teach Yoga. Yoga and healthy living are a big part of my life. I love to experience, live and understand life to the fullest and I am delighted to share my beautiful space with people who want enjoy the best that this city has to offer and find a lovely urban sanctuary.

I am a  self employed French teacher who has been living in Australia for some time now. I enjoy travel both national and international - anywhere that takes me off the beaten track. I also appreciate wine, and spending time with a good book in my garden. 
I look forward to welcoming you and hosting you in this special part of Sydney.

I live in Sydney, Australia. I work as a university lecturer, teaching teacher librarians how to run libraries and teach their students how to research. Airbnb has been a delightful new experience in my life, both as an Airbnb host, and in travelling staying with other people.  Our trip to US saw us staying in Airbnb homes in San Francisco and New York, and in France we stayed in a beautiful Airbnb place in the Loire Valley.  We've stayed in Airbnb homes whenever we travel, whether in Australia or overseas. I love to travel, and really like the sense of belonging you feel when you stay in an Airbnb home anywhere.  I try to offer that sense of belonging in my own apartment, when I have Airbnb guests.

I am in my 40's with a background in law and politics, and currently work as a political adviser.  I love to travel, and manage to get overseas at least once a year.
I have friends in the building and neighbourhood and spend my weekends doing bunch, coffee, dinners out, concerts and movies.  
I often travel to the Blue Mountains at weekends to spend time with friends.
I travel interstate for work from time to time.

Professional guy that loves to travel!  Enjoy discussing travel stories.  I have lived in Sydney for 15 years and love the city.

Always keen to chat about the sort of experiences you would like while staying in Sydney and help to plan Itineraries.  Whether it be a visit to Circular Quay or the Museum of Contemporary Art or perhaps a visit to the beaches of the Central Coast or down to Kiama to see the blow hole.

Went to school on the Gold Coast in Queensland and have family there, so may be able to help with forward planning your Australian trip.

Have also lived in regional centers in New South Wales, Victoria and Queensland - happy to advise holiday spots.

fields.location: North Narrabeen, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I left Australia yearning for adventure. 7 years later I returned, with alot more than I left with; a British Husband, a gorgeous 2 year old son and another on the way! I now have 3 gorgeous kids who have changed the way we travel, but i can't wait to show them all the world has to offer.

When I am not thinking about travelling I am dreaming about it, but there really is no place like home. Having seen most of what the world has to offer, there is nowhere else I would want to be than right here. Beaches, lakes, National Parks, fantastic climate and easy going people is what it is all about.

My ultimate dream destination with Hubby is Tahiti. Waking up 'in' the water in an overwater bungalow is my idea of heaven. We never had a honeymoon so I might have to start to make this happen!

Dream destination with the kids is the Serengeti. Life changing trip for me over 10 years ago now, and I want them to see how life really is, and to appreciate all that they have.

We are a multicultural couple regularly spending time in Europe to visit family, however currently residing and raising our 3 children in Wahroonga, Sydney. We are both open minded and easy going people, enjoying exposure to different ideas and cultures and a relatively simple and sustainable lifestyle.

I am Livia, Brazilian Australian, married to a lovely Chilean man, mom of 2 ridiculously cute babies and proud owner of the softest american staffy.

Big fan of travelling and taking the family out to enjoy Sydney's beautiful weather. Also a big fan of reading, relaxing at the beach and an ocasional glass of wine.

This flat has been my home for 6 years now and I absolutely love it. 
We bring a real Home feel to the unit by keeping it clean and tidy.
Waldorf Australia & NZ Group provide selection of furnished & Serviced Apartments accommodation in Australia & NZ
Professional on vacation looking for a local's view of the places I stay in.

French / Australian single female - enjoy yoga, singing, bush walking, good food and wine, friends and travel.

Life motto, make everyday count, carpe diem.

I am a German artist who's been living in Sydney since 2003.

I like snorkeling, traveling, kayaking, camping, walking, photography, the beach and circus. 
 (Website hidden by Airbnb)

fields.location: Berowra Waters, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I am the CEO of a Conference and Event Management company based in Sydney, and my wife Penny, is a lecturer at the Australian Institute of Music at Sydney University. Our son Harry is in Class 11. We love to travel and spent 6 weeks in France, Germany and Italy last year staying at AirBnB's, where we learnt what is important in a place to stay when on holidays. Things have to be clean, have charm and be comfortable, relaxed, have style, fun, attention to detail, and, be close to the things that made the destination attractive in the first place.
We get a great deal of satisfaction introducing our guests to the beauty and lifestyle that our locations have to offer and to share our local knowledge. Our aim is to make your time at our place very special.
I can't live without good coffee, good food, good music, good friends, good wine a good heart and good intent.

fields.location: North Bondi, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: My husband and I are co-founders of an Australian start up here in Sydney. We love the community here in North Bondi... the organic bakery on the corner with the fresh bread every day, the best coffee at La Piadina and only minutes walk to Bondi Beach.
I am a professional, open-minded and interested person which loves traveling, connecting with people and food:)

I am an avid traveller and like to share stories of interesting places. I was born in Sydney and lived here all my life except for a few stints overseas.
I live near the beach and love relaxing on the beach and swimming in summer.
I often have international students staying at my place so am very use to hosting people from overseas.

Airbnb is built on relationships. Help other people get to know you.

Tell them about the things you like: What are 5 things you can’t live without? Share your favourite travel destinations, books, movies, shows, music, food.

Tell them what it’s like to have you as a guest or host: What’s your style of travelling? Of Airbnb hosting?

Tell them about you: Do you have a life motto?

fields.location: Croydon Park, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
A friend of mine told me about Airbnb and it sounded like a great idea. I am originally from the UK, I have three younger siblings, two in the UK and one in LA, so I am away a few times a year seeing them and figured it would be a great opportunity to rent my place out and help pay for those expensive flights. 

After my first airbnb hosting experience renting my whole place was a success I figured I should get some use out of my spare room whilst actually living in my apartment too. Friends who are hosts have told me about some of the cool people they have met and it sounded fun. 

I have lived in Auz for 8 years now, have become a citizen and intend to stay here for good. Bought the place I am offering just over 4 years ago. Its a great place, and not a bad location but with Sydney prices I couldn't afford a space this nice by the water on one salary... However, as the reviews will show, it's ideal for a family or group of friends to use as a base exploring Sydney and NSW or visiting friends or family of their own, likewise for a single person or couple just renting the spare room.

I'm a self employed creative. I'm kind hearted and easy going. I like to see the goodness in people and life in general. I like to get out and about for walks, discover new places, go to galleries etc. One of the highlights of life that make it superbly interesting is meeting new people to have a good laugh and share stories.

fields.location: Potts Point, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Hi my name is Sharron and I live in the trendy suburb of Potts Point, Sydney. I am someone who loves to travel and experience foreign cultures and I always find that your accommodations whilst travelling can either make or break your holiday. It is whilst I am away from my home that I would like to make available my lovely home. I am immensely fussy with my home so I am only looking for tenants who will treat it with the upmost respect and care the way I do.
French Australian living in Sydney

I work in a private hospital near home.I love the place I live in because of the most beautiful surroundings.I love nature,the ocean and long walks along the coast.
I spend my free time reading books,designing home decorations,making photos.
I would love to welcome you to my house.

I am an inner city Sydney girl who has a dining walk business where I take  visitors & locals alike to four different restaurants in one night in Surry Hills, Darlinghurst or Potts Point.

Sharing food is a wonderful ritual that brings people together for daily meals and special events. I love the conversation that happens over a dining table and the sharing of recipes and food knowledge.

I mostly travel back to my original home of New Zealand - always happy to share tips on where to go in Auckland - and around Australia. Melbourne is my next favourite city.

Bit of an art house cinema buff and often have soundtracks from my favourite films on high rotation on Spotify.

I am keen to go on a big trip one day and check out the worlds major cities: New York, Rome, London and Paris.

I love to meet new people and love sharing my apartment with friends and family. I enjoy working out, socialising, networking, as well as running my own recruitment business. I am really looking forward to welcoming visitors to my home.
Aspiring writer and frequent traveller, movie buff and enthusiastic cook.

Hi my name is Ho-Yan and I am from Sydney, Australia. I was brought up, live and work in Sydney most of my life.

I enjoy travelling, food and a drink here and there.

We are a married couple from Sydney Australia who live to travel. Most recently added a baby girl to our travel team and are so excited to show her the world. 
We have visited over 30 countries across Europe, South America, North America, Africa and Asia but call Sydney Australia home. 

Attempting to live like a local is our preferred way to see a city. Food and experiencing the culture is at the top of our priority list when visiting a city. 

We are renting out our own home to give others the oppurtunity to experience our way of life. 

Next big trip; Croatia, France, Slovenia, Bosnia, Dubia and Italy. (This time with our 9 month old). 

Life motto - "I haven't been everywhere, but it's on my list"

fields.location: Bondi Junction, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I'm from a large family and lived in shared houses both in Sydney and overseas for a number of years, so I'm a pretty easy-going guy who is use to sharing his home with people.

I actually grew up in an iconic Bondi Beach backpacker hostel (Noah's Backpackers), which was my family's business for 20 years, so I'm well acquainted to sharing my home with travellers and making sure they feel welcomed and comfortable. I do genuinely prefer my guests feel like it is as much their home as mine. 

I'm a fairly well travelled guy with more than 50 countries to my passport (not that I'm keeping a tally... okay, yes I am, it's 53), so I'm always up for sharing travel stories.

As a born-and-bred Bondi local I'm also a wealth of knowledge of the area.

I look forward to welcoming you to Chez Billy!

Living in beautiful Bronte, I cherish my walks up the coast from Bronte Beach to Bondi Beach. I also love that I can walk to Bronte beach pool for a quick swim anytime I like. The best time is during the week when it is quiet.
I try my best to lead a healthy life and I've just started getting into Green Smoothies! 
After a recent trip to Paris for a month, my family and I have caught he Travel Bug. We enjoyed living like the locals and hope that others will feel the same when they come to Bronte. 
I love reading and watching movies, dinner with friends and weekend getaways.
U.K musician from London living in Australia

Hi, 

I'm a young professional living in Sydney Australia. I am now a seasoned Airbnb host with over 250 reviews with a 100% response rate. 

From the first day of joining the Airbnb community, I've taken pride in making sure my guests are comfortable, stress free and are enjoying all that Sydney has to offer. Communication is paramount in developing a trusting relationship between a host and guest and I have always attempted to provide exceptional service and communication with my guests from the moment of their first enquiry. In short, my wife Karen and I try to make our guests stay in Sydney as close to perfect as possible. 

I am well travelled, having been to the USA, Europe, South East Asia, Middle East, Central America and many others. Travel is our passion to say the least so I know what my guests are going through when they are in a foreign city. When we travel it's all about the food, bars and water views. 

My wife and I love the areas we have our two listings. We couldn't recommend better areas to absorb the buzzing Sydney city lifestyle! Local knowledge is the key to enjoying the best food in both areas of our listings so if you have any questions regarding our apartment in Darlinghurst or the house in Leichhardt and need any suggestions with where to eat or drink, just shoot us a message and we're full of advice! 

Looking forward to meeting my future guests!

Mitch

Hi, I'm Ainsley,

I'm a working mum of two kids (10 year old boy and 8 year old girl). We live with a lovely flatmate in a spacious 3 bedroom garden apartment in Kensington (a central suburb of Sydney).  Sometimes our flatmate goes away and she is happy for us to airbnb her room.

Having recently retired from running a small retail business on the Northern Beaches, my wife Margie and I are now concentrating on hosting guests in our lovely self-contained cottage.   

Learning from our own experiences of staying in self-contained accommodation when we have travelled, we have endeavoured to create a warm and comfortable environment for our guests and provide them with great facilities and plenty of information.  We feel that having a home base when spending time in one destination, gives you the chance to explore the area properly and then be able to put your feet up at the end of the day and relax and choose whether to eat in or out. 

Our interests include travel, art and music, movies, catching up with friends, and, of course, great food and wine and our beautiful local beaches.

We consider ourselves as an affable, easy-going couple who love to meet new people.
Welcoming host who wants you to enjoy the beautiful surrounds at Coogee Beach

Raised in England, emigrated to Sydney to enjoy the good life & so glad I did.
Relaxed owner looking for tenants who appreciate the uniqueness of my apartment and would treat it as their own.
Love family time, contemporary architecture, skiing. boating & the great outdoors.

I am a busy professional with a just as busy social life.
My philosophy to life is its short and it should be spent doing things you enjoy.
I'm easy going but very sensible.  I love a good laugh and spending time both professional and personally around people that are inspiring and have a similar sense of 'don't sweat the small stuff' and are practical.

My wife is originally from Perth, and I moved from my hometown Munich via Singapore to Sydney in 1999.  We are both professionals working from home, so can typically help you with questions on short notice.

Born and raised in Sydney and love to travel.

Especially love NYC .... the pizza my favourite

I love Airbnb as it makes travel more affordable and comfortable for people... a little home away from home.

My first experience was in Miami where we stayed at a place on South Beach. So nice to be able to chill out in your own pad with kitchen, wifi etc. Will defiantly travel that way in the future.

I have been a host for about 3 years now. I have welcomed guests from all over the world. I also get guests from people that live in the area and want a place for family that are visiting from the UK. 

I know Sydney well and will do my best to give you tips of places to go and anything else to make your stay an enjoyable one.

In the unit I have left a compendium with some FAQ and my fav places along with some tourist brochures you may find of use.

If my place suits your  needs your welcome to instantly book or if you have any further questions just message me and I will respond promptly

fields.location: New York, New York, United States
fields.about: Sydneysider, now living in NYC.
Hi I'm Vanessa, I'm 37, an Architect, was born and bred is Sydney Australia. I bought my apartment in December 2011 and love it so I know you will too.
Australia
I'm an entrepreneur, biohacker and overall health geek. Love meeting new people and having novel experiences.
"Live every minute, Love every moment"

I am a professional photographer, based in Sydney. Australia. Covering lifestyle subjects such as Food, Interiors and travel, mostly for magazines and books and advertising clients. Born and raised in Sydney, I do love to travel and I have been lucky to have done a lot of that both personally and professionally. 
I enjoy making things and have always got a project on the go
Cooking is another great passion of mine. Hence the offer of baked goods and homemade jam!
Please feel free to email me with any question you might have.

My husband and I live in our stunning apartment in North Bondi. We love to relax and enjoy the luxuries our apartment has to offer. Watching movies with a good home cooked meal is a popular way to enjoy our evenings. And if we're not eating at home then we're out trying a restaurant recommendation. 

We love to travel and experience different foods, cultures and lifestyles. When we get the chance to go on holiday we will always try to go somewhere new and undiscovered. 

We are big family people and love to spend time with our family as often as possible. Our friends also play a big part in our lives and we invite them over regularly and host dinner parties and movie nights.

I am an international interiors journalist. I love beautiful houses and write stories about them from all over the world.

I spend time in London each year also which is great fun!

I love swimming in the ocean right opposite my apartment as much as I can during the summer - you will love it too!

We are a small family (male, female, 11 year old girl). We run an online organic food business in Sydney which keeps us very busy. We have a spare room in our apartment and thought we would put it to good use by renting on airbnb. So far we have met a diverse range of people from all over the world and have had a great experience.

Hi, I'm Jacqui.  I get a kick out of experiencing new places and meeting new people. When I'm not travelling, I marry awesome couples in Australia. I also love returning to some of my favourite places in the world: London, Paris and Berlin and catching up with old and new friends. Besides travelling and weddings, I love the outdoors - be it ocean, bush, forest, desert or mountains. I also love happening cities, independent films, all types of music genres, local fresh food, good red wine, swimming and yoga. Being part of the Airbnb community has bettered my world in so many ways!

Originally from the UK, I have lived in Sydney now for over 30 years. Some years ago I opened an art gallery. Some of the works I collected hang in the apartments now
We closed the gallery the other year so we could travel more. 
I started the apartments before the gallery as a place for visiting family and friends. Then I listed them and I have been busy ever since. I love having the apartments and meeting guests who are often visiting relatives in the area. People come back time and again and become friends.
Hi! I'm from Sydney, Australia, well-travelled, love writing and photography, teach Pilates, currently working on a master of philosophy in peace and conflict studies.

Like you, I travel quite often and rather than staying at expensive hotels we book holiday rentals whenever we can. So, I understand the traveller's expectations and more so, I try to offer flexibility to accommodate your journey and make it pleasant and flowing.

I live 5 minutes away from the house in Napoleon Street and it is easy for me to jump in the car and come to help you with the keys, the internet connection, or whatever comes up! The house has been offered for short stay rentals (through another holiday rental website) only for a year now, and the guests who have stayed there have all enjoyed their time in Napoleon Street. And I have really enjoyed meeting these guests.

Rozelle is a great neighbourhood with the charm of these little streets, the many parks (big and small) to take my dog for a walk to, the waterfront, and some of the best bakeries, patisseries, and cafes. The people in the street are all community minded people.

I also enjoy preparing the house for the arriving guests and thinking of these little details that are going to make their stay comfortable.

fields.location: The house is 10 minutes from the city by public transport and walking distance to harbour beaches. We are also in walking distance from shops , cafes , restaurants and a theatre. We offer overnight bed and breakfast style accommodation in the two upstairs
fields.about:
My wife Helen and myself have lived in this house since 1978 and have raised three children here. They have gone of course leaving a fabulous private upstairs space available for guests. We are both semi retired and lead an active outdoor life swimming daily at nearby Balmoral Beach in Sydney Harbour.

With two bedrooms and bathroom for exclusive use of guests our space is suitable for overnight stay but not ideal for an extended stay when the the common areas of the house would be used extensively .-

Hi, Martin here...
I'm a 49 year old well travelled Sydney local.
I work in Television, creating Closed Captions for the Deaf and Audio Description for the Blind, plus various multi-media platforms around that…
My interests include… reading, writing, movies, music, architecture, metaphysics, spirituality, water and living in the great city of Sydney. 
Other things I like are cheese and purple... (0;
I'm a hoster and a hostee and a home owner so I'm well house trained, responsible and polite.
Cheers

fields.location: Cronulla Beach, New South Wales, Australia

fields.about: test contact v2

I am a sculptor and  moved to Australia from the UK in 1989 and have 2 adult children.

I like simple comfortable design that works from an aesthetic, spatial and functional point of view.

I love the flat as is so handy to everything - it is just seven minutes walk across the Domain to The Art Gallery and there are regular buses to the City Centre. The local night-life is vibrant and there are many bars and restaurants to choose from.

fields.location: Stanmore Sydney when I am not travelling
fields.about: I have recently taken a redundancy from work after 24 years working in Museums in Sydney and wish to spend at least half of the next few years travelling. Renting my lovely apartment will be hard because I enjoy spending time there but it is necessary to help support my travels. I love reading & am interested in art, architecture, design, opera, ballet , classical & early music. I love walking in the countryside & my feet have always been my main form of transport. Never owned a car but love horse-riding & animals generally. Grew up in the country but love Sydney too.

Born and bred in Sydney.  I am a cabin manager for Qantas so fly internationally at least once a week.  My apartment is modern, minimal and clean.  I bought the apartment in 2011 which I absolutely love.  
Aside from my job, I love to travel.  I try to get away as much as I can.
Married couple from Norway. Living in Sydney, Australia.

Alan is a retired architect with an interest in family history, and Ursula is a lover of Renaissance drama, researcher of green sickness in Shakespeare and colleagues. We are grandparents to six beautiful children. We have lived in Paddington, Sydney for the past forty years, and looking forward to many more to come.

fields.location: Whale Beach, Sydney when not travelling as I retired from the EPA in mid 2012
fields.about: Loves outdoor life, jogging, walking, sightseeing, reading, film, theatre, fishing and sport (especially rugby). Married to Tina who shares most of these interests and also loves swimming and Pilates.

Hi im Anthony and i live with my partner Jeab in my North Sydney apartment. I have lived in this apartment for 4 years.
Come and stay. I love having guests in my apartment and have 1 spare bedroom for your use. I do everything I can to ensure that you enjoy your stay. 
I love to travel and meeting people from other countries is great. 
I enjoy being outdoors -bush walking and ocean swimming are my favourites.
Come, relax and enjoy this special part of Sydney that is so close to the best that Sydney offers. 
Favourite travel destinations would be United Kingdom, but looking to explore more of SE Asia in the future such as Cambodia,Laos and Northern Thailand.
My favourite TV shows would be Game of Thrones and the Sopranos.
I love Thai and Indian foods as well as a good Aussie BBQ.
Also my partner can speak Thai.

im from Sydney and i live in colourful Kings Cross ! i enjoy going out with friends for a few drinks and a nice meal ! 
I enjoy morning walks down to Rushcutters Bay 
I love spending quality time with my cat 
 i love tattooes and being pretty left of centre !

I am a freelance journalist and married to Will, an actor and sculptor.  I enjoy pottering in our large garden and grow my own vegies (or try to, anyway). When travelling we like to get away from the well-trodden tourist trail and experience real life wherever we go, so the airbnb option has great appeal for us, as does hosting our own B&B in Sydney. Our guest accommodation is a delightful studio in the garden with its own entrance.

Every guest and tenant is special to us and we like nothing more than our guests to feel right at home with quality Sheridan linen, fluffy bath and beach towels, luxurious bath robes along with providing other little comforts to make your stay a 5 star memorable one! 

We are very sociable, but provide guests privacy & can provide best spots to dine or site seeing. We have a beautiful young family with 2 x amazing little girls and we are energetic & love many sports such as swimming, dancing, water skiing, surfing, gym, bush walking, cricket & we love to travel & discover new destinations.

Angela is a very talented and accomplished singer/entertainer with a degree from the Australian Institute of Music in Sydney (AIM) along with a fashion degree, child care degree & is also an amazing cook & loves her fitness.

Kevin works as a very successful Senior Award Winning Property Buyers Agent with Propertybuyer and has been involved in over 1,400 property transactions during his 24 year career working with multiple strategies such as subdivision, development sites, duplex/dual living, renovate for profit, investment properties, high yield, high growth, commercial, locating ideal properties for owner occupiers and investors. Kevin has helped hundreds of people build wealth through property, and feel free to chat with Kevin if you have interest in property to discuss how he can guide you in growing wealth through a property portfolio. 

We believe in Carpe Diem - Live life to the fullest

fields.location: Surry Hills, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I'm a 30-something gay guy working in the Arts (which is almost an oxymoron). I travel extensively for work, so my place is often available when I am not there. Sorry that at times I don't know months in advance whether it is going to be free, but do ask!
Hi, I am a interactive producer. I love travelling, meeting new people and having a good laugh. I am pretty laid back, easy going.

Married to a builder, we have resident chooks, and a Jack Russell. I love my garden, passionate about the area we live in, and happy to share some local knowledge. love to bush walk, camp and kayak in the beautiful waters we are surrounded by. Like to spend as much time as I can with our 3 daughters and 5 grandchildren

I have created a great place to live, in the best part of Bondi, in the best city in the world. I would love people to share and experience the fortunate life and surrounds I am part of. 
30 seconds to shops and transport. 
2 minutes to the best part of the most amazing beach in the world. 
The garden and day bed are a tranquil escape, with nothing behind, except for trees, greenery and the cliff to the ocean. 
I like a good tunes and an occasional beverage. Join me for a bbq on a warm night. Watch movies. Check out the stars on the day bed. Take the snorkel and jump off the rocks and swim with the fish. Some of my favourite things... 
If you are feeling really adventurous, a morning run at sunrise on the beach and coffee at Icebergs is the best.
I am an accomplished marketed / agency leader and work a lot in strategy and creative as well as progressive, innovative areas - digital, technology, social, AI. But I am happy to talk about anything from food, philosophy, technology, the future, culture or sports. Open minded people are very welcome of course.
I am out or away a lot, but would love to meet interesting people like you and chat and give good advice to in order to enrich your experience whenever possible ;)

Enjoy trying new food. If I haven't tried it, I'll eat it! Can live without beans & carrots though. Like traveling when i can, always drawn by bright lights. Love the sun in winter, foreign film & a little bit of pool (playing). Wish the world could be more equitable.
I am retired, but like meeting new people.

I LOVE WHAT LIFE THROWS AT US, THE UNKNOWN EXCITES ME, EXERCISE, NOURISHING CONVERSATIONS,TRAVEL , DIFFERENT CULTURES, LIVE SHOWS, CONCERTS, FOOD, LOVE  RESTAURANTS AND WRITING REVIEWS ON JOURNEYS AROUND THE WORLD IN  5 STAR ACCOMMODATION. 
MY HOUSE IS MY PERSONALITY - WARM AND INVITING.
I TRAVEL QUITE OFTEN AND IT'S NICE TO HAVE PEOPLE STAY FROM ALL OVER THE WORLD HEARING THEIR STORIES, FEELS LIKE I'M STILL AWAY.
I AM ON  OTHER SITES FOR TRAVELLERS WANTING A CONVENIENT PLACE  CLOSE  TO THE AIRPORT  / 20 MINS TO CITY BY TRAIN, 15 MINS BY CAR.
WHEN YOU LOVE WHAT YOU DO, YOU NEVER WORK A DAY IN YOUR LIFE - FOLLOW YOUR PASSION

Lisa lives in Victoria and started in 2008 with a couple of properties she owns in Victoria and Queensland. In her previous career in the amusement business, she travelled regularly and found a lack of clean and affordable accommodation. 

Therefore she started focusing her activity on enhancing the traveller's experience and creating 'home away from home' experiences for guests. Lisa loves interior design and puts this passion into each and every one of the properties we have available. 

Celeste lives in Sydney and works with Lisa to provide guests with round the clock communication for all guests.  

Together we are dealing with almost 3,000 happy guests per year and focus on providing an excellent, easy experience for our guests. 

We look forward to hosting you in one of our properties!

I'm originally from Toronto, Canada, and have been living at Clovelly Beach, Sydney, with my partner Natsuko, for nearly 3 years. I've been in Australia for over 25 years. I'm a science guy and work in health promotion in the city designing and evaluating national programs that target health professionals.

Natsuko is originally from Japan and works as a hair stylist down at Clovelly Beach. She has lived in Sydney since 2007. Natsuko and I love to travel, explore new places, buy art at auctions and hunt down great Italian restaurants. We prefer to feel like we're at home on our travels and not in a soulless hotel. 

We love having guests stay with us and will do all that we can to make sure you have a great time in Sydney. Our aim is to provide a place for you that feels like home.

I’m addicted to travel 100+ countries to date ..I don’t even know where I come from anymore :) Consequently my lovely crib is often vacant close to beaches the cool parts of town & 10 mins from the airport. If I’m home I’ll gladly give you the top tips for sydney but I sometimes forget your staying and sing badly in the shower !

Hello,

We are creative, down to earth and open-minded couple, who enjoy a healthy lifestyle and a vibrant home.    There are much happenings in our home, from photo shoots, to art salons to creative dinners and occasionally short film making.

We have been greeting and hosting guests from all over the world, for just over three years. We host a wide variety of people from all over the world.  Our home is a unique step into an old world reality, and we enjoy sharing it with others.
