As an alternative,  if you are after the privacy of a one bedroom Paddington pad, have a look at our listing at: https://www.airbnb.com.au/rooms/3795958?preview

We hope you enjoy your time in our home!
Arnie & Lorraine

I am a single parent of two lovely boys, Gabriel and Louie and we live in a lovely downstairs floor of a duplex in Randwick, near Coogee Beach. It is airy and spacious, with floating boards throughout. Gabriel has just left home so I am renting his bedroom to airbn'b.  The communal table is now on the deck and it is a share space. A healthy self serve breakfast is included.
 I am a trained Chef and after running business for 13 years and working in the hospitality industry for 25 years,  I have decided to have a break from the kitchens. After grabbing a diploma in Fine Arts 2 years ago, I decided to spend more time painting but I still cater from my kitchen at home.
Our home is clean and usually quiet. I would prefer to rent the room out for max 7 days at a time but this is flexible.
We do not own a TV.  We offer wireless fast internet.
Don't hesitate to ask any other questions relevant to your stay

My husband and I are Sydneysiders, we have raised our children here and are very settled in our Birchgrove home.
We worked for many years in hospitality industry and still love meeting new people.
As we have just sold our sailing boat however we are very involved in the local Balmain Sailing Club.

I have travelled quite a bit and lived in London, England. Love shopping, movies, books, travel, eating. 

Journalist, editor and blogger.

My favourite books are Michael Connelly's crime novels, mostly featuring LA detective, Harry Bosch but also books about another famous Harry, Mr Potter.

Hello
My name is Remo.
I am happily married since 1988.
We have 3 beautiful children.
I am from Italian heritage.
My family loves to travel and when we do we really like to experience the place that we visit as the locals would.
We enjoy reading, photography, walking, cycling, gardening, skiing, snorkelling and swimming at the beach. We have both stopped working and are looking forward to trips overseas in the future.

Hi my name is Steve, I work in car insurance and live in Balgowlah with my wife.  We are heading overseas for a month this year and I am looking to rent our place out while we are gone.

I am a very keen surfer so I love our place the local area, its close to many great surfing beaches, shops and cafes and has a really relaxed vibe.

Hi, my name is Joanna. 

Contact (Email hidden by Airbnb) if you're interested at staying at the terrace in leafy Roseville. I'm originally from the UK, and if you haven't visited Sydney before, you're in for a treat!

I work in Design Journalism. And write short films. 

I have one son. His name is Batman. He is a Mini Fox Terrier. 

My favourite city in the world is Amsterdam. 

I was born in Adelaide. 

I speak English and (broken) Spanish. 

I love meeting people from around the world. Airbnb has allowed me to meet and greet so many wonderful souls from so many places. 

Each review I have received means so much to me and I remember almost every guest. 

My Elizabeth bay property is not currently available, but I am now hosting my beautiful, 2 bedroom bungalow in Sydney's Lewisham.

fields.location: Forest Lodge, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I am a Sydney girl born and bred, so can advise on places to go and things to do according to your interests. 

UrbanOasis Studio is the city pad I had to give up when my children came along. I plan to live there again once they have flown the nest!

Arcadia Cottage is my escape from the city just over an hour away in the Blue Mountains.

i'm 50, work in TV, love the beach, friends, travelling, good food and great wine...and i love my home and will respect yours.
i would love some info beforehand...on great food, wineries, markets, must-do restaurants, lazy strolls, energetic hikes, fabulous shopping, shows not be missed, bargains to be found etc. 
thanks.
Beach and food lover

I'm from Manly beach in Sydney and love being in, on or near the water all year round. I enjoy travelling and discovering new neighbourhoods and the local favourites. Being a host or a guest, it's the small things with a personal touch that count.

Easy going female, moved back to Sydney in 2011 from a 20 year stint in London.
Have been living in Glebe for just over 5 years now, I chose this place as its so close to work, city centre, transport & shops. Love Sydney!!
I like to keep fit & healthy, do a couple of gym & yoga classes a week. Like to hold dinner parties, like to kayak, ski and sail (having also circumnavigated the world).
I like to watch TV, reality, comedy, crime scene investigation, documentaries (David Attenborough) & go to the cinema.
Have done an extensive amount of travelling and yet have so many more places I would love to see. Currently am travelling around Australia with my partner in our motorhome. The reason why I'm airbnb-ing my house for the duration of my trip away.
I love the idea of staying in someones home when in a new city/country and I want my guests to feel like my home is theirs for the duration of their stay.

Hi I am a friendly outgoing active person who loves working with people and inspiring them to follow their dreams and passions.

I love living in Cronulla with its wonderful beaches and community living.
I have four grown up children and now have the freedom to get involved in the things I enjoy doing. I love going to the gym, walking my dog and dancing when I can. I work in career education at a Catholic school and also run woman's programs at TAFE. I am currently working on starting my own business in Career Guidance and delivering a program called re-invent yourself. I can live without friends, family, community, beach, adventure and meeting new people

One of my favorite sayings is.....
“The future belongs to those who believe in the beauty of their dreams.”
― Eleanor Roosevelt

I live in a beautiful apartment on the beach. I am a teacher by profession and have taught in Australia and Papua New Guinea.I have now moved out of the classroom and teach swimming with the Department of Education. I enjoy ocean swimming,cycling, playing my guitar and above all, travelling. I love meeting people from all over the world and learning about their culture. Airbnb gives me the opportunity to share my home and meet interesting people from all walks of life. I have 3 beautiful children and 8 grandchildren who I adore. Some of my favourite travel experiences have been,Trekking in Nepal and Peru and Cycling in Austria, Spain, France, Vietnam, Italy and Corsica. My motto in life is "Always look on the bright side"
Professional creative family living between Australia and America.

Hi, I discovered Airb&b when planning a trip last year. We had a great time and stayed in 8 listings in 2 continents. I took my time choosing places and it paid off. All the 8 listings were very good and a few were outstanding for different reasons. All the hosts were genuine, caring and interesting people.We took care of their places and have been invited back to all of them. What more can I say? As a guest traveling the world I know I was looking for a good sleep on a comfortable bed and a pleasant outlook that felt safe so I could enjoy being a tourist .The fact that we also met lovely interesting people and that I didn't break the bank with Hotel prices, well that was good too.I can confidently offer you this with my studio listing and its location is perfect for accessing the city, universities and beaches.
I love nature and enjoy nurturing my garden and other creative activities. I can point you in the direction of art galleries and good live music.

Hi, What can I say other than I am 39 years old, professional female in a relationship. Very easy going. I just recently renovated my whole house, pretty much a knock down job so new everything. I heard about air B&B and thought what a great idea. I have a clean house including a great kitchen so feel free to make yourself at home when you stay with me. Just let me know if there is anything in particular you may need. This is also the perfect room to shut yourself away in if that is what you'd prefer.

Family of  2 adults/2 girls. Ian owns a design and brand communication company in Sydney and Los Angeles and Kristin is a film producer. We have 2 daughters ages 16 and 18. We love skiing, surfing, travelling. We go away together as a family frequently often visiting Byron Bay, Noosa Heads and Thredbo. We love food, dining out and tend to go away to places both here and overseas where we can immerse ourselves in food culture and great eating. Ideally we would would welcome guests in our house that appreciate a beautiful home, and being in close proximity to the worlds best beaches as well as amazing restaurants.

Freelance photographer and fine woodworker from UK originally, got married to Iva last year and together with are beloved cattle dog, Pheonix, we now live between Sydney and Mullumbimby.  If you are interested in my photography, please search for steve back photography and you will find my site, it will not allow me to write it here.

Love AIrBnB, both using it and renting out my spaces on it.  Always have had really great tenants and stayed in some great places.

Hi 
I am Liliya, live in Sydney,  Australia. I am an owner of cosmetic clinic in Sydney CBD and been working as a cosmetic  practitioner for a number of years.
Travel is my passion and I try to take vocations as often as I can to be able to explore the world and get familiar with the new cultures.  
When I am on my holidays I dedicate my time to local art sceneries: museums, concerts, theatre performances. I like being out and meeting new people.   
I am very social person, but like my privacy at the same time. I am very tidy and clean and have a lots of respect for people personal belongings. 
When I am looking for accommodation, it has to be “warm” and comfortable, conveniently located close to local attractions and public transport. 
I travel on my own most of the time, so I will be out a lot. Also I am not a smoker. 
Hope this information will give you a bit of idea of who I am and I look forward to hearing back from you soon!

I have lived with my husband Chris in Bundeena for 28 years, bringing up our two sons who have now left home. We are artists and educators. We love photography, music, food, movies and travel, and believe you are never too old for the next adventure.

fields.location: Surry Hills, New South Wales, Australia

fields.about: Originally from Hamburg, Germany we have been in Australia for 17 years now and have turned into a small family. We travel frequently, and while we are away, we rent out our house to contribute to the cost of travelling.

fields.location: North Sydney, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I'm a young Sydney based woman, working as a Cellist and teacher full time. I enjoy traveling, and do a fair bit of this for work within Australia and sometimes further afield. I love living in Sydney, trying new places to eat and go out and soaking up everything the city has to offer.

I work in the IT industry and live with my husband in Sydney.  My interests are travelling, furniture upholstery restoration, movies, books, dancing, gardening and alternate life style.   

I love connecting with people from all around the world.   You get to meet some great people.  We have hosted guests from all over Australia, France, Germany, America, Canada, Sweden, Britain, Norway, New Zealand, Australia, Japan, China, Singapore, Malaysia, India, Sri Lanka, Pakistan and Bangladesh.  All of them are unique and have been wonderful guests.

I love travelling and always looked for holiday accommodation where I felt at home.  My goal was to set up Sydney Amazing Holiday Home Bridal BnB, a place where people will feel at home, relax and be themselves.  I made sure that the accomodation would be a place where I would be happy to stay if I was on holidays, a place where I could relax and unwind and be energised.
I am from Sydney and  compete in Showjumping as a hobby based in Berry NSW
I love travelling and this is a must do every year!
I enjoy cooking, meeting new people and playing tourist guide. I have a car and love to show people around the city and outlying areas.

I'm a full time creative professional. When I am not working in Sydney I am traveling the world!

My home of 15 years is immaculate and very well maintained - it was renovated between September 2013 and January 2014 and furniture is constantly being updated. 

It would suit a professional single or a professional couple without children. Not suitable for those wishing to hold parties.

Hey,
I am french living in Sydney and work as a hotel manager. I like enjoying some moments with friends in a cafe or at the gym... I like travelling all around the world and meeting new people.
Engineer/Designer

31 year old male from Sydney, Australia. Seasoned traveller. New York is quite possibly my favourite city in the world (apart from Sydney). I'm very spontaneous and don't like living life by routine or schedule. I love food, coffee, eating and hunting for new cool restaurants and bars. I have a wonderful fiancée who loves to travel with me when she can.

fields.location: Potts Point, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
Welcome to Sydney! 
I travel often for work and pleasure, therefore am able to offer my lovey one bedroom appartment in the heart of Potts Point for rent while I'm away.
Overlooking leafy Ward Avenue, its 5 min stroll to the train stattion, the Kings cross night life, the beautiful rushcutters bay park and marina, a 20 min stroll has you in the heart of downtown Sydney or a 5 min train.
The Appartment has a large airy bedroom with queen size bed, hanging space, a seperate lounge dining room, with 42in tv and dvd player, full kitchen. Shared coin operated laundry, or the drycleaners across the road! Full bathroom with a bath ladies! 

My space is my sanctuary from work and I love its bright airyness and the potts point village life. Markets on the weekends, cafe's open at all hours, fabulous bars clubs and fine dining if you wish for it. 

I hope you get to enjoy it as I do!
M

We are a family with 3 children aged 17, 16, and 14. We aim to do what we love and love what we do. Living outdoors as much we can, exploring, meeting new people, and spending time with friends and family. We both work from home when the children are at school. Having spent time travelling around Australia and overseas, we love having guests share our home.

My partner and I are born and raised in Sydney. Even though we love traveling, we always love coming back home to Bondi Beach. My girlfriend is an actress and I am an executive for an internationally well known sporting organization.

I live with my partner Jeff. We are both professionals working full-time but are quite relaxed and easy to get along with. We love food, gym, tennis, theatre and the occasional night-outs.

We will respect your personal space but are quite happy to interact with our guests as well.

We love travelling and are respectful of other cultures.

My husband and I are from Hong Kong. We've lived in Sydney for over 30 years.  We love traveling ourselves and usually spends half a year visiting a new city or country.  Our home is your home when you're with us as we'd love to meet other like minded travelers!

I'm a film producer and publisher of Australian audio books.  Amongst the other bespoke 
tourist services our company provides, we have the two luxe Coogee apartments which we let out to travellers.

I love to travel, and hate to pick favorite places, as there are too many!

I work in TV and film in the production side... which is convenient as I live next to Fox studios.

Life motto would have to be... "Work to live, live to travel"

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I work in retail selling luggage.  I have a husband and two teenage children.  We enjoy watching our children play their sport Rugby Union , Basketball , Netball and touch football.  Our favourite thing to do together is to go to watch Rugby League games  together.  Oh and we love to eat too ! Mainly Chinese food.

Our favourite holiday destination is Hong Kong !

The price in high season is $150.00 a night and if there is a booking of less than 2 weeks then that price stays constant. If the applicant wants to stay a minimum of 2 weeks then the price per week drops to the Airbnb accepted percentage.

I'm from Sydney Australia and love the beach and outdoors!!
 
I currently work in marketing and have been lucky enough to have the opportunity to live in NYC working in advertising. 

I also love to travel and experience different countries and cultures.

Hi,  We are Jessie and Craig. We're fun, relaxed, creative types and very house proud.  Craig and I have created a beautiful, unique, art-filled home and we are happy to share it with like-minded travellers. 
We both have fine arts backgrounds.
We love yoga and healthy living.
We love travelling and have visited Europe, most of Asia, the USA, Brazil and have recently returned from Cuba and Mexico. 
We love to return to sunny Sydney and to our lovely home.  We trust that during your stay you will respect our home and our art, furnishings and belongings, and our neighbours.  
You will have a wonderful time in Annandale and Sydney.
Jessie and Craig.

Hi I am a singer, masseuse, yoga teacher and celebrant , travel and music are two great loves along with singing, skiing and eating ginger.
This past year I've been in Brazil, Cuba, Laos and Bali and improved my Spanish and salsa dancing living 2 months in Cuba - so feeling invigorated and grateful to be alive; also partial to massages (daily if possible!) yoga, going to the gym, meditation, swimming and listening to good music...I really enjoy meeting world travellers and helping them see Sydney in an affordable, fun way!
Manly resident. It takes a lot to get me to leave! I love the buzz, beaches and people!

I'm a young professional with a passion for the city I live in and a love of wining, dining and entertaining. I'm extremely sociable, fun, friendly people and enjoy nothing more than to share all my inside tips on Sydney's best restaurants, bars and night spots. (I've tried them all!)

I've lived in beautiful Kirribilli for almost nine years and think it is the best place in the world to live. I absolutely love having people over and seeing their jaws hit the floor when they eye our amazing view of beautiful Sydney Harbour. It's an ever-changing view we never, ever get sick of!

When I'm not working we love socialising either out and about in my beautiful city and all of it's incredible bars and dining spots, or shaking up cocktails for friends in my apartment, or firing up the barbecue on our rooftop!. My motto is you only live once, so you might as well do what you love!

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Professional, easy going, loves to travel

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: After growing up in Melbourne and doing a 4 year "rite of passage" in the UK I settled in Bondi Beach over 10 years ago & love it. I keep myself busy in my spare time by swimming, surfing & running and volunteering as a lifesaver at North Bondi.

fields.location: Potts Point, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
My name is Emma, I'm 37 and have been living and working in Sydney for the past 9 years...and almost a citizen! Originally from Ireland. Love making a house a home, travel, meeting new people and anything outdoors (swimming, hiking, camping, yoga!) Favourite travels spots include Guatemala, Tasmania, France and Ireland. Can't live without time in nature, weekend getaways, good wine and home cooked food. 

I'm clean and tidy, social yet independent and reliable.

fields.location: Potts Point, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I am a Veterinarian in my own practice 2 blocks from the apartment; frequent traveller; over 40; interested in art, culture, architecture and food. I stay nearby with a friend when a guest wants to rent my apartment, so I am always available to help out. Because I work every day, guests need to be aware that it may take me 1/2-1 hour to meet them to check-in, and for check-out we need to arrange a mutually convenient time.
Im a professional Actor, Musician and AirB&B host who resides in Leura in the Blue Mountains just outside of Sydney.
We are a semi-retired couple and have a lovely spare room that we are happy to offer to travellers - we love to meet people and share experiences. All we ask is that our home is respected.

My wife & I love rugby union, traveling, good food, theatre & the movies, golf, family and friends - and our lovely Waverton village environment. 
We travel extensively & spend much of our time (i) at our Hardys Bay house on the beautiful NSW Central Coast, and (ii) at our house in Dunsborough, Western Australia, close to the Margaret River wine region. Both are available for rental. In fact, returning guests within 12 months will receive special pricing if we are reminded at the time of their next booking.
We invite our AirBnB guests to share our three lovely homes and invite you to plan a future Itinerary to include stays at each of these beautiful locations. 
Ros & I will do what we can to ensure our guests’ stays are memorable and enjoyable (even helping create a great Itinerary especially suitable for those staying 7 days or less), and will do what we can to ensure you enjoy our homes (& cities and localities) as much as we do.

Emma, from Sydney. Like outdoor activities, meeting new people, being creative! 

I really love the idea of shared resources. Why shouldnt others enjoy this fabulous place, whilst in the comfort of a home environment rather than a hotel? Whilst my unit is occupied by respectful guests, I hang out on my boat. That means that when I live in the unit, I can ensure that it is kept to excellent standards, ready to share.  I really love living in (Website hidden by Airbnb) feels as though I have finally found a place I can settle . I have travelled widely and have a deep respect for all cultures and ethnicities. 
I love meeting new people and am eternally fascinated by how diverse we all are. 
I may get to meet you if it suits us both when you check in, otherwise I will leave instructions for self check in. Either way I am never far away and always happy to help or ask questions. 
Enjoy!
Energetic and open, kind and funny, straight-forward but shy... Young professional female always looking for new challenges and adventures. Obviously, I loooove travelling!

I am 60 years old, a builder/Musician working on Terrace renovations in Darlinghurst which is a a suburb next to the City. I like to stay fit by riding my old ten speed around, swimming and Yoga. I love the City and use all it's facilities. I also attend C3 Church and am involved in the Music team playing acoustic guitar and mixing sound.
I have 4 wonderful children a 27 year old son living in New York, a 23year old daughter in Western Australia, a 14 year old son and 10 year old daughter here in Sydney.

I'm from Sydney Australia. I'm a theatre and screen director. I travel regularly for work and fun. Non-smoker, non-drinker. Respectful & responsible. 

When I'm at home I rent the second bedroom in my apartment and when I'm away I rent my entire apartment.

Love to travel and meet other travellers. I've been to over 40 countries and have lived for 9+ years in three. So I'd like to think that I'm quite familiar with most cultures of the world. Easy going, friendly, and respectful. 

I work during the day in a big bank, and after work am mostly doing other types of activities!

The outdoors is much better than indoors, but sometimes its nice to relax and do nothing.

Hobbies: Running, music, exploring, freediving, movies, eating and laughing!

Favourite places:
Mongolia
Iceland 
North Korea (not really a 'favourite' but definitely an eye opening experience)
Japan
Greek Islands
Cambodia
Tanzania
North America 
Philippines
And Australia

Hope to meet you all one day on this blue/green planet we call Earth!

G'day!
Amazing apartment minutes from iconic Bondi Beach.

A little from column A, a little from column B...

Lover of good food, wine, adventure's and company. 
Traveler - open minded - laughter seeker
Yogi -  surfer - nature loving -  finance worker

Sydney has been my home for almost 7 years now and I’m still loving this beautiful city.  Glenn grew up here so he’s as local as one can get. We both work full time and enjoy spending the weekends doing outdoor activities or just chilling at home on a wet rainy day.

I am English, living in Sydney Australia. Married, two daughters. I used to produce science television. I  now bring together an international  conference of people who produce and broadcast science and history television. It is a  unique window on the world and enables me to travel extensively - mostly in Europe and North America, but also recently in Malaysia and China. Our family is passionate about food and wine and we all love to cook. I also love biking and walking, books and theatre. If you stay in our apartment we can give you great leads for enjoying the best Sydney has
 to offer.
Hi, my name is Yen and I live in Balmain. I love this little village where there is a great local feel and character about the place. Come and find out for yourselves :)

fields.location: Palm Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
Well travelled host, classic Baby Boomer, chucked in a successful corporate/executive career many many years ago to embark on a life of rolling mid life crisis and bucket list fulfilment A self confessed motoring enthusiast with a broad  penchant for the classic and unique, don't do 'normal' cars.  Never did grow up and not planning on doing it any time soon !!! A typical Saggitarian ... I can resist everything EXCEPT temptation

My B&B motto is "A traditional style B&B that's run as a lifestyle, not a business ... and it shows"

Life is great.  I have 2 beautiful children, an amazing husband and a great career as a handywoman.  We are keen sailors, campers and generally outdoorsy people.  

As a host, I try to give our guests maximum privacy while still being available to answer questions or deal with issues should they arise.  As a guest, I'm very respectful of the places we stay and know what goes into a changeover so try to help out where I can.

I grew up in Sydney and have finally returned after many years living in various parts of the world - France, USA, UK, Singapore.  Airbnb has enabled us to keep the travel bug alive within us.

Hi, my name's Lloyd and my partner is Clare. Welcome! We have lived in Sydney for over ten years. We love art, design, docos, food and nature, and hope you might enjoy hanging out in our place. We just finished renovating and look forward to sharing our home with you. Life motto?.. It's a big life, think, talk, be awake and be happy.

Hi I'm Charmene. I heard about airbnb through a friend of mine and thought it's a great way to advertise my place to share with those who want a cozy unique traveling experience, as how I enjoy traveling myself. I'm artsy and have a love for secondhand things as you'll find in my place.

I'm a Swedish viking enjoying life under the blue sky in the city of my dreams. I kickbox, hike, bike and run every chance I get. I'm a bit of a health nut, slightly addicted to greens. I consider a couple of cucumbers as perfect long haul flight-snack and if I got stuck on a deserted island with only avocado + coconuts I would be a happy girl. But don’t worry I also love to bake Swedish delicacies such as Cinnamon rolls and ”Semla” and I make a mean Espresso Martini. Passionately love Sydney and try to visit a new restaurant, cafe, place every week to stay up to date. Happy to give you all our recommendation on everything from best bar, perfect pre-work run, must do´s etc. Beside from Sydney other favorite destinations are: Copenhagen, Palm Springs, anywhere in the Greek islands, Hawaii or why not a snowy ski slope finished with hot coca! Hope to meet you!
Lives in Sydney
Hi everyone, I am looking forward to welcome you to Sydney in the near future!

Jonny is originally from London UK and Sabine from Hamburg Germany. We met and fell in love many years ago in Sydney, where we still live now. We are both designers: Jonny owns his own digital design studio in Surry Hills & Sabine works as a graphic designer in advertising. 
Besides the work that pays the bills Jonny is learning to become a furniture maker and Sabine is doing photography. A few other things we love to do: Surfing, cycling, camping, cooking & adventures. 
We have been using Airbnb for a few years now, as hosts and guests and think it is a wonderful way to get to know an insider view of a new place / culture and meet great people.

I am a researcher working on Renewable Energy & Solar. 
I have a great passion for traveling and music. I play percussion & hang drum and do meditation & yoga practice music.
I try to maintain a loving, kind and compassionate attitude towards myself and my surroundings.

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
Airbnb "SuperHosts" which guarantees 5 Star Experience, Fast Response & 100% Commitment. 
We are a local couple with 2 kids who have lived in Bondi for over 20 years.

We have travelled the world but also know the in's and out's of the local scene.

Ask "SuperHosts" Nick or Ivana about surfing, swimming or sightseeing. We also know the best local cafes, bars, restaurants, markets and shopping!

We have now been rated as Airbnb "Super Hosts" which means we are experienced hosts who provide a shining example for other hosts, and extraordinary experiences for their guests!!

I am from Sydney but originally born in Chile.   My job keeps me busy, i am in Finance working for one of Australia's largest bank.  I own my apartment. I am a non smoker and love to travel myself so i love AirBNB as its great to meet people from all around the world

I am Sydney based designer/maker of interior products, travel frequently to the UK, Japan and holiday to other locations.  I bought and designed this apartment in Sydney in the year 2000, letting it as holiday accommodation since then.

As a guest I enjoy staying in private apartment of other hosts in different countries to experince the life style, as well as discovering new hotels and resorts.
I love art, music, trekking, nature, festivals and sharing food and wine with family and friends. I love travelling but I also love coming home and that makes me feel pretty lucky.

My husband, Mick, and I have two young boys aged 6 and 9. We love living in Fairlight and enjoy going for a surf before work, even in winter. Our home is comfortable and cosy and very indestructible, accustomed as it is to small curious children.

Hi, I'm a born and bred Sydneysider and after many years travelling and exploring our beautiful planet, finally came home after realising the grass isn't greener elsewhere, just gloriously different... 

We are lucky to be bringing up our kids in this safe and beautiful place with its diverse and active community. It's a busy life but great fun and we love the opportunity to share our beach lifestyle with others if only for a week or two!

fields.location: North Bondi, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Married to an amazing woman with two beautiful children living the dream by the beach in Sydney town..
Sydney Australia

I feel very lucky to live in Avalon Beach on Sydney's Northern Beaches where I rent two properties close to the the northern end of Avalon beach. I hope you get a chance to visit & enjoy our little piece of paradise!

Avalon Beach Retreat is a 3 bedroom beach house perfect for families or friends and Avalon Beach Break is an villa/apartment, ideal for couples. 

Both are less than 100 meters to Avalon Beach. 

My aim is to provide accommodation and service that goes beyond my guests expectations. I want my guests to feel completely at home so they can enjoy the kind of holiday I like for myself-happy & worry free!

I look forward to hearing from you and perhaps meeting you in the future. 

Warm regards,

David

I'm a 48 yr old Irishman, living in Sydney the last 15 years with my wife, Sue, and our two kids. Play football (loose description) in the winter, swim in the ocean in the summer.
Happy to have people in our house and hope that anyone who decides to stay in our place enjoys it as much as we do.
Anything you need to know, please ask.
Phil.

We are a family of four who love travelling and seeing new things. Originally from England we moved to Australia in 1997 and love the outdoor lifestyle and the climate in Sydney. We love to go sailing or bush walking and just love living where we do down by the water.

Hi there
My name is Kylie which, not many people know,  is actually an Australian aboriginal word for Boomerang. 
I bought this apartment decades ago because I loved the area and wanted to close to the city and my work. It’s such a melting pot of interesting culture and entertainment, but also a real community. 
For over a decade I worked at the Art Gallery of NSW which is a short walk from the apartment. I’d walk into work every day and most days do a quick walk at lunch time around the Botanical Gardens to take in the view of the Opera House and Harbour Bridge. 
I moved out when we had our baby and wanted to be closer to family. We love doing Airbnb as we love hosting and it keeps us connected to the area.
Designer. Traveler. foodie.

From Sydney Bondi beach
Play water polo
Organize events

Hi! We are a recently married couple who live in the beautiful city of Sydney. I was born and raised here and spent 5 years living and working in New York City, where I met Sheena who is originally from Mumbai. 

I'm an Engineer by trade and Sheena is in fashion. We are very friendly, easy-going and responsible as well as neat, clean and tidy! When not designing a super tall building or styling for the next top model we are fairly relaxed and like going out to bars, restaurants and going to the beach.

My family time is precious to me.  We love spending time together in our beautiful home.  We spend a great deal of time outdoors - even in the cooler months.  We love to light a fire and sit around it telling stories.  Sharing a delicious homemade meal with family and friends fills me with joy.
I am currently living in Sydney, working and playing all over the place.

My room is the best, I go away often, found the room originally with airbnb, I am very happy here. so I know you wont be disappointed .

My room is light and heaps of space, enough for the short stay traveller.

I am Australian, and travel alot with work, I like meeting like minded friendly people.
Fun loving guy with style who's easy to get on with and will try anything once.

We are a family of 4 with 2 teenage boys. 
We love our home, travelling and being active together.

fields.location: Dangar Island, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: We are used to international travellers as my husband was a well known opera singer in Europe, so feel assured that any special needs will be catered for.  Looking forward to meeting you. Ann
We live in sydney and love traveling the world and experiencing new food!!

gregarious person living life as fully as possible. I live in Sydney Australia and when I'm not at my day job I'm a freelance writer and photographer. I love to travel,  and feel equally at home in downtown Manhattan or the great outdoors. I have been known to spend hours waiting to  shoot a scene with the right lighting.. weird right? I love locals telling me the best places near them to visit.. 

I started using airbnb a few years ago and realized how much I enjoyed staying in peoples places and talking with them to find out what was happening in their area so I now offer back this service.

My pleasure is to travel and to help other travellers.

I'm one of those fortunate people who have travelled a lot and lived on several continents. That means I have extensive personal experience of what is needed to make a stay enjoyable for guests and for hosts.  

I spent the 5 years to 2012 living part-time in Sicily and in Australia..  In this next 5 years I'm focussing on volunteer work as my travel model and have recently returned from working as a volunteer zoo keeper in Belize - a great adventure.

I'm an outgoing person and seem to always have some new project underway.  My past includes being an academic in Australia, studying in the U.S., setting up a not-for-profit bookshop in Italy and managing a horse farm in Canada.  My range of interests is just as diverse, especially if you add in my being a parent to grown-up children.  

I live by myself, am currently in the middle of an occupational course on community service, work as a volunteer at a radio station and happily socialise in my other moments.  I'm reluctant to describe myself as 'retired'.

I genuinely look forward to meeting you.

Dear Julia,So glad this is sorted now. Where are you coming from, and how will you travel?
Can give you directions from the airport, closer to your arrival. Beatrice
Welcome to Manly! Situated just steps from the sand, this apartment is a home away from home.
Large size quiet room in a great area of Sydney, very central location.
English but live in Sydney Australia

I am from Sydney, Australia and I love good food, sailing, wine and exploring new cities around the world. 

I am a very hospitable host and my house is always clean, comfortable and welcomes new guests.

I like to live every day to the full so I am a very busy guy.

Eve has lived and worked in Sydney all her life and knows all the best places to eat out and what to see

Eve loves being with family and friends, traveling, music, theatre and reading

Eve and her partner Brian live in the main house and are friendly and welcoming. They have two daughters studying to be teachers at University. 



Eve and Brian do have two Maltese cross poodles (Ella and Willie). They're part of the family and are harmless, but they will seek you out and try to make friends with you

We are an activity family who's lifestyle revolves around the local beaches given the surf & sporting activities.

We travel like we live, "beach casual" no matter if it is Cape York or outback Queensland.
I'm an adventurous outdoors person who loves the sun, ocean, mountains and bush.

Whilst originally from Auckland, New Zealand, I grew up in Australia and now live with my girlfriend, Lizzie here in Sydney. I have been fortunate to travel throughout my career and lived in Australia, UK, Asia and the US, however we are now settled in in Sydney - for the time being anyway!
Lizzie and I spend our time enjoying the local area with friends and spending time outdoors which Sydney is brilliant for!

A fun loving mature lady who loves to travel with a group of close friends, mainly Europe Asia, likes dancing music, craft markets, Church or community volunteering, keeping up with technology important and also current events to keep mentally active & be able to communicate effectively with guests.
Expect a host who may go out of her way to help or do everything possible to make someone's stay a memorable & comfortable one.  In return,  respect and honesty expected from our guests.
THANK YOU for visiting our site & hope to hear from you ASAP.  nina

Hi! We both love travel and enjoy using AirBnB as guests and hosts.  We trust that any guest in our home will love the modern facilities, and the ease of checking in and having an instant comfortable, cool, relaxing sanctuary.
Have traveled using airBNB and think this is a fabulous place to share your own home with fellow travelers. Come and enjoy...

Active, optimistic,mature woman with an interest in people and a love of life.
Warm secure  family and friend  relationships. Loves animals, reading, theatre, walks, travelling, meeting new people.  
My life motto which was strong in my family is all about tolerance, acceptance, nonjudgmental attitudes and an appreciation and engagement in people and life.
I like to read and meet new people.

I'm a Sydney-sider born and bred and love this city.
I also travel regularly and would like to rent out my apartment while I'm away!

Currently living in Sydney, Australia. With a travel bug in my bones ive explored beautiful, dangerous and awe-inspiring parts of the world and plan to explore a whole lot more. Love this city, am biased but do think it is one of the best and love to have people come and visit it. 

Feel free to send me a message if you have any questions!

I'm a writer, editor and actor. I love living in Bondi and I love travelling. In recent years my husband, Murray, and I have travelled through the US, spent two months  in Sri Lanka, stayed in Istanbul then drove down the west coast of Turkey, and then travelled to Italy by ship via the Greek island of Kos. All wonderful experiences. I am now learning Italian in order to return with a bit more ability to communicate in the smaller towns I prefer.

fields.location: Surry Hills, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Born and raised in Sydney, Surry Hills is our favourite neighbourhood. With so many amazing restaurants and bars it is hard to visit them all. You will usually find us trying a new restaurant or bar on weeknights. On weekends we like to try and get down to the beach for a run and then have a late brunch locally. We love to travel and seize any opportunity we can get. We have been to most continents but our favourite places our Italy, South Africa and the U.S. (California). We used to live in San Francisco but have returned to Sydney and proud to call it home. There are few places that have the right mix of city, beach and nature and Sydney allows us to experience them all.

I'm a Sydney based professional working within the events industry in a role that requires frequent travel.
Having lived abroad for 10 years, I love being back home in Australia and consider Sydney one of the best cities to live.

From Sydney, love to travel and explore Australia and neighboring countries. 
Like to unwind with friends and family.

I'm Cain and my partner with full-on Disney hair is Ryan. We're both decent fellows that mothers think would make great boyfriends for their daughters... but you know that is bittersweet ;) I'm a graphic designer/photographer, while Ryan works in aged care. 

We've travelled a lot in our 7 years together, and our next spot is to join you in your home!

My wife and I love to travel. We have 3 adult children. I worked in the IT Industry but am now semi-retired and my wife, Daisy is a Deputy principal at a local school. My interests are music (I play in a classic rock band), photography and travel. I also enjoy technology and dabbling with computers. Daisy enjoys gardening and loves her dog, Koby. We both enjoy  TV and movies for relaxing and love going to see musical theatre.
We have hosted many students in our home in Sydney and have thoroughly enjoyed the experience in cultural exchanges.

I enjoy travelling,meeting people and growing relationships and know how wonderful it is to find fantastic accomodation that suits the Budget. Sharing part of our house is one way of supporting others in their travels. You'll find me to be warm, hospitable generous and caring.

fields.location: North Bondi, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
Rob: into cycling and fishing. Just learning to sail. 40 year old accountant working for Westfield ( Shopping Centres)
Sarah: Into running & occasionally cycling! Enjoy camping, travelling, the great outdoors & socialising with friends. Work in training for Elizabeth Arden
I'm a Sydney-based, UK born artist/curator. I've been living in Bondi for the past 10 years and love it.. the beach, bars and great healthy food.

My husband Stuart and I bought our North Bondi apartment in 2012. Living here feels like being on holiday every day, but as frequent travellers, we're pleased others can use our home to have the same holiday experience.
I'm an Architect who works in the City. I renovated this apartment in Potts Point.  If you have any questions about the area I'd be happy to answer them!
We are a mum and daughter who love travelling the world and love sharing our favourite place - our home and Sydney - with guests.

fields.location: Hurlstone Park, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I'm a happy, friendly, creative person with an adventurous spirit.
I've done quite a bit of travelling in the last 4 years  and much of
my accommodation has been with airbnb - so much better than a 
sterile hotel environment.
My experiences have helped me in setting up my own airbnb listing. I want
it to be a lovely, comfortable and restful place for travellers to come back to at the end of the day and feel at home. Feedback so far tells me I'm on the right track!

Hey there,

My name is Ito (short for Itohan) and I'm currently undertaking a Masters in Clinical Psychology.
 
I grew up in Sydney so have plenty of insider information and tips on where to go/what to do.

I enjoy good food, good books, good films, good music etc etc…!

Looking forward to meeting you!
We are  a retired,writer, and  a psychologist. We travel often , and  enjoy sharing our home with like minded people.
Sydney, Australia

We are a family living on  a unique 25 acres in Sydney . We have 2 daughters. 25 and 23. We have travelled to many countries around the world - enjoying many of our stays with air B&B also have lived an interesting life working in the Australian film industry from 30 years. We now run an importing business from Bali and our property is similar to a Balinese village .we sell water features furniture giftware etc from our property.
We love meeting new people and enjoy their travel stories. 
We are  close driving distance to various towns Windsor, rouse hill, dural etc.
Also situated on our property is our private rainforest which is a lovely peaceful area for our guests to chill out .
We look forward to meeting you sometime in the future.
I am a New Zealander who lives in this home with my wife and 2 kids.

I love travelling and have a beautiful house that has various times of availability depending on my children.  I am from New Zealand and if you are plannning a trip there after Australia I can certainly help you with that.  
I love a bargain and can guide you to fantastic cheap restaurants, charity shops (if thats your thing) great bush walks that are easily accessible from the nearby trainline.  They are absolutely exceptional.  I work as a Special Needs teacher and I  am interested in cognitive psychology, philosophy, reading and spend any spare time writing.

Am a creative, homeloving, book loving,theatre loving ballet loving , travel loving soul. A well known local identity  I  run my own millinery business locally and have lived in Balmain for 28 years.
Cant live without my family , memories of my travels , dreams  of future travel, and my creativity.
I am from Adelaide, South Australia, and work as a Software Developer at Telstra. Looking forward to meet you!

I live in Maroubra with my amazing husband and our dog, Harris. I love to walk by the beach and draw energy from the ocean, then head back to the real world.
I do this so I can travel as often as possible.
I love Travel more than anything else in the world and as we were looking for places to stay in Paris & San Sebastian it occurred to me that we could possibly rent our place in Sydney.
I'm a scuba diver, I read A LOT, my husband and I go to a lot of live music gigs, I've seen almost everyone I care about. 
I own a Digital Marketing Consultancy that works with not for profit organisations to help them give their supporters a better experience online and raise funds for their cause. I choose to work in this space because I can put my whole heart and mind behind these causes. I'm not interested in doing anything that doesn't make the world a better place. One step at a time, right?

My wife Nadya and I – both keen travellers ourselves – have lived here together for the last ten years after extensively renovating the house. We run our graphic design business from our home office. Nadya comes from London, and I've lived in the area for most of my life. When not pushing pixels around, I also lead the TEDxSydney photography team on a pro bono basis. 

We have a great deal of local knowledge to share: be it the burgeoning food and wine scene, local entertainment venues and historic landmarks, or the abundance of great bush walks nearby.

We feel very lucky to have such a beautiful place to live in, and love sharing the space via Airbnb. Every experience we've had so far has been fantastic. It's a great privilege to be able to host our guests: it seems that almost without exception we meet as strangers and part as friends. We'll do anything we can to help you get the most from your stay.

We're both very easygoing, and love introducing guests to our favourite local morning bush walk under the Northbridge bridge and down to the waterfront at Tunks Park. Put on your hiking shoes and join us for an easy 5km round trip before breakfast... There's no better start to your day!

I have lived in sydney for 20 years, originally from New Zealand and now work as an Bhutanese textile specialist and also work part-time in a hospital as a registered nurse.
I love all the good things of life and am particularly interested in the arts, (painting) and music.
I love yoga, swimming, snorkling and other outdoor activites.

I'm from Mexico City, but I've lived in Sydney for the last 10 years. :)
The 5 Things I can't live without are: Music, Exercise, Organic Peanut Butter, Books and Movies.
My favourite place in the world (so far) is Sydney.
Sydney Australia

My husband and I are "young"50 something,enjoying family and friends, the outdoors,good food and wine!
Steve is an osteopath and I'm a teacher/mosaic artist/beachvolleyball coach:)
With our boys out of the nest,we like to travel as much as possible!

Hi there,

My name is Catherine and I am a Sydney based vocalist, cabaret artist and producer.

I am an avid traveller, lover of photography, meeting new people, music and the arts.

I look forward to hearing from you.

Regards,

Catherine

fields.location: Bondi Junction, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: My wife and I are retired educators who love to travel to visit our children and grandchildren who live overseas.We are very house proud and our home is very well maintained. We often exchange homes with travellers from abroad and care for their homes in the manner with which we would like our own home to be treated.

fields.location: Sydney Olympic Park, New South Wales, Australia

fields.about:
I love Newtown and have lived here for many years so I know the area extremely well. I like to think of my guests as people who are visiting me and always try to be available for assistance.

Have met some really lovely people through Airbnb and hope to meet many more.

My aim is to provide accommodation that feels like a home away from home.

We are a husband and wife, who have lived, swam, educated our children and enjoyed the Northern beaches for over 20 years.
We are well informed about the area, and only  too happy to share any helpful local  knowledge.
We have been involved, through our children with Avalon Surf Club for over 15 years also and highly recommend the local beach.

I'm a 37 year old marketing professional with a deep rooted passion for all things adventurous. I'm a very sociable person who enjoys drinking great wine, eating fantastic food and chats with friends.

Hi. We live in Canberra and travel often to Sydney to see the rest of our family. We love our little Glebe studio and hope you will enjoy it too. It is in the heart of the village, opposite the University of Sydney and very close to the centre of Sydney. Usually we rent it out for more than two days . We are available anytime to provide advice or assist you during your stay. 
best wishes
Gail and Daniel.

Hi there,

My name's Wayne. I live in Sydney, Australia with my fiancé, Kate.

I'm a management consultant, an author, a commercial helicopter pilot and I've recently developed a real love of travel with time in LA, Turkey, Greece, London, Vietnam, Thailand, Camboodia, Bali, Hong Kong and France all in the last 12 months.

We've done quite a lot of share living both at home and abroad so we'd like to think we know what makes a good environment in a home.

Hope to meet you soon!

Wayne and Kate
HI, I run a furnished accommodation business.  i have done so for about 8 years now.  I have various properties in and around Adelaide as well as in the western suburbs of Sydney.

I have travelled in Europe, Asia and the USA and understand the need for well located, comfortable and safe accommodation. I live in beautiful Sydney and can help with advice on what to see and do here as well as other destinations within Australia. You will be very comfortable here - our guests really love the apartment and the area.

I'm Irish-born and live in Sydney. I have travelled extensively, including living in India for a period of time.  I love spending time with friends, doing yoga, escaping to the country whenever I can and international travel when time allows.

Hi my name is Kerri and I’m a Sydney-sider.  I love this city and the rich and varied experiences it has to offer. My life revolves around my friends, cooking, kayaking and my bookclub, as well as hunting out cute bars and restaurants.

I would describe myself as creative and adventurous. I studied art, but work professionally as a set designer and creative director on film, television and events; mainly the latter these days. I love my work. It is interesting and varied, with unusual and creative challenges.

Travel has been a great passion of mine, which I've been doing regularly since I was 13. For many years I travelled to different parts of South and Central America, where I stayed with local families and studied Spanish.  Living with the locals enriched my travel experience as it made me feel part of the community. 
 
It’s a great pleasure hosting travellers and sharing with them my knowledge of this wonderful city. Airbnb has a great sense of community, which I love. I look forward to welcoming you to the place I call home.
Bronte, Surfing and golfing.
We look forward to welcome you. We are sure you will find your stay in this special, stunning location truly memorable!

Living in Sydney, while exploring the world

Hi there! I am a professional, living in Sydney for the past 5 years. It's kinda a given - to be on this site - and profess a love for travelling, but it's true! 

Stepping off a plane onto new ground. Seeing new faces, absorbing smells and sounds of different cultures. The unease of exploring unfamiliar territories. Observing similarities & differences of communities across the world. And the taste sensations of food from local kitchens. All these inspire my constant need for seeing new parts of the world, whenever I can. 

And while I'm in between travel, I enjoy exploring my current home city of Sydney - the culture, night life, arts & music scene, beaches and bush. I thought, since I currently have a spare room, why not open my home to fellow travellers?  By making it available on Airbnb, I can continue to meet new people and experience different cultures via the people travelling through Sydney - best of both worlds indeed. 

As my guest, you will be welcome to treat my place as your home away from home, a safe & comfy place to retreat to while you're in Sydney. If you like, I would also be delighted to share little hidden secrets of Sydney that I'm continuing to discover - cool little bars, best local gelato, secret gardens, little known best view points of Sydney skyline and the Harbour Bridge - from around the neighbourhood!

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
We are from South Africa & Canada, and are happy to now call Bondi our home, together with Jerry & Kat Stevens (our furry friends).

We've used AirBnB for years, staying at great locations all over the world and are now having fun doing some hosting of our own.

Seeya!

We are a young family loving life in Sydney with three kids (one boy and two girls) under the age of five. We love travelling, cooking, exploring new places and lazy days on the beach. I work in health education and my husband is operations manager for a buildings company - together we make an interesting couple with a diverse set of skills and interesting stories to tell from both our lives and industries. We enjoy meeting people, and laughing together. Hospitality is important to both of us and making people feel welcome in the home we've been blessed with.

I live with my husband in Sydney and we spend time in our terrace house in Paddington (about 30 mins from Manly) and our beach house on the south coast ... 3 hours south of Sydney at a little town called Manyana.
Manly is a wonderful holiday destination - it is very relaxing, but still manages to have a palpable vibe and energy!!  Maybe one day we will be able to live in Manly full-time - definitely something to look forward to in the future :-)
We love to travel, entertain friends at home and enjoy recreational activities like snow skiing, and to keep fit, I go to the gym and like to walk on the beach.

A sassy senior.  Well travelled, well read and I've been an innkeeper for over 40 years - from backpackers in London to stylish and contemporary apartments here in Sydney.  Favourite travel destinations - Sri Lanka, France, The Maldives, New York City and any place I've yet to visit.  

I travelled overland from Sydney to London in the 70's across the Old Hippy Route so i've worn out a bit of shoe leather and managed, remarkably, to visit Burma, Afghanistan, Kashmir, Iran and all those hot spots that are now less accessible.  With so much in life, it's all a matter of timing.
Life Motto - Fortune Favors the Brave.

Professional female, creative and animal lover. I travel a lot for work, use home stays and B&Bs all over the world, and hope to provide a warm happy home for nice person passing through for a few weeks and to treat them with all the respect and care that I've always been shown on here.
Young professional female from Sydney, Australia.
Sydney Born. Travelled UK and Europe.

I am a warrior woman who is passionate about Fitness and Wellness and dance for joy, helping people reach their fitness and wellness potential, while earning my living most days in Sydney and anywhere I am in the world. I am married to Didier (from Paris) and we enjoy a life of family, friends and love of travel. 
'Choose your intentions well as your subconscious mind believes all you tell it.'

Hi my name's Sophie, I am from Belgium and I moved to Australia permanently in September 2012. I love to travel, especially when i can find great deals! I look forward to discovering new cities and people. Cheers !

fields.location: Horsfield Bay, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
I'm a Sydney native who has recently had a 'sea change' and moved a little further north, out of the big smoke.  I spend most of my time in the garden, at the beach or in my studio being inspired by the abundance of wildlife on my doorstep.

Favourite travel destinations:  Istanbul, London, New York, Uluru, Hong Kong, Grand Canyon

I'm a communications consultant and writer from Sydney, Australia. I love literature, cinema and food.
I live with my gorgeous 9 year old daughter, who is into the Borrowers and also a big reader. We have recently started gallivanting around the world and we love it.
We love our home and like the idea of sharing it with other people.

fields.location: North Bondi, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: If I'm not off on an adventure - I'm stuck in the fabulous 'Bondi Bubble'! My days are filled up with a morning swim, teaching yoga & getting inspired by my friends/family. I love meeting people, trying new things & sunset picnics!

We live in Sydney's inner west in a unique home and garden backing onto the Cooks River and parklands. We love living on the river, watching the bird life, taking in the sunsets, walking and riding to nearby parks, cafes and markets. We enjoy travelling as well as living in a vibrant, multicultural community. We enjoy meeting new people and sharing what is special about Sydney.

I live and grew up in the Sydney, Australia.
I love to travel throughout the world and understand the importance of having a comfortable, modern and clean home away from home.

Been leaving in Sydney for over 20 years,  I enjoy travelling, theatre, movies, nature, walking, and meeting people. I'm happy to help in any way i can, but you can be assured of total privacy if you just want to relax and do your own thing.

We live in Camperdown, Sydney. We think this is the best location in all of Sydney. Funky Newtown with bars, restaurants, shopping just 5min up the road. Beautiful Glebe, Annandale and Leichardt 10 min in the other direction. The city is a 5 min bus ride or half hour walk away. 

Watch the New Year's Eve fireworks on our extraordinary roof terrace - with 360 degree views across Sydney. Also BBQ, sun decks, gym, sauna, spa, lap pool, gym and tennis court - all free for you to use at your convenience. 

We take pride in our beautiful home with its high ceilings, wooden floors and industrial chic design. Enjoy spectacular Sydney in our beautiful home.
We are a family of four with busy lives. We are lucky to live in such a great part of the world and love the sanctuary that we've created in Bondi.

I'm from Mosman in Sydney - a beautiful area. I'm really keen to explore the cultural delights of the world and share my amazing part of the world with travelers.  On trips, I would be spending a lot of time in museums, galleries, markets.  Should I stay at your place, be assured that I would treat your home respectfully :)

I grew up in Sydney's inner city and still think it's a pretty magical place. I've spent one year in South America, one year in California and backpacked bits of Europe and New Zealand. I studied for a long time in the liberal arts, mostly theatre/gender/performance. Some of my favourite things are white balsamic vinegar, ocean swims, wandering open-air markets and dancing to Tom Waits' more tuneful numbers with my little girl.

Steve and I have been married 30 years and have 3 georgous kids- Jock 21 years old and currently at university.  Max and Lily who are both 18. Lily and Jock attend Uni at Bathurst so are rarely home.
I am an interior stylist which keeps me very busy. I love to exercise, play tennis , sail and am currently learning golf.
I love life and love to have a good time and love to entertain.

Rejuvenate, relax and unwind in one of our first class holiday properties spanning the entire globe. Offering a diverse range of accommodation, from tastefully modern apartments right up to magnificent 7-bedroom waterfront homes. Let us arrange everything for you, so you can just put up your feet and have a perfect unforgettable holiday.

I am a nice professional guy who has had experience renting a couple of high end properties places to vactioners for the past few years. I am into cycling (cliche I know), surfing and good eating. 

You will only see me when you arrive...and that's about it. I am quick to respond via text, phone or email so let me know if you have any problems. 

See (Website hidden by Airbnb) to look at the other place I own and manage - plenty of references there.

I am a fun loving, family orientated person who loves to travel and will spend months  dreaming of and saving for our next big adventure which  has varied between sailing between Greece and Fiji and touring India by train.
Keen traveller and friendly Sydneysider with an appreciation of what it's like to travel and crave those creature comforts!

Hi, We are Fred and Bernadette, married, with 3 young adult children.  We love to travel and have visited many different countries.
We enjoy spending time with family and friends and appreciate meeting new people.  I am into running marathons and Bernadette enjoys tennis, trail walking and is currently learning Italian. We are interested in different cultures, enjoy good food, theatre, going to movies, walking, hiking - most things in life !

I am a kiwi living in Sydney for the last 17 years. I love meeting new people so enjoy people coming to stay and I enjoy travelling myself.  My background has been in the performing arts and I continue to love that and my other passion is having people fulfil their own dreams.  I love personal development.  I aspire to being a cup half full person and life is about being the best we can be.

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I love to welcome you all to my beautifull apartments so you can have a more pleasent stay!!!

Australian - Colombian Living in Sydney, Fiance Manager for a holding group, on my earlier 30's. .

I like travel around the world, enjoy a good food, good company music and explore the cities in not a tourist view. 

Like Make new Friends and build relationships for life,  easygoing, friendly, down the earth.

I am an Australian man. I love to travel, and will take off on an adventure any chance I get. 
My favourite place in the world is Sri Lanka, apart from Sydney, obviously!
As a host, it's my home, not a hotel. So expect lots of personal travel mementoes around the place.

Hi I'm Andy - a Learning and Development professional who is a lover of travel, music and this beautiful city I call home.  I am originally from England and relocated to Australia back in 2006.

I have a passion for travel and am constantly trying to quench my travel bug.  I have traveled extensively throughout Asia, Europe, the US and Canada but no matter where I go, I like to immerse myself in local culture.  I really feel that it is the best way to experience a city or country.  And this is why Airbnb is such a great idea.  I have used Airbnb a number of times for my own travels and this was a really positive experience - and my partner and I have just started hosting which we are very excited about.

You'll find us very welcoming and friendly and we love to meet new people.  What better way to find out about Sydney than from a Sydney-Sider?  We will be more than happy to assist you in planning your itinerary whether it's local attractions, markets, nightlife or places to eat.  We respect our guests privacy and time alone, and will interact with you as little or as much as you like while you stay with us.

As a guest I am respectful, considerate, clean and friendly.  As hosts we expect similar qualities from our guests.  

 Read our listing for full details on our property and feel free to ask any questions.  We look forward to hosting you soon!

fields.location: Northern Beaches of Sydney, Curl Curl Beach
fields.about: Active family of 4, travel as regularly as possible to ski and surf destinations

I live in Sydney's beautiful leafy Eastern Suburbs with my husband.
The unique studio apartment is located within easy access to Bondi Beach & Centennial Park. We have lovely shops restaurants cafes & produce markets nearby.  Westfield Bondi Junction is 10 minutes walk away.  The exclusive village boutique shops in Queen Street Woollahra are also within walking distance.  The well know suburbs of Paddington & Double Bay are nearby. 
I enjoy travelling to Europe every year for extended stays to visit family in France & London.
I enjoy meeting people from all parts of the world & assisting them with their Sydney & Australian travel needs.
We have hosted many overseas & interstate guests & they have always been delighted with their stay. The main advantages being the location & total privacy of the apartment. It is in a quiet setting adjoining swimming pool & parkland  - you can even hear the birds sing.

Hey there!

I'm kat, love to see the world, based in Sydney. Easy going, friendly, love learning about people and cultures. I love to laugh and hang out with those who like to look on the bright side of life. 



My place: 
Located in East Redfern, the cool part of town - youll have access to: COLES, ALDI  loads of cafes, the infamous Dank St, Waterloo, plus loads of other shops. 
Extremely close to Surry Hills, Fox Studios...Very close access to buses on Cleveland st which go all over, plus we have the M20 and 301,303 buses that are closer and head into central and up circular Quay way.

The street is quiet, and green and leafy. The apartment has security. Lots of padestrian traffic on Bourke St, about 50m from our street. 

We prefer a non smoker.
No couples please.
3 bed apt, 3 girls.
Jamie and Jackie are loving living in the inner-city with their small family.  Looking forward to more getaways though!

Hi there I am Louise but you can call me Lou!
I work from home and run my own business and I love the freedom that working from home gives me. Having your own business we don't get to go away alot but
I am lucky enough to live in a beautiful area close by the sea so our holidays are right here on our door step Clovelly beach one day and Bondi the next.
I am a hands on kind of person and don't mind a challenge and taking on a project or 2. My recent project was taking on 3 chickens however we ended up with 2 Roosters so they have now gone but I would like to get some hens in the near future so I hope to be offering fresh eggs to you soon. So for now the vegetable patch is my project and teaching my kids the importance of fresh food and where food really comes from!
Please feel free to email me any questions you may have.

My little family live in Bondi Beach in Sydney,Australia.
We own two organic wholefood cafes, are very clean-living and respectful of peoples possessions and privacy.

fields.location: Bondi Junction, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: As a retired International Flight attendant, I love caring for people and making them feel very welcome and comfortable. I would say I go beyond the call of duty to make people have a memorable journey. I treat people the way I would like to be treated. I am a mother of two beautiful boys - only one lives with me. I am a very healthy and fit person. I love running on Bondi Beach.

I'm a writer and I work in digital content. I love socialising and meeting new people and I love travelling... which means I often leave my little apartment vacant for lucky visitors to Sydney. 

I'm happy to cross over from time to time though as I love meeting new people and taking them out for a drink. 

I'm very hospitable and clean and you'll be comfortable here - expect a welcome bottle of Australian wine or sparkling and some welcome food on your arrival. I'm also full of good tips for places to eat, drink and must-see tourist and non tourist spots in Sydney. 

Sydney is such an amazing city but a lot of the accommodation is not within the best areas - these seem to be reserved for the locals. I love this city and my area with all my heart and I promise you will too!

We are a couple with grown up kids and a large, friendly family home. We are experienced travelers, having lived in the UK, Canada, USA and Germany. We know what it is like to find your way in a new city and love to help visitors make the most of their time in Sydney.  We are keen cyclists and enjoy walking our beagle (Bella) in nearby Centennial Park.  We like the theatre and restaurants and know all the best places for coffee. If you are lucky we will show you our 1970's Mercedes Benz!
Easy going
Lovely little family with beautiful beach house to rent!
Lisa is a Professor at a local university and Mark is a research engineer. They live a quiet life, love the garden and enjoys spending time with friends and family.

Hi, my name is Timothy. 
I invite you to come share my lovely home with two beautiful cats Lulu and Smoochie. You will love it. Promise.

I am a very easy going guy who loves the beach, going out to see bands and riding my motorcycles.

I run a small company that provides product development and production services to the fashion industry. 

My great passions along with surfing are skiing and music. 
So far I have been lucky enough to fall down mountains in Australia, New Zealand, Canada and Japan.

I am a consultant by profession, working for Deloitte Australia. I love to travel and have been a hobbyist travel photographer.  Some of my work can be (Email hidden by Airbnb) or (Website hidden by Airbnb)

Born & raised in the Alps, I feel most comfortable on rock solid ground or snow. But driven by curiosity and a hunger for adventure I found my new home in Sydney and now indulge myself in the beach lifestyle. I visited many beautiful places in this world and will always choose a shared private home over an impersonal hotel room for accommodation. This is why I joined the airbnb community and made the best and most memorable travelling experiences using the sharing platform.
We love travel, adventure and meeting new people!    Even more, we love showing guests around our beautiful city...

fields.location: Dulwich Hill, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: A Masters of Anthropology student and Musician.

Hi there!

We are a friendly couple from Argentina and England and love living in the Eastern Beachside Suburbs of Sydney. 

We are an easy going, sociable, and active couple who enjoy spending time at the beach, walking around the suburb and discovering all the hidden treasures that Sydney has to offer. 
We work full time and enjoy making things for the house in our spare time. We also love catching up with friends and cooking and baking for them.

We are both well traveled and it is our main passion, so we understand how good it feels to stay in a nice and comfortable place while your are travelling or enjoying a holiday.

Feel free to get in touch with any questions about Sydney or our apartment.
My husband, Andrew, and I are retired and enjoy our grandkids, travelling and pottering in the garden of our heritage home in this lovely suburb.

L'Abode Accommodation Specialists provide accommodation and concierge services for families, corporate clients and holiday makers where they can rent affordable accommodation to cater for all of there needs while they are either searching for long term permanent accommodation or are only living in Sydney for a short period of time.

All of our properties are fully equipped and fully furnished this includes:

 - all furnishings
 - Wifi and Internet 
 - Power
 - hotel quality luxury linen
 - welcome amenities, shampoo, conditioner, body wash, body lotion, dishwashing liquid, tablets, washing powder, tea, coffee, milk, sugar 
 -  appliances
 -  crockery
 -  cutlery
 
-  entertaining, cooking


This is to ensure this is your home away from home and that you are feeling comfortable and relaxed for your stay.

We are a family of four including two teenage boys, aged 18 & 15. We travel frequently to Europe and South Africa where we have family. Our trips are usually very busy with loads of action and sightseeing. We love the beach or bush (safari) for summer holidays and the snow for winter holidays. Our downtime invariably involves a casual restaurant and a bottle of red. In Sydney we both work hard during the week - Anton works in telecommunications and I am a marketing manager in the education sector. We also rent our own house out through AirBnB when we are travelling.

fields.location: Surry Hills, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Active and outgoing lifestyle and loving all the great bars, pubs and restaurants that Surry Hills as to offer.  I am a co owner of a management consulting firm based in Sydney and moved to Australia in 2004.

I am a girl with a business and a family, that wishes she spent more time reading great stories and playing on the beach.  I could happily spend my life developing recipes and cooking for my friends and family, but seem to spend most of it managing my international production company. I am the most fortunate person that i know!
Happy, fun loving energentic Family of six loves to travel, surf and enjoy the great outdoors.

We live in and love Bondi, and to share the joy of such a wonderful location, we have decided to let our apartment out while we are away. We are a small family and our street is filled with families - it's a village feel and great place to be.
We are from Sydney's Northern Beaches and love everything it has to offer.

I'm a Sydney based travel enthusiast, who loves to meet new people from all over the world.
I have visited or lived in the following countries:
Argentina, Australia, Brazil, Cambodia, Canada, Chile, Denmark, Egypt, England, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Hong Kong, Ireland, Israel, Italy, Japan, Laos, Malaysia, Mexico, New Zealand, Peru, Poland, Romania, Russia, Singapore, South Africa, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Tahiti, Thailand, Uruguay, USA.
I'm always happy to talk to new people, and help out in deciding things to do, places to see, best transport options, and if time permits happy to be your food or travel guide.
I'm working on improving my Spanish, Portuguese and Japanese.

We are a family of three. Two mums and daughter. We have lived in Sydney all our lives and love to travel as much as we can. We work in the creative field. Love the adventure of traveling and experiencing other cultures. Absorbing the food, language, smells, visual and audible delights this amazing world has to offer. We are listing our home on Airbnb so guests can experience this wonderful area and live like a local in this incredible city. The city centre is only a 15minute walk from our door! We ask that all visitors be mindful and respect of our surroundings and our neighbours, as we would if we were to stay in their home.

we are  an active retired Aussie business couple , love to travel,  but love also being in our bushy retreat in suburbia Sydney.Our children are all grown and long since fled the 'nest' so we have room to host guests love native animals, bike riding, good food and healthy lifestyle
Born and breed in Sydney but have travelled the world :-)

I am an aging performing artist.
Still got it.....!

We moved from Berlin to Sydney a while ago - and are having the time of our lives! We work in the city and stay by the beach, living the Australian dream. 

We love travel, good food, wine, surfing and live music. Chilling with friends in the garden, listening to nice tunes while sipping on a cold beer and waiting for steaks to cook on the barbie - those are the nights we probably like the most.
We are a family of four who love the beach!

fields.location: Rose Bay, New South Wales, Australia

fields.about: When we discovered Mackeral we couldn’t believe that such a beautiful and secluded spot could exist within an hours drive from central Sydney. Claudia and I instantly fell in love with Mackeral and over the years have introduced many friends to this piece of paradise.

fields.location: Potts Point, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Mature, wise woman - loves living in the middle of everything, and spending time with friends and family. Very happy to share some of the good things in my life.

I like connecting with nature, history and culture, and hope to visit places like New Zealand, India, Europe and Singapore.
