I like to read crime fiction that critiques the society we live in as well as non-fiction on the same subject. My favorite shows include all of Shaun Micallef's shows, most of the Chaser, The Castle, Roy & HG, The Wire, The Bill, Spooks, Call the Midwife, Little Britain, The Young Ones, Allo Allo (1970's). I love creative food.

I respect privacy and diversity. The most important thing is to provide my guests with decent, comfortable accommodation. However, I am interested in your background and story if you are up for a chat.

Hi there! I own a photography and web development studio. I am also an avid traveller, so I am often on the go. I am interested in offering my house for holiday stays in the lovely suburb of Annandale, in Sydney's Inner West. 

You will find the house stocked with my favourite things... photographs, cookbooks, pantry supplies, knitting patterns, artwork and a VERY comfy lounge. You will also have access to a lovely garden for relaxing in the quiet while in the heart of Sydney.
Fitness fanatic, beach loving and obsessed with home magazines. We also have two (Website hidden by Airbnb) life is one hectic ride,!!
I'm a very laid back kind of guy that enjoys hanging out with friends and making the most of living in beautiful Sydney.
Husband and father of two boys.  We enjoy the beach and outdoor lifestyle of living on the Northern beaches as well as boating, fishing and entertaining at home.

fields.location: Surry Hills, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about:
Lively and very social lady living in Sydney. I work in the music industry and music is a big part of my life.
I love living in Surry Hills and I know you will love my little pad too.

Outgoing, well travelled, have been hosting for about 5 years now and enjoy having guests to stay in Woollahra. I have lived in 5 countries myself and love the beach and playing sport. I work 3 days a week, live in Sydney and visit France every July. Please note my response may take 8 hours due to the time difference from Europe and USA to Sydney. My friend Jean Jacques will meet the guests at the French apartment.
The Paradise Beach House is dedicated to providing it's guests the most enjoyable, pleasant and relaxing stay possible.

Hi there!  Currently I am a stay at home mum looking after our 4 year old daughter and 8 year old son but before motherhood I worked in the banking industry.  My husband keeps himself busy running an architectural practice with 2 partners, it is a local practice which is good so the kids get to see him!
We love the beach, getting out for a walk, a spot of gardening and having friends over for a BBQ. We are very excited to show you a little piece of our world!
Don't get so busy making a living that you forget to make a life -- Dolly Parton
Travel bugs!

Open-minded, healthy, happy camper and world traveller...over 60 countries visited so far on my bucket list of 100 countries. Syria (pre-war) and Kenya two of my most loved. Lived a decade too in the land of the rising sun.

Passionate about art, design, yoga, fashion, interior decorating vintage cinema, antique books and other more geeky interests like cricket, sewing and baking. Have a little store on Etsy selling cushions for the great outdoors. Enjoy devoting some of my free time to volunteering and feel doing some good is everyone's responsibility, and joy.  

Bit of a undercover greenie, choosing not to own a car - going instead with the ever reliable 'foot falcon'. Luckily home is a two minute walk to the beach and bus...going vehicle-free is easy in North Bondi!

I'm originally from Germany, but moved to Sydney 6 years ago for work and am now a permanent resident, calling Sydney home. I'd say I know the city and surrounds really well and can give you great advice on what to do and where to go that goes beyond what the guidebooks tell you. I organize a lot of activities for my group of friends, so the likelihood is high that you can come along to something if you like. :)

I dive, surf, love to travel, good food, and I'm a lover of good wine.

 I also absolutely adore animals, I'm a dog person by heart but ended up adopting a kitten that I love dearly as well. 

When you request to stay with me, it would be really nice to know a bit about you - especially when you're requesting to stay for a long time :) much appreciated!
Number one on my bucket list is whale shark diving at the Ningaloo Reef - happening soon!

Update: I just returned from a trip around the world. This trip has been absolutely amazing and has really fuelled my passion for traveling and meeting like minded travellers. It also made me resign from my corporate job and start my own business related to the wine industry (well, I'm in the midst of that!), because I wanted to do something that I'm passionate about, not just something that pays the bills. If you're in the same mindset, definitely get in touch :)
Have been a Civil Engineer for 45 years working as a Contractor on Ports and Bridges.  Now semi retired and design and construct tensioned membrane structures.

Hi,
I'm Lisa. I'm a mum to 2 girls and a wife to a busy lawyer. We've lived in Bronte for 6 years. We love living here. The house is great for kids. We love being such a close walk to the beach and just a quick walk or bus to Bondi Junction. 

We hope that you will like our house as much as we do. 

We love using Airbnb for our own travel around Australia or overseas.

My husband and I live by the beach in Sydney with our two young daughters. Originally from the UK I moved to Australia twelve years ago after I fell in love with the laid back lifestyle, beautiful beaches and summery weather. Living in Clovelly is a dream, we spend our weekends playing with the kids, surfing, swimming or eating out with friends. We love to travel, which is why we listed our home on airbnb. We've already used airbnb ourselves across Paris, New York, Rome, Nice, London and Amsterdam so decided we'd give the same opportunity to people wanting to stay in Sydney.

Hi, my name is Joy and I look forward to welcoming you as my guest.

We live downstairs and rent out our lovely flat upstairs which is fully contained and separate from our living accommodation. But don't worry, we leave our guests in peace but often invite our guests for a drink in the balmy summer months.    

You will love Coogee with its array of cafes and restaurants with a beautiful beach immediately opposite. 

Please contact me if I can help you in any way.

See you soon.
Joy

Matthew and I are happy positive people full of energy. We met nearly 10 years ago whilst I was exploring the world and Matt (who is English & was working in London) was a surprise addition to my suitcase home. We welcomed baby Hunter in September and are besotted.
We love the sunny outdoor Sydney lifestyle and will often start the day with a run, swim & coffee at The Boathouse , before Matt catches the bus into the city.
Since moving into our home we have renovated & lovingly restored each room to create a stylish yet cosy home we are proud of. We love food and often have friends around for casual dinner parties.
We feel very lucky & hope to share the joy of our home with like minded souls.

I'm from Sydney Australia. I'm a music teacher who loves all styles of music - western art music, world music, jazz, rock. I love going to concerts and visiting art galleries, reading, walking, good food and experiencing other cultures.
Peter from Sydney Australia, I am 6'8" :) We have a few holiday homes on the east coast of Australia, we do not use them very often, so thought I would put them to some use.

Hi there, Born in NZ to a long line of danish vikings, I moved to Australia when I was 17 and then to London when I was 20...

Ever since then I've been addicted to travelling and bounced around the world non stop for about 4 years during which time I backpacked to over 90 countries, became a Dive Instructor in Thailand and eventually decided to commute between London and Sydney for the summers on both sides of the earth. I trade forex in my spare time, Background in Sales and Marketing, Building Construction and Renovations, IT Project Management and studied Clinical Nutrition, I'm now 32

Hello! I'm Chris. My partner Brett and I produce and manage a circus/cabaret/variety show and have travelled extensively with it over the last ten years. Our work often takes us to some wonderful locations around the world, and we have toured throughout much of Europe and North America. Brett grew up in a sleepy idyllic town on the beach called Moonta in South Australia, and I am originally from beautiful Vancouver, Canada.

We call Australia home, although we don't often get to spend as much time there as we would like, because of work. We now live between Sydney, Melbourne and London. We have been lucky enough to get to present the show over several years in Sydney and fell in love with the Potts Point area, which is why we jumped when the opportunity to purchase this apartment came up. We also recently purchased an iconic property in the beautiful beach town of Brunswick Heads, New South Wales.

We love travelling and after having stayed in many hotel rooms and apartments over the years, we definitely know what we look for when staying away from home, and we have tried our best to make our homes as comfortable, well-stocked and convenient for guests as possible. We look forward to hearing from you!

fields.location: North Curl Curl, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: Life motto,"Never give up"
I'm an art director who runs his own boutique digital agency in Sydney. I love where I live and am happy to share the experience with others :)

I am an Australian woman in my early forties and share the house with my british husband and two small children ( 4 and 6).  We are a relaxed and friendly family who enjoy the outdoor life sunny Sydney provides.

We are a family of 3, Kylie, Nathaniel (Nat) and Louis (our toddler son) we live between Bondi and the Central Coast. Together we love travelling, the beach, being outdoors, eating out, spending time with our friends and family.
Young family, kids aged 16, 14 and 11
From Paris originally, I've lived in Sydney over 10 years now. As you can see from the places i'm offering, i like different.

fields.location: North Balgowlah, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: We are an International family of two adults and three children born in four different countries: Germany, Australia, Japan and Denmark. Hence we travel a fair bit to keep up with languages and being with our families as far spread as Florida, Germany and Denmark. We are quite active and love the beach life style.
I'm a Welshman who's been living in Sydney, Australia for 12 years now. I'm a freelance photographer that loves sport and music and travels whenever possible.

We are a French couple who fell in love with Sydney 15 years ago. We work full time and take every other opportunity to go out, relax and experience the Sydney lifestyle.
We enjoy walking everywhere, to trendy local cafes and restaurants, to the movies. We like spending our weekends to the parks or to the beach for picnics and barbecues.

I have been hosting Airbnb guests from all over the globe since 2012.  I've worked in the Hospitality for many years in various forms, having that natural desire to provide my customers / guests  with the best experience possible. I am currently working full time in the CBD but when not working I like to explore Sydney's food and art scene, nature, keep fit, and travel to places off the beaten track .  
I am reasonably well travelled, however there are still many more places to see and things to do. Besides many and varied trips within Australia, I have traveled to Borneo, Canada, US  (all but 2 states) Thailand, Italy, England, France, Switzerland,  Japan and my all time favourite trip was Africa in 2012 where I climbed Mt Kilimanjaro. 

I love cooking, and entertaining, enjoy movies when I have the time. I am not much of a reader but do enjoy a good biography or non fiction from time to time. 
I enjoy meeting new people and getting to know them but also am delighted to be able to contribute in a positive way to your experience in Sydney. (sorry for the essay!  The indepth profile description is because I host in my own home where people share my space, so I like people to get a feel for who I am. Its not so applicable for people renting my 'entire house' option in Potts Point.

Jessica is a yoga teacher, author and mum to two senior school age boys.  
Steve runs an investment business in Sydney.
We will make your stay here enjoyable and easy with help available when needed.

I'm a busy working Mum of two little girls who light up my life. We are fortunate to live in a wonderful place near the beach, we love to swim and play outdoors. We also love to travel and enjoy overseas adventures when we can.

I am easy going. I love travelling, gardening, photography, fishing, tennis, cooking
 ( eating ) swimming, cycling.

I am a woman who loves to entertain & particularly enjoys cooking  international travelling & being outdoors.
Being an animal lover you will need to cope with a rather shy kitten
I love movies, theatre, fine dining in particular & I try to walk 3/4 Kilometres per day
I believe the best is yet to come as far as life is concerned 
Looking forward to enjoying your company & a fine drop of Pinot

I like long walks on the beach, sushi, nights by the fire, friends say I'm funny... Haha, just kidding. I am responsible, employed, neat and respectful, non-smoker, no drugs, drinking is pretty much restricted to a couple glasses of Red these days, love conversation and hanging out with new people. Originally from the USA. I live in Bondi Beach, Sydney, Australia, but travel so much these days that I always feel "up in the air." In my 30's, internet entrepreneur and investor. Well-read, love movies, and travel.

Hello!
 
Comfy quiet 2 bedroom apartment with balcony, perfect for the young travelling family. Easy walk to Parramatta centre, shops, trains and buses. Apartment situated in a great location and with the M4 just down the road (but I promise you, you don't hear any traffic!) it's in a perfect position to do day trips. The Blue Mountains are just half an hour away by car (or by train), and Sydney City is 20mins away by train.

Hi I'm a sydney resident for 49 yrs.  I work as an advocate for the environment  and great ideas. I'm also an artisan, a company director, a gardener.  I am happy to share my beautiful spaces and places with you.

4 continents, 27 countries, 60+ cities and thousands of kilometres covered, I have accrued an endless supply of memories abroad that I wish to expand on through my active involvement within the dynamic and exciting Airbnb community. 

An infatuation with travelling abroad to foreign destinations, seeing unique sights and experiencing different cultures and cuisines is a universal epidemic that crosses continents. 

As a host I take great pride in sharing the beautiful sights, spectacular views and glowing warmth of my home city of Sydney.  Having been a member since September of 2013, I have thoroughly enjoyed playing an active part in the Airbnb Community and welcome you to my humble abode.
Minja Suh from Australia, originally from South Korea.
Love spending time with my family, great art, yoga and travel.

I love the outdoors hence why I have changed careers from being a travel agent to a fitness professional. My heart continues to tell me to help people and that is now my life long goal. I have travelled the world for work and continue to travel for leisure however living the beach life is where I need to settle and be now. 
The home I have made for myself is my sanctuary and I enjoy sharing it with others. I believe there is no point in having a nice little home that cannot be shared with others which is why when I'm away, I would like to offer my little piece of sanctuary with you.
Health, Fitness and Wellbeing is extremely important to me which is where my motto of "Look Good. Feel Great" stems from. Let the relaxation of the ocean, the scenic coastal walks and the cosy cafes make you Look Good and Feel Great when you stay at Surfside Beach House.

I have travelled the world (mostly on motorbikes) and are happy to share our home with visitors. I run my own business from our home office so I am here most days. I have two 2 teenage girls and their cats. We all love living in Sydney even though I am a Kiwi and it's great getting to know people from other countries. This is a beautiful place to live and we enjoy all the bush walks on our doorstep.

This is the first time that I have listed my place. Let me tell you guys a little about myself. I am 48 years old. I was born and brought up in Sydney in a very very Italian house. I am a video maker specialising in medical/hospital films so I spend a great deal of time travelling. Hence the reason I have decided to list my place. This is actually my home. I am typing this email at the moment from my sunny balcony. If you are living here it means that I am actually travelling or living at my girlfriend's house.

I am an award winning  TV Producer of many years experience. I travel widely with my work and enjoy it greatly. I surf, ski love to eat in great restaurants and strive to  enjoy each day as it comes.

My other great passion is my family!

PWB

I have lived in various places in this area for 25 years and can't think of anywhere else in Sydney I would rather live. My teen children and I love the community feel, having friends in walking distance and all the indoor and outdoor activities in walking distance.
As for travelling myself, I have been to lots of countries. My last trip was to America and last year visited three of the music towns - Austin, Memphis, Nashville.
I am into simplicity on as many fronts of my life as I can, yoga, sustainability, cycling, animal protection.  Bit of a hippy by the sounds of it, maybe that's why I liked the stained glass that is on the deck of my house. 
I love the idea of the sharing economy, and want to help you enjoy your stay and make the most of all this area and Sydney has to offer.
Young at heart, welcoming and energetic, and so is the dog!

Will and I are both from Sydney Australia. We bought this lovely one bedroom apartment in Redfern in 2013 and we absolutely love living there. 

We are looking for some lovely, responsible adults to rent our space over Christmas and New Year while we are on holidays. 

We have lived in many different places and we love travelling and exploring the world. Finola is a marketing professional who has gone back to uni to pursue architecture and Will manages an Art Gallery in Elizabeth Bay. We are both travel enthusiasts, art collectors, amateur musicians, theatre and cinema attendees, cyclists and lovers of all food and entertaining (Will is the chef in the couple). 

We had a wonderful experience with airbnb in Paris staying in a typically Parisian apartment in the Marais and we were very pleased with the guests who rented our apartment for the last 3 summers.

We would like to share our home so someone else can have a wonderful experience in Sydney.
Quiet family from Cremorne that enjoy travelling.
We are a professional couple who work in Sydney's CBD. We love traveling and meeting new people, so we decided to make our spare room available to other travelers!
I am originally from Canada, living in Australia. I am a full-time science student at University and I work at a soap store. I love live music and cooking.
We are sub-letting while away so someone can enjoy this great location.

fields.location: Potts Point, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I am a writer based in Sydney and regularly travel.

Hi, I'm a creative person, mother of Louis age 5 and Manon age 2. I like warm, inviting environments with character, That is how I would describe my own home. On holidays I seek  nature, culture and good food. I enjoy markets and music festivals and look forward to experiencing these things with my kids.
I teach kids sewing and so I aspire to find a slower pace of life more in tune with nature and the environment'.

Fun
Optimist 
Interested in the world 
Creative & humanistic– family background of artists, lawyers and doctors.
Decent, honest and dependable

I enjoy the exploring the world.
I am passionate about travel and a lover of nature.
I'm friendly, quiet and artisitic. I enjoy good food, good friends, sunshine and Sydney's glorious beaches. I love nothing more than to travel.

We are a family of 5. Mum (Justine), Dad (Neil) and three daughters (Ella, Amy and Anna) aged 11, 9 and 5. In 2015, we are embarking on a lot of travel before our eldest daughter, Ella, starts 'big' school !  We will be relying on a lot of hosts, and would like to thank you in advance for letting us stay at your place; you can be assured we will treat your property with respect and leave it as we find it.

I live in Sydney, have my own business, am a volunteer lifeguard at Bronte beach, am married and love riding my Vespa and swimming in Sydneys rock ocean pools ! I love travel, sports and speak several languages.

I’ve lived in Sydney for the past twelve years, although I’m originally from Brisbane.  My husband Delzad (pictured) and I LOVE travel, and are lucky to have travelled for work as well as personal pleasure over the years.  Some of my most favourite destinations so far are Mumbai, Tokyo, Luang Prabang, Lalibela and the Simien Mountains, Istanbul, Berlin, and Maui.

We've also recently had a little boy Elliott, who we are hoping inherits our love of travel!
I am a quiet yogi and solo mum who enjoys the beach and friends and working from home.

fields.location: Bondi Beach, New South Wales, Australia

fields.about: I love to live the manly lifestyle, sun, surf, yoga, drinks with friends and time with my family.

I am a design professional and a Sydney local, and my well traveled husband is a San Francisco native. My young family and I have lived in Darlinghurst for 7 years, love to travel and appreciate a great 'base camp' to explore from. We think our apartment on a beautifully quiet tree lined street on the boundaries of Darlinghurst and Paddington is perfectly placed to explore some of Sydney's great restaurants, cafes, markets, beaches and beyond.
We look forward to meeting you when you stay!

Hi there.
My friends call me the "Aussie Ambassador" as I love this country so much and am constantly singing its praises!! I work in travel, helping people have the holiday of a lifetime seeing and experiencing this country.
I am a very active, outgoing person and love where I live as it's away from the hustle and bustle of the city and close to some of the best beaches in the world.
My place is a cosy yet spacious apartment and I encourage anyone who stays here to make themselves at home.
Professional working in the social justice sector.

Hi I'm Lisa. I'm an active, friendly and easy-going person. I have 2 kids, Jack (12 years) and Ellie (10 years), who are involved in various sports so we are quite busy. We're also a pretty quiet family although it can get noisy sometimes with the kids.
We have enjoyed hosting English Language students and travellers from various countries for a number of years and love having people enjoy our home and the area. 
I work in the travel industry so have a passion for travel as well as photography
Family of 6. Professional, love to travel.

We are a young family who love to travel and have our extended families scattered all over the world. We try and jump on a plane at least once a year as there is always a new destination we want to see, experience like a local, and easily fall in love with.
As a host, we understand you need to feel at home where you lay your head and our place offers that comfort and familiarity.
My motto in life is "treat people the way you want to be treated"

Our family love the Manly/Fairlight area - there's always something to do, from surfing and stand up paddle boarding to eating out at the fabulous restaurants and cafes in the area. It's perfect for adventure loving families like ourselves. 

Our beautiful 1860's sandstone terrace is an oasis from this holiday hot spot and is too beautiful to keep to ourselves. You'll love the character of our home and its  newly renovated modern conveniences. We're able to rent it out whenever we are away visiting family or traveling overseas.

I am originally a country girl from North West NSW, and have been living in Sydney for the past 10 years. I have owned my unit for 5 years now - how time fly's!! I am sporty and love to stay active. I play tennis quite regularly (2-3x/week), and also do Pilates classes, swim, run, walk - pretty much what ever I can get involved in! I also love to cook, have my friends over to enjoy a glass or 2, or just read a good book.

I have been fortunate enough in my life to have travelled a bit. In my 20's I did the usual pilgrimage to London, where I worked for 2 years. I also did 5 summers working at a kids camp in Maine, USA, a full ski season in Whistler, Canada (I skied 70 days that season - wahoo!!) and a wonderful Eurail trip through France, Italy, Greece and Turkey! More recently I have been exploring South East Asia (Bangkok, Jakarta, Singapore, Chang Mai), and New Zealand.

I am hoping by signing up with Air BnB, that I can repay some of the kindness I got while travelling!

We're about a family who loves to travel and have recently listed our Sydney and Melbourne apartments with Airbnb. We also enjoy staying at places with high standards and cleanliness of a 5 star apartment, the way we wish to live when we travel.

fields.location: North Bondi, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: We are a couple living in Sydney who like eating well, travelling and getting the most out of life :)
I live in Sydney with my husband David, We both enjoy eating out, drinking the local wines, gardening, walking and generally making the most of everything that beautiful Sydney has to offer.

I love travelling, I am passionate about environmental issues, and I am a fabric artist . I love the outdoors and I love the beach. I am also very Australian - open and friendly  - happiest barefoot and in nature. I share my time between London and Australia and our children who are on three continents. I miss our wonderful, spacious, bright, airy and colourful home in Manly and our tranquil rural wildlife sanctuary retreat by the beach south of Sydney and we let both of them on Airbnb.  Our house in Manly looks like us I think - bright, full of evidence of our travels and airy. The cottage on our property at Meringo is cosy, secluded and surrounded by nature.

fields.location: Dolans Bay, New South Wales, Australia
fields.about: I am from Melbourne however live in Sydney with my husband and three boys aged 1, 5 & 8. We are an active family who enjoy the out-doors and travelling.
